the assessment. The assessment will be documented and stored with the relevant maintenance schedule documentation”. Updated form numbers FM-QC-029, FM-QC-030, FM-QC-123, FM-QC-124 and FM-QC-125 to new template and included new logo in header.','QC-022D','FM-QC-027 : Instrument Categorisation.\nFM-QC-029 : Instrument Repair Request.\nFM-QC-030 : Instrument Repair Record Log.\nFM-QC-123 : Preventative Maintenance Annual Schedule.\nFM-QC-124 : Preventative Maintenance Monthly Schedule.\nFM-QC-125 : Instrument PM Record – Category A Instruments.\nQA-005 : Assigning Equipment Identification Number.\nVA-002 : Qualification Procedure.\nQM-007 : Calibration Policy.\nQM-013 : Change Control.\nUSP <1058> Analytical Instrument Qualification.\nEudralex Chapter 6 and Annex 15.\nQM-004 : Good Documentation Practices.\nQA-002 : Contract Service Provider Management.\nQM-010 : Investigation System.\nMF-008 : Labelling of Material, Product, Room and Equipment.\nFM-QM-020 : Calibration label (SOP QM-007).\nFM-QM-112 : OUT OF USE label (SOP QM-007).\nFM-MF-040 : Preventative Maintenance Status label.'),(87,'QC-023A','OPERATION AND CALIBRATION OF VWR 609-0185 STOPWATCHES','The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and calibration of the VWR 609-0185 stopwatches.\n---\nThe scope is limited to the use of the timers by the QC/ARD Department in Amneal Ireland.\n---\nThe purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and calibration of the VWR 609-0185 stopwatches.\n---\nRevision: QC-023, Date: 30-Sep-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued.\nRevision: QC-023A, Date: 2017-12-01, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Update SOP logo and removed reference to Appendix throughout.\n---\nIt is the responsibility of all personnel within QC/ARD to adhere to the requirements outlined in this procedure.\nAll QC/ARD personnel must ensure that they are trained on the current revision of the SOP.\nIt is the responsibility of the Laboratory Manager (or designee) to ensure that the SOP is followed by all QC/ARD personnel.\nIt is the responsibility of the QC Manager (or designee) to ensure that all QC/ARD personnel are trained on the current revision of the SOP.','QC-023A Operation and Calibration of VWR 609-0185 Stopwatches.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and calibration of the VWR 609-0185 stopwatches.','The scope is limited to the use of the timers by the QC/ARD Department in Amneal Ireland.','The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and calibration of the VWR 609-0185 stopwatches.','QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','It is the responsibility of all personnel within QC/ARD to adhere to the requirements outlined in this procedure.\nAll QC/ARD personnel must ensure that they are trained on the current revision of the SOP.\nIt is the responsibility of the Laboratory Manager (or designee) to ensure that the SOP is followed by all QC/ARD personnel.\nIt is the responsibility of the QC Manager (or designee) to ensure that all QC/ARD personnel are trained on the current revision of the SOP.','Revision: QC-023, Date: 30-Sep-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued.\nRevision: QC-023A, Date: 2017-12-01, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Update SOP logo and removed reference to Appendix throughout.','QC-023','FM-QC-021 : Calibration Log for Stopwatches.'),(88,'QC-024C','OPERATION AND MONITORING OF LIEBHERR FRIDGE IN THE QC/ARD LABORATORY','The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and monitoring of the Liebherr fridge.\n---\nThe scope is limited to fridges used by the QC/ARD Department in Amneal Ireland.\n---\nThe purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and monitoring of the Liebherr fridge.\n---\nRevision: QC-024, Date: 17-Jan-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued.\nRevision: QC-024A, Date: 26-Aug-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated SOP to introduce new Amneal Logo. Formatted header to remove preparers name. Section 5.3 - Updated 5.3.5 to remove Fridge Contents logbook, Appendix 1 (FM-QC-024) and to include Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-015). Updated 5.3.7 to remove Fridge Contents logbook, Appendix 1 (FM-QC-024) and to include Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-016). Added 5.3.8 and 5.3.9. Section 5.4 - Update 5.4.1 to include daily alarm check and instruction that data logger to be downloaded in the event of an alarm being encountered. Update 5.4.2 to clarify that the temperature of the fridge will be recorded every 10 minutes. Update 5.4.3 to state that the data logger will be placed in a representative location within the fridge. Section 5.4.4 – include instruction stating that the temperature data from the data logger will be downloaded on a monthly basis and that calibration cert for data logger will be saved also. Remove section 5.4.4. Add section 5.4.5 to state that all deviations from acceptance criteria should be recorded in FM-QC-025. Section 5.5 - Add clarification that maintenance is documented in FM-QC-025 in point 5.5.5. Section 5.6 - Add section in relation to use of data loggers. References Section - Remove appendix references. Remove reference to FM-QC-024 and SOP-035. Insert references to FM-QC-015 and FM-QC-016.\nRevision: QC-024B, Date: 16-Jul-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-051, Reason: Section 5.3.5 updated to All standards stored in the fridge must be recorded in the Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-015). Section 5.3.6 updated to All items stored in the fridge must be securely sealed and clearly labelled. Section 5.3.8 and 5.3.9 was removed. Section 5.5.1 Prior to performing any maintenance remove samples / standards from the fridge. Complete the clean within a maximum period of 30 minutes to minimise the time that standards are outside of the refrigerated conditions. Section 5.5.2 updated to Clean the inside, equipment and outer walls with lukewarm water and a small amount of detergent. Do not use abrasive or acidic cleaners or chemical solvents. Note: Fridge Clean will be performed annually prior the Fridge Calibration.\nRevision: QC-024C, Date: 2021-07-01, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-049, Reason: Section 5.2 – updated instruction as per new Liebherr Fridge, AI-QC-136. Section 5.4 – added new section to describe how to operate the maximum/minimum thermometer. Section 5.5, monitoring the temperature moved from section 5.4. Section 5.5.1 - added instruction for the monitoring of the fridge using the minimum and maximum thermometer “the minimum and maximum temperatures shall be checked as per section 5.4.5 and 5.4.6. The minimum and maximum temperatures shall be recorded along with the date/time of the minimum and maximum temperatures. Section 5.5.2 - Instruction added on how to deal with excursions of temperature outside the 2°C - 8°C range. Removed section 5.6, use of temperate data loggers. Section 6.4, added reference to IT-014. Updated FM-QC-025 to include new process for monitoring refrigerator temperatures with minimum/maximum thermometer.\n---\nIt is the responsibility of all personnel within QC/ARD to adhere to the requirements outlined in this procedure.\nAll QC/ARD personnel must ensure that they are trained on the current revision of the SOP.\nIt is the responsibility of the Laboratory Manager (or designee) to ensure that the SOP is followed by all QC/ARD personnel.\nIt is the responsibility of the Laboratory Manager (or designee) to ensure that all QC/ARD personnel are trained on the current revision of the SOP.','QC-024C Op & Monitoring of LIEBHERR Fridge in QC-ARD Lab.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and monitoring of the Liebherr fridge.','The scope is limited to fridges used by the QC/ARD Department in Amneal Ireland.','The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and monitoring of the Liebherr fridge.','QC/ARD: Quality Control/ Analytical Research & Development.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','It is the responsibility of all personnel within QC/ARD to adhere to the requirements outlined in this procedure.\nAll QC/ARD personnel must ensure that they are trained on the current revision of the SOP.\nIt is the responsibility of the Laboratory Manager (or designee) to ensure that the SOP is followed by all QC/ARD personnel.\nIt is the responsibility of the Laboratory Manager (or designee) to ensure that all QC/ARD personnel are trained on the current revision of the SOP.','Revision: QC-024, Date: 17-Jan-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued.\nRevision: QC-024A, Date: 26-Aug-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated SOP to introduce new Amneal Logo. Formatted header to remove preparers name. Section 5.3 - Updated 5.3.5 to remove Fridge Contents logbook, Appendix 1 (FM-QC-024) and to include Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-015). Updated 5.3.7 to remove Fridge Contents logbook, Appendix 1 (FM-QC-024) and to include Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-016). Added 5.3.8 and 5.3.9. Section 5.4 - Update 5.4.1 to include daily alarm check and instruction that data logger to be downloaded in the event of an alarm being encountered. Update 5.4.2 to clarify that the temperature of the fridge will be recorded every 10 minutes. Update 5.4.3 to state that the data logger will be placed in a representative location within the fridge. Section 5.4.4 – include instruction stating that the temperature data from the data logger will be downloaded on a monthly basis and that calibration cert for data logger will be saved also. Remove section 5.4.4. Add section 5.4.5 to state that all deviations from acceptance criteria should be recorded in FM-QC-025. Section 5.5 - Add clarification that maintenance is documented in FM-QC-025 in point 5.5.5. Section 5.6 - Add section in relation to use of data loggers. References Section - Remove appendix references. Remove reference to FM-QC-024 and SOP-035. Insert references to FM-QC-015 and FM-QC-016.\nRevision: QC-024B, Date: 16-Jul-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-051, Reason: Section 5.3.5 updated to All standards stored in the fridge must be recorded in the Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-015). Section 5.3.6 updated to All items stored in the fridge must be securely sealed and clearly labelled. Section 5.3.8 and 5.3.9 was removed. Section 5.5.1 Prior to performing any maintenance remove samples / standards from the fridge. Complete the clean within a maximum period of 30 minutes to minimise the time that standards are outside of the refrigerated conditions. Section 5.5.2 updated to Clean the inside, equipment and outer walls with lukewarm water and a small amount of detergent. Do not use abrasive or acidic cleaners or chemical solvents. Note: Fridge Clean will be performed annually prior the Fridge Calibration.\nRevision: QC-024C, Date: 2021-07-01, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-049, Reason: Section 5.2 – updated instruction as per new Liebherr Fridge, AI-QC-136. Section 5.4 – added new section to describe how to operate the maximum/minimum thermometer. Section 5.5, monitoring the temperature moved from section 5.4. Section 5.5.1 - added instruction for the monitoring of the fridge using the minimum and maximum thermometer “the minimum and maximum temperatures shall be checked as per section 5.4.5 and 5.4.6. The minimum and maximum temperatures shall be recorded along with the date/time of the minimum and maximum temperatures. Section 5.5.2 - Instruction added on how to deal with excursions of temperature outside the 2°C - 8°C range. Removed section 5.6, use of temperate data loggers. Section 6.4, added reference to IT-014. Updated FM-QC-025 to include new process for monitoring refrigerator temperatures with minimum/maximum thermometer.','QC-024B','FM-QC-025 : Fridge Temperature Logbook.\nFM-QC-016 : Reference Standards Monthly Review Log.\nFM-QC-015 : Incoming Reference Standards Logbook.\nIT-014 : Synchronisation of time for standalone equipment/instrument.'),(89,'xxxx','Travel and Expense Policy','To provide guidelines and procedures for employees who travel and incur business-related expenses.\n---\nApplies to all Amneal Ireland employees and contractors travelling on Amneal Ireland related business.\n---\nEmployees must book travel through Heffernan Travel. Corporate credit cards are issued to frequent travelers. Reimbursement for business-related expenses is provided. Non-compliance may result in delayed or denied reimbursement or termination. Airline reservations should be made at least 2 weeks in advance. Economy class for UK and Europe, Business class for flights over 10 hours. Rental cars should be intermediate size. Use of personal cars is reimbursable at 39.86 cents/km. Lodging and meals are reimbursable within limits. Travel insurance is provided by the company.\n---\nEmployees must comply with the policy. Managers must approve travel and expenses. Site Director must authorize travel and approve expense reports.','Amneal Ireland Travel Expense Policy.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'To provide guidelines and procedures for employees who travel and incur business-related expenses.','Applies to all Amneal Ireland employees and contractors travelling on Amneal Ireland related business.','Employees must book travel through Heffernan Travel. Corporate credit cards are issued to frequent travelers. Reimbursement for business-related expenses is provided. Non-compliance may result in delayed or denied reimbursement or termination. Airline reservations should be made at least 2 weeks in advance. Economy class for UK and Europe, Business class for flights over 10 hours. Rental cars should be intermediate size. Use of personal cars is reimbursable at 39.86 cents/km. Lodging and meals are reimbursable within limits. Travel insurance is provided by the company.',NULL,'Employees must comply with the policy. Managers must approve travel and expenses. Site Director must authorize travel and approve expense reports.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(90,'EMP-HANDBOOK-2022','Employee Handbook August 2022','To provide employees with a comprehensive guide on company policies, procedures, and expectations to ensure a productive and compliant work environment.\n---\nAll employees of Amneal Ireland Limited and Amneal EU Limited.\n---\nEqual Opportunity, Conflict of Interest, Termination of Employment, Time & Attendance, Compensation & Benefits, Leave Provisions, Key Company Policies, Health & Safety, Code of Conduct\n---\nThis handbook supersedes and replaces all previous handbooks, personnel policies, practices, and guidelines. Effective August 2022.\n---\nEmployees: To adhere to the policies outlined in the handbook. Management: To enforce and ensure compliance with the policies. HR Department: To provide guidance and support on policy-related matters.','Employee Handbook August 2022.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'To provide employees with a comprehensive guide on company policies, procedures, and expectations to ensure a productive and compliant work environment.','All employees of Amneal Ireland Limited and Amneal EU Limited.','Equal Opportunity, Conflict of Interest, Termination of Employment, Time & Attendance, Compensation & Benefits, Leave Provisions, Key Company Policies, Health & Safety, Code of Conduct','Equal Opportunity: Ensuring no discrimination based on gender, civil status, family status, sexual orientation, age, disability, race, religion, or membership of the Traveller community. Conflict of Interest: Avoiding activities that conflict with the company’s business interests. Termination of Employment: Procedures for termination and payment in lieu of notice. Time & Attendance: Policies on working hours, time off, and flexible working. Compensation & Benefits: Details on base pay, bonuses, and benefits. Leave Provisions: Policies on annual leave, sick leave, maternity leave, etc. Key Company Policies: Anti-discrimination, anti-harassment, and disciplinary policies. Health & Safety: Ensuring a safe workplace. Code of Conduct: Ethical guidelines for employees.','Employees: To adhere to the policies outlined in the handbook. Management: To enforce and ensure compliance with the policies. HR Department: To provide guidance and support on policy-related matters.','This handbook supersedes and replaces all previous handbooks, personnel policies, practices, and guidelines. Effective August 2022.','Revision 14','Employment Equality Acts 1988-2015, Equal Status Acts 2000-2018, Minimum Notice and Terms of Employment Act 1973-2005, Unfair Dismissals Act 1977-2005, Terms of Employment Information Act 1994-2012, Safety, Health and Welfare at Work Act 2005.'),(91,'HOLIDAY-SELL-SCHEME','Annual Leave Sell Scheme Policy','To allow employees to sell a portion of their unused Annual Leave for monetary value while ensuring compliance with the Organisation of Working Time Act.\n---\nAll Amneal employees who have successfully completed their probationary period.\n---\nEmployees can sell up to 3 days/24 hours of unused Annual Leave. Requests must be submitted by 31 October each year. Payment is based on the employee’s hourly rate and can be paid through payroll or put towards an AVC.\n---\nThis policy introduces the Annual Leave Sell Scheme, allowing employees to sell up to 3 days of unused Annual Leave.\n---\nEmployees: Submit requests to sell Annual Leave by the deadline. HR: Process requests and ensure compliance with the policy.','Holiday Sell Scheme.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'To allow employees to sell a portion of their unused Annual Leave for monetary value while ensuring compliance with the Organisation of Working Time Act.','All Amneal employees who have successfully completed their probationary period.','Employees can sell up to 3 days/24 hours of unused Annual Leave. Requests must be submitted by 31 October each year. Payment is based on the employee’s hourly rate and can be paid through payroll or put towards an AVC.','Annual Leave: Paid time off granted to employees. AVC: Additional Voluntary Contribution to pension.','Employees: Submit requests to sell Annual Leave by the deadline. HR: Process requests and ensure compliance with the policy.','This policy introduces the Annual Leave Sell Scheme, allowing employees to sell up to 3 days of unused Annual Leave.',NULL,'Organisation of Working Time Act, Working Time Regulations.'),(92,'IT-001B','DOMAIN SECURITY ADMINISTRATION','To provide instruction and guidance for the administration of the Amneal Ireland Limited local area network (LAN) and wide area network (WAN) security devices, application and general end-user practices.\n---\nThe Amneal Ireland Limited LAN/WAN authorize users, security devices, applications, and network operating system active directory settings.\n---\n1. Enforce unique user password with minimum seven characters.\n2. Password expiry every 90 Days.\n3. System lockout threshold for invalid login attempts is Three (3).\n4. Locked-out users are automatically unlocked after 7 minutes.\n5. Users are given a generic password for password resets and are prompted to change password at first logon.\n6. Desktop and laboratory computers have local administrator password managed by IT.\n7. Anti-Virus software scans for malicious code and content.\n8. Firewall configured to prevent unauthorized intrusion.\n9. VPN access available for remote users.\n---\nIT-001 | 12-Jan-2016 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-001A | 05-May-2020 | AI-CC-18-140 | 1. Updated Amneal Logo and removed reference to Appendix\n2. Added FM-IT-053 to reference section.\n3. Removed FM-IT-001-00 from reference section.\n4. Form FM-IT-001-00 to be retired.\nIT-001B | 14-Sep-2022 | AI-CC-21-072 | 1. Add definitions section\n2. Add details for ServiceNow Self-Service Portal.\n3. Add Hiring Manager approval process\n4. Add detail for IT team /ServiceDesk to service the request.\n5. Added additional detail for usernames for employees with same name.\n---\n1. The Information Technology (IT) Manager or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\n2. It is the responsibility of Domain User and Instrument Operator to ensure login with his/her user id and logout after task completion.','IT-001B Domain Security Administration.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'To provide instruction and guidance for the administration of the Amneal Ireland Limited local area network (LAN) and wide area network (WAN) security devices, application and general end-user practices.','The Amneal Ireland Limited LAN/WAN authorize users, security devices, applications, and network operating system active directory settings.','1. Enforce unique user password with minimum seven characters.\n2. Password expiry every 90 Days.\n3. System lockout threshold for invalid login attempts is Three (3).\n4. Locked-out users are automatically unlocked after 7 minutes.\n5. Users are given a generic password for password resets and are prompted to change password at first logon.\n6. Desktop and laboratory computers have local administrator password managed by IT.\n7. Anti-Virus software scans for malicious code and content.\n8. Firewall configured to prevent unauthorized intrusion.\n9. VPN access available for remote users.','HOD: Head of Department\nIT: Information Technology\nLAN: Local Area Network\nQA: Quality Assurance\nSOP: Standard Operating Procedure\nVPN: Virtual Private Network','1. The Information Technology (IT) Manager or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\n2. It is the responsibility of Domain User and Instrument Operator to ensure login with his/her user id and logout after task completion.','IT-001 | 12-Jan-2016 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-001A | 05-May-2020 | AI-CC-18-140 | 1. Updated Amneal Logo and removed reference to Appendix\n2. Added FM-IT-053 to reference section.\n3. Removed FM-IT-001-00 from reference section.\n4. Form FM-IT-001-00 to be retired.\nIT-001B | 14-Sep-2022 | AI-CC-21-072 | 1. Add definitions section\n2. Add details for ServiceNow Self-Service Portal.\n3. Add Hiring Manager approval process\n4. Add detail for IT team /ServiceDesk to service the request.\n5. Added additional detail for usernames for employees with same name.','IT-001A','FM-IT-053 : Access & Disable Electronic System Request Form'),(93,'IT-002E','COMPUTER NETWORK ACCESS, HELPDESK AND TERMINATION','This procedure outlines the guideline for providing new computer network access, helpdesk services and network access termination for the computer network.\n---\nThis procedure applies to all employees requesting computer network access, helpdesk services and network access termination from the computer network at Amneal Ireland.\n---\n1. Requesting Secure Folder Access or changing current User Access.\n2. Requests to Helpdesk.\n3. Terminating User Profile.\n4. Transfer of GxP data from original equipment to Secure Folder.\n5. Retention of data on secure folders.\n---\nIT-002 | 12-Jan-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-002A | 21-Dec-2017 | AI-CC-17-107 | Updated purpose, scope, definitions, and procedures.\nIT-002B | 03-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-036 | Revised section 5.2 and added section 5.5.\nIT-002C | 29-Apr-2021 | AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-21-031 | Amneal Logo change, removed word ‘services’, replaced Department Head with HOD, and other revisions.\nIT-002D | 01-Jun-2021 | AI-CC-21-033 | Added ServiceNow portal details.\nIT-002E | [Date] | AI-CC-21-053, AIM-CC-21-009 | Returned Form FM-IT-027 into service and added MDI Functional Tester.\n---\n1. The Information Technology HOD or designee is responsible for the overall security of the Amneal Ireland computer network.\n2. IT team members who have administrator privileges are responsible for administering/managing security of the computer network and network folders.\n3. The respective HOD or designee is responsible for requesting network access for all new employees and requesting to revoke access for existing employees as required.\n4. The Human Resource HOD or designee is responsible for informing the IT department when an employee who has access to the computer network has been terminated or relieved from the services.\n5. The Head of QA or designee is responsible for approving access to the Quality Management folder/subfolders and secure network folders.','IT-002E Computer Network Access Helpdesk & Termination.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'This procedure outlines the guideline for providing new computer network access, helpdesk services and network access termination for the computer network.','This procedure applies to all employees requesting computer network access, helpdesk services and network access termination from the computer network at Amneal Ireland.','1. Requesting Secure Folder Access or changing current User Access.\n2. Requests to Helpdesk.\n3. Terminating User Profile.\n4. Transfer of GxP data from original equipment to Secure Folder.\n5. Retention of data on secure folders.','IT: Information Technology.\nHOD: Head of Department.\nAll Amneal Ireland Employees: Full time permanent staff.\nAll Amneal Ireland non-Employees: Directly Supervised Contractor, contract agency person with the same duties as a permanent employee.\nAll Amneal Ireland Contractors: A contractor hired by another company who provide a regular service at Amneal, for example Cleaning Contractor.','1. The Information Technology HOD or designee is responsible for the overall security of the Amneal Ireland computer network.\n2. IT team members who have administrator privileges are responsible for administering/managing security of the computer network and network folders.\n3. The respective HOD or designee is responsible for requesting network access for all new employees and requesting to revoke access for existing employees as required.\n4. The Human Resource HOD or designee is responsible for informing the IT department when an employee who has access to the computer network has been terminated or relieved from the services.\n5. The Head of QA or designee is responsible for approving access to the Quality Management folder/subfolders and secure network folders.','IT-002 | 12-Jan-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-002A | 21-Dec-2017 | AI-CC-17-107 | Updated purpose, scope, definitions, and procedures.\nIT-002B | 03-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-036 | Revised section 5.2 and added section 5.5.\nIT-002C | 29-Apr-2021 | AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-21-031 | Amneal Logo change, removed word ‘services’, replaced Department Head with HOD, and other revisions.\nIT-002D | 01-Jun-2021 | AI-CC-21-033 | Added ServiceNow portal details.\nIT-002E | [Date] | AI-CC-21-053, AIM-CC-21-009 | Returned Form FM-IT-027 into service and added MDI Functional Tester.','IT-002D','IT-001 : Domain Security Administration\nFM-IT-027 : Secure Folder Access Request form\nHR-001 : Employee Induction Process\nFM-HR-009 : Exiting Employee/Non-Employee/ Contractor Checklist'),(94,'IT-004E','DATA BACKUP, RESTORE PROCEDURE FOR SERVER SYSTEM','This procedure outlines the guidance to describe IT approach to backup and restore of the data for the server system.\n---\nThis procedure applied to software applications, data and documents held in electronic format on the server system as per Table 1 Data Backup Schedule at Amneal Ireland.\n---\n1. Backup Procedure for Acronis Backup for VMWare.\n2. Restore Procedure for Acronis Backup for VMWare.\n3. Backup schedule for Amneal Ireland Servers.\n4. Backup Storage of media.\n5. Retention of external hard drive backups for 3 months.\n---\nIT-004 | 17-Nov-2016 | -- | First Issued.\nIT-004A | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | Added details for Acronis Backup, NAS storage, and Onsite Fireproof Safe.\nIT-004B | 13-Dec-2018 | AIM-CC-18-031 | Added AMNLIECAESX04 link and details for HP Storage Works Tape Autoloader.\nIT-004C | 25-Feb-2020 | AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-19-146 | Updated definitions, added backup definitions, and updated server links.\nIT-004D | 05-Aug-2021 | AIM-CC-21-019 | Added Serialisation System (VMs) to Table 1.\nIT-004E | 01-Nov-2023 | CC-AMN-23-5881 | Updated NAS Box definition, backup and restore processes, and server assignments.\n---\n1. The designated Systems Administrator or designee is responsible for ensuring the backup and restore procedure is followed.\n2. The HOD, Information Technology or designee is responsible for ensuring compliance to this procedure.','IT-004E Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'This procedure outlines the guidance to describe IT approach to backup and restore of the data for the server system.','This procedure applied to software applications, data and documents held in electronic format on the server system as per Table 1 Data Backup Schedule at Amneal Ireland.','1. Backup Procedure for Acronis Backup for VMWare.\n2. Restore Procedure for Acronis Backup for VMWare.\n3. Backup schedule for Amneal Ireland Servers.\n4. Backup Storage of media.\n5. Retention of external hard drive backups for 3 months.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nData Backup: Making copies of data to restore the original after data loss.\nFull Backup: Complete backup of all software components.\nIncremental Backup: Copies only data changed since the last backup.\nDifferential Backup: Copies all data changed since the last full backup.\nSoftware Backup: Ensures latest and correct versions are available.\nBackup for VMWare: Complete copy of the VM server.\nBackup Interval: Frequency of backups.\nMedia: Means of storing electronic data.\nCD: Compact Disc.\nDVD: Digital Versatile Disk.\nVM: Virtual Machine.\nIT: Information Technology.\nGFS: Grandfather-Father-Son Clean-up Scheme.\nZIP: Archive file format.\nSNMP: Simple Networking Monitoring Protocol.\nFTP: File Transfer Protocol.\nIDF2: Integrated Distribution Frame 2.\nQC: Quality Control.\nRestore Procedure: Returns lost data to its original condition.\nHOD: Head of Department.\nVDMK: Virtual Machine Disk.\nESX: VMware ESXi.\nIP: Internet Protocol.\nURL: Uniform Resource Locator.\nNAS Box: Network Attached Storage Box.\nBMS: Building Management System.\nQEMS: Qualified Environmental Management System.\nLocal USB HD: Local Universal Serial Bus Hard Drive.\nFull Virtual: Restores entire virtual machine.','1. The designated Systems Administrator or designee is responsible for ensuring the backup and restore procedure is followed.\n2. The HOD, Information Technology or designee is responsible for ensuring compliance to this procedure.','IT-004 | 17-Nov-2016 | -- | First Issued.\nIT-004A | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | Added details for Acronis Backup, NAS storage, and Onsite Fireproof Safe.\nIT-004B | 13-Dec-2018 | AIM-CC-18-031 | Added AMNLIECAESX04 link and details for HP Storage Works Tape Autoloader.\nIT-004C | 25-Feb-2020 | AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-19-146 | Updated definitions, added backup definitions, and updated server links.\nIT-004D | 05-Aug-2021 | AIM-CC-21-019 | Added Serialisation System (VMs) to Table 1.\nIT-004E | 01-Nov-2023 | CC-AMN-23-5881 | Updated NAS Box definition, backup and restore processes, and server assignments.','IT-004D','IT-009 : Preventative maintenance for IT systems\nIT-015 : Empower & Instrument Server Data Backup, Archival & Verification\nFM-IT-052 : IT Fireproof Safe Access Form'),(95,'IT-005A','PROCEDURE TO INSTALL AND CONFIGURE A NETWORK SWITCH','The purpose of this procedure is to provide the standards and instructions to execute a correct and complete installation and functional verification of switches within the Amneal Ireland network.\n---\nThis procedure applies to all people involved in the installation of network switches running IOS operating system within the Amneal Ireland network.\n---\n1. Software Management: Verify correct IOS version for new switches.\n2. Generic commands for all switches: Default configuration, enable services, naming convention, management address, default gateway, console and VTY settings, MOTD banner, UDLD, logging, DNS, HTTP management, SNMP settings, NTP, VTP, VLAN configuration.\n3. Switch specific commands: Access switch, server switch, distribution switch, collapsed core/distribution switch, core switch.\n4. Example configuration: Basic switch configuration example.\n---\nIT-005 | 26-Feb-2019 | -- | First Issued.\nIT-005A | 01-Feb-2022 | -- | Updated procedure for new installations and configurations.\n---\n1. The Information Technology (IT) Manager or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\n2. It is the responsibility of personnel involved in the configuration of Network Switches at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-005A Procedure to Install and Configure a Network Switch.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'The purpose of this procedure is to provide the standards and instructions to execute a correct and complete installation and functional verification of switches within the Amneal Ireland network.','This procedure applies to all people involved in the installation of network switches running IOS operating system within the Amneal Ireland network.','1. Software Management: Verify correct IOS version for new switches.\n2. Generic commands for all switches: Default configuration, enable services, naming convention, management address, default gateway, console and VTY settings, MOTD banner, UDLD, logging, DNS, HTTP management, SNMP settings, NTP, VTP, VLAN configuration.\n3. Switch specific commands: Access switch, server switch, distribution switch, collapsed core/distribution switch, core switch.\n4. Example configuration: Basic switch configuration example.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nDNS: Domain Naming System.\nHTTP: HyperText Transfer Protocol.\nHSRP: Hot Standby Routing Protocol.\nMOTD: Message Of The Day.\nNTP: Network Time Protocol.\nSNMP: Simple Network Management Protocol.\nUDLD: Unidirectional Link Detection.\nVLAN: Virtual Local Area Network.\nVTP: VLAN Trucking Protocol.\nIOS: Cisco’s Internetwork Operating System.','1. The Information Technology (IT) Manager or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\n2. It is the responsibility of personnel involved in the configuration of Network Switches at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-005 | 26-Feb-2019 | -- | First Issued.\nIT-005A | 01-Feb-2022 | -- | Updated procedure for new installations and configurations.','IT-005',NULL),(96,'IT-006B','PROCEDURE TO INSTALL AND CONFIGURE A WINDOWS SERVER','To provide instruction and guidance for the installation and configuration of a Windows Server at Amneal Ireland.\n---\nThe Windows Servers in operation at Amneal Ireland\n---\n1. VMware Setup\n2. Virtual Machines (VM) Setup\n3. Windows Operating System (O.S) Setup\n4. Add to Domain\n5. Anti-Virus Setup\n6. SQL Installation\n7. Installing and Configuring a Windows Server on VxRail Infrastructure\n---\nIT-006 | 26-Feb-2019 | -- | First Issued\nIT-006A | 21-Feb-2022 | AI-CC-18-140 | SOP updated to new Amneal Logo\nIT-006B | CC-ACM-2000 | CC-AMN-22-4156 | 1. Added “VM: Virtual Machine” to section 4.0 Definitions 2. Updated Section 5.5 Anti-Virus Setup for Crowdstrike on VMs. 3. Added Section 5.7 Installing and Configuring a Windows Server for new VxRail Infrastructure\n---\nThe Information Technology (IT) HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the building of Windows Servers at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-006B Procedure To Install And Configure A windows Server.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'To provide instruction and guidance for the installation and configuration of a Windows Server at Amneal Ireland.','The Windows Servers in operation at Amneal Ireland','1. VMware Setup\n2. Virtual Machines (VM) Setup\n3. Windows Operating System (O.S) Setup\n4. Add to Domain\n5. Anti-Virus Setup\n6. SQL Installation\n7. Installing and Configuring a Windows Server on VxRail Infrastructure','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nISO: Short for ISO9660, the name of the standard specification for CDs\nUSB: Universal Serial Bus. Port available on computers.\nCD/DVD: Compact Disk/Digital Versatile Disc.\nVM: Virtual Machine','The Information Technology (IT) HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the building of Windows Servers at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-006 | 26-Feb-2019 | -- | First Issued\nIT-006A | 21-Feb-2022 | AI-CC-18-140 | SOP updated to new Amneal Logo\nIT-006B | CC-ACM-2000 | CC-AMN-22-4156 | 1. Added “VM: Virtual Machine” to section 4.0 Definitions 2. Updated Section 5.5 Anti-Virus Setup for Crowdstrike on VMs. 3. Added Section 5.7 Installing and Configuring a Windows Server for new VxRail Infrastructure','IT-006A','21CFR Part 11: Electronic Record and Electronic Signature Rule'),(97,'IT-007C','PROCEDURE TO INSTALL BMS APPLICATION SOFTWARE','To provide instruction and guidance for the installation of BMS Application Software at Amneal Ireland.\n---\nThe BMS System in operation at Amneal Ireland.\n---\n1. Tridium Niagara Supervisor Application Installation\n---\nIT-007 | 26-Feb-2019 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-007A | 21-Feb-2022 | AI-CC-18-140 | SOP updated to new Amneal Logo\nIT-007B | 07-Mar-2022 | CC-AMN-22-1017 | Updated questionnaire onto correct template FM-QM-011.\nIT-007C | √5 ~ √k ~ 2√2 l | CC-AMN-24-3188 | 2.1 Replace ‘Windows Server’ with ‘System’ 3.2 Replace ‘Windows Server’ with ‘System’ 5.1 Replaced ‘Tridium AX’ with ‘Tridium Niagara’. 5.1.1 Added Niagara to Tridium Niagara. General editorial changes.\n---\nThe Information Technology (IT) HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the building of BMS System at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-007C Procedure to Install BMS Application Software.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'To provide instruction and guidance for the installation of BMS Application Software at Amneal Ireland.','The BMS System in operation at Amneal Ireland.','1. Tridium Niagara Supervisor Application Installation','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland\nHOD: Head of Department','The Information Technology (IT) HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the building of BMS System at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-007 | 26-Feb-2019 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-007A | 21-Feb-2022 | AI-CC-18-140 | SOP updated to new Amneal Logo\nIT-007B | 07-Mar-2022 | CC-AMN-22-1017 | Updated questionnaire onto correct template FM-QM-011.\nIT-007C | √5 ~ √k ~ 2√2 l | CC-AMN-24-3188 | 2.1 Replace ‘Windows Server’ with ‘System’ 3.2 Replace ‘Windows Server’ with ‘System’ 5.1 Replaced ‘Tridium AX’ with ‘Tridium Niagara’. 5.1.1 Added Niagara to Tridium Niagara. General editorial changes.','IT-007B','21CFR Part 11: Electronic Record and Electronic Signature Rule'),(98,'IT-008A','PROCEDURE TO INSTALL QEMS APPLICATION SOFTWARE','To provide instruction and guidance for the installation of QEMS Application Software at Amneal Ireland.\n---\nThe QEMS Windows Server in operation at Amneal Ireland.\n---\n1. Trend Application Installation\n---\nIT-008 | 26-Feb-2019 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-008A | ∂1-ℓ̲2 - ∂̲3 | AI-CC-18-140 | SOP updated to new Amneal Logo\n---\nThe Information Technology (IT) Manager or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the building of BMS Windows Server at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-008A Procedure To Install QEMS Application Software.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'To provide instruction and guidance for the installation of QEMS Application Software at Amneal Ireland.','The QEMS Windows Server in operation at Amneal Ireland.','1. Trend Application Installation','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','The Information Technology (IT) Manager or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the building of BMS Windows Server at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-008 | 26-Feb-2019 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-008A | ∂1-ℓ̲2 - ∂̲3 | AI-CC-18-140 | SOP updated to new Amneal Logo',NULL,'21CFR Part 11: Electronic Record and Electronic Signature Rule'),(99,'IT-009D','PREVENTIVE MAINTENANCE FOR IT SYSTEMS','This procedure will outline the process for the maintenance activities that are required for IT systems at Amneal Ireland.\n---\nIn Scope:\n1. Routine maintenance activities that are required to ensure that the IT system applications are running as expected.\n2. Quarterly checks on the IT systems to ensure optimum performance, backup and restore of servers.\n3. Hardware associated with backup and restore (tape drives & NAS boxes).\nOut of Scope:\n1. Maintenance of peripheral hardware such as label printers, scanners, client PCs etc.\n2. Maintenance of stand-alone laboratory and production hardware.\n---\n1. General IT System Requirements\n2. Quarterly Maintenance Activities\n3. Review of Application Event Logs\n4. Backup Script Checks\n5. Security Log Reviews\n6. Access Control List Reviews\n7. Database Counters Review\n8. Database and OS Defragmentation\n9. Backup and Restore Testing\n10. Server Reboot and Service Restart\n---\nIT-009 | 20-Oct-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-009A | 16-Mar-2017 | AI-CC-17-010 | Sections 2.1.2, 5.2, 5.1.2, 5.1.3, 5.1.4 and 5.1.7 change the word “periodic” to the word “Quarterly”.\nIT009B | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | 1. Additional Row added to table in Section 2.1.3 with description: Maximo – Maintenance Schedule System.\n2. Editorial changes in section 6 – References.\nIT009C | 06-May-2021 | AI-CC-18-140 | AI-CC-21-032 | Annual Logo change\n2.1.3 Added RF-Smart and SCADA\n3.1 Replaced (IT) Manager with HOD\n5.1.2 Replace Appendix I with Form\n5.2.2 Add ‘completed successfully’\n5.2.3 Added details on Event Viewer, SIEM and Falcon Crowdstrike.\n5.2.6 Added details on Defragment and Optimize Drives.\n5.2.7 Added ‘SOP’\n6.1 Replaced Appendix I with FM-IT-004\nIT009D | 06-Aug-2021 | AIM-CC-21-019 | 2.1.3 Table 1: Added MDI Packaging Line\n4.9 Added MDI: Metered-Dose Inhaler.\n---\nThe Information Technology HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the preventive maintenance activities at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-009D Preventative Maintenance for IT Systems.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'This procedure will outline the process for the maintenance activities that are required for IT systems at Amneal Ireland.','In Scope:\n1. Routine maintenance activities that are required to ensure that the IT system applications are running as expected.\n2. Quarterly checks on the IT systems to ensure optimum performance, backup and restore of servers.\n3. Hardware associated with backup and restore (tape drives & NAS boxes).\nOut of Scope:\n1. Maintenance of peripheral hardware such as label printers, scanners, client PCs etc.\n2. Maintenance of stand-alone laboratory and production hardware.','1. General IT System Requirements\n2. Quarterly Maintenance Activities\n3. Review of Application Event Logs\n4. Backup Script Checks\n5. Security Log Reviews\n6. Access Control List Reviews\n7. Database Counters Review\n8. Database and OS Defragmentation\n9. Backup and Restore Testing\n10. Server Reboot and Service Restart','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland\nBusiness Owner: An individual who owns the relationship between the system, business process and data, ensures the system is maintained in a compliant state including providing adequate resources, and explains the system and business processes to auditors.\nDomain: Collection of workstations or user accounts in a Windows Server environment.\nDNS: Domain Name System\nDHCP: Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol.\nIT Application Owner: An individual responsible for managing the development / implementation, and/or operation of the system from a technical perspective and supervising the system upgrade. The individual who can answer questions relating to technical or business needs of the system. Provides input for the requirements and the communication planning.\nNAS: Network Attached Storage devices used to backup server data.\nSIEM: Security Information and Event Management.\nMDI: Metered-Dose Inhaler.','The Information Technology HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the preventive maintenance activities at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-009 | 20-Oct-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-009A | 16-Mar-2017 | AI-CC-17-010 | Sections 2.1.2, 5.2, 5.1.2, 5.1.3, 5.1.4 and 5.1.7 change the word “periodic” to the word “Quarterly”.\nIT009B | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | 1. Additional Row added to table in Section 2.1.3 with description: Maximo – Maintenance Schedule System.\n2. Editorial changes in section 6 – References.\nIT009C | 06-May-2021 | AI-CC-18-140 | AI-CC-21-032 | Annual Logo change\n2.1.3 Added RF-Smart and SCADA\n3.1 Replaced (IT) Manager with HOD\n5.1.2 Replace Appendix I with Form\n5.2.2 Add ‘completed successfully’\n5.2.3 Added details on Event Viewer, SIEM and Falcon Crowdstrike.\n5.2.6 Added details on Defragment and Optimize Drives.\n5.2.7 Added ‘SOP’\n6.1 Replaced Appendix I with FM-IT-004\nIT009D | 06-Aug-2021 | AIM-CC-21-019 | 2.1.3 Table 1: Added MDI Packaging Line\n4.9 Added MDI: Metered-Dose Inhaler.','IT-009C','FM-IT-004: IT Preventive Maintenance Recording Form\nIT-004: Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System\nQM-004: Good Documentation Practice'),(100,'IT-010C','PERFORMANCE MONITORING FOR IT SYSTEMS','This procedure will outline the process for the performance monitoring activities that are required for IT systems at Amneal Ireland.\n---\nIn-Scope:\n1. Performance monitoring activities that are required to ensure that the IT system applications continue to perform as expected.\n2. Monitoring of IT systems to ensure optimum performance of servers.\n3. Monitoring of IT systems to ensure optimum performance of backup process.\n4. Monitoring of IT systems to ensure optimum performance of databases.\nOut of Scope:\n1. Performance monitoring of peripheral hardware such as label printers, scanners, client PCs etc.\n2. Performance monitoring of stand-alone laboratory and production hardware.\n---\n1. General IT System Requirements\n2. Solarwinds Network Performance Monitor Configuration\n3. Network Switch and Server Alerts\n4. Node and Volume Thresholds\n5. Administrator Accounts and Email Recipients Configuration\n6. Incident Logging and Impact Assessment\n7. Performance Monitor Usage in Case of Solarwinds Failure\n---\nIT-010 | 20-Oct-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-010A | 16-Mar-2017 | AI-CC-17-010 | 1. Sections 2.1.2, 2.1.3, 2.1.4, 5.2.2, 5.2.1, 5.3 and 5.4 from “periodic or “periodically” to “Quarterly”. 2. Section 2.1.5 Amended Table 1 to add the following systems with descriptions; Empower -QC Lab Data Acquisition System Instrument – QC Lab File Storage\nIT-010B | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | 1. Section 2.1.5 Amended Table 1 to add the following with Description; Maximo – Maintenance Schedule System 2. 6.0 References - Editorial changes 3. Section 5.3.1 Replaced instruction to record processor value with “The value that the processor is pegged at should be much less that 100%.” 4. Section 5.3.1 Added “A screen shot of the “Perform” monitor window shall be taken to verify counters are running as expected.” Removed definition for C.S.V. (Computer System Validation).\nIT-010C | 04-May-2021 | AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-21-032 | Annual Logo Change 2.1.1 Replaced ‘Quarter checks’ with ‘Monitoring’ 2.1.5 Added RF-Smart Labelling 3.1 Replace (IT) Manager with HOD\n---\nThe Information Technology HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the performance monitoring activities at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-010C Performance Monitoring for IT Systems.pdf',3,2,'2025-11-17 22:05:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,9,NULL,1,NULL,'This procedure will outline the process for the performance monitoring activities that are required for IT systems at Amneal Ireland.','In-Scope:\n1. Performance monitoring activities that are required to ensure that the IT system applications continue to perform as expected.\n2. Monitoring of IT systems to ensure optimum performance of servers.\n3. Monitoring of IT systems to ensure optimum performance of backup process.\n4. Monitoring of IT systems to ensure optimum performance of databases.\nOut of Scope:\n1. Performance monitoring of peripheral hardware such as label printers, scanners, client PCs etc.\n2. Performance monitoring of stand-alone laboratory and production hardware.','1. General IT System Requirements\n2. Solarwinds Network Performance Monitor Configuration\n3. Network Switch and Server Alerts\n4. Node and Volume Thresholds\n5. Administrator Accounts and Email Recipients Configuration\n6. Incident Logging and Impact Assessment\n7. Performance Monitor Usage in Case of Solarwinds Failure','Business Owner: An individual who owns the relationship between the system, business process and data, ensures the system is maintained in a compliant state including providing adequate resources, and explains the system and business processes to auditors.\nIT Application Owner: An individual responsible for managing the development / implementation, and/or operation of the system from a technical perspective and supervising the system upgrade. The individual who can answer questions relating to technical or business needs of the system. Provides input for the requirements and the communication planning.\nDomain: Collection of workstations or user accounts in a Windows Server environment.\nDNS: Domain Name System.\nCPU: Central Processing Unit.\nGDP: Good Documentation Practices.\nDHCP: Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol.\nSQL: Sequential Query Language.\nPerformance Monitor: Perform application run from Windows Run command field.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','The Information Technology HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the performance monitoring activities at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-010 | 20-Oct-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-010A | 16-Mar-2017 | AI-CC-17-010 | 1. Sections 2.1.2, 2.1.3, 2.1.4, 5.2.2, 5.2.1, 5.3 and 5.4 from “periodic or “periodically” to “Quarterly”. 2. Section 2.1.5 Amended Table 1 to add the following systems with descriptions; Empower -QC Lab Data Acquisition System Instrument – QC Lab File Storage\nIT-010B | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | 1. Section 2.1.5 Amended Table 1 to add the following with Description; Maximo – Maintenance Schedule System 2. 6.0 References - Editorial changes 3. Section 5.3.1 Replaced instruction to record processor value with “The value that the processor is pegged at should be much less that 100%.” 4. Section 5.3.1 Added “A screen shot of the “Perform” monitor window shall be taken to verify counters are running as expected.” Removed definition for C.S.V. (Computer System Validation).\nIT-010C | 04-May-2021 | AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-21-032 | Annual Logo Change 2.1.1 Replaced ‘Quarter checks’ with ‘Monitoring’ 2.1.5 Added RF-Smart Labelling 3.1 Replace (IT) Manager with HOD','IT-010B','IT-004: Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System\nQM-004: Good Documentation Practices\nIT-011: Computer System Incident Management'),(192,'AAA-AAA','aaaa','aaaa','',1,8,'2025-11-28 14:30:15','2025-12-03',NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,1,10,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
