 Report: serious AEs immediately, non-serious per protocol. Regulatory: SUSARs to authorities within timelines.','2025-11-24 21:08:38','2025-12-08 18:11:14',NULL,NULL,356,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(318,'step',NULL,'Active','Adverse Event Collection','Collection of adverse event information from investigational sites including AE forms, medical records, and follow-up information.',NULL,NULL,'Collect: AE reports from sites, medical records, follow-up information, laboratory results. Document: AE forms, narrative, severity, relationship, outcome. Ensure: completeness, accuracy, timeliness.','2025-11-24 21:08:38','2025-11-24 21:08:38',NULL,NULL,317,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(319,'step',NULL,'Active','AE Assessment and Coding','Assessment and coding of adverse events including MedDRA coding, severity assessment, and relationship assessment.',NULL,NULL,'Assess: severity (mild, moderate, severe), relationship (related, not related, unknown), outcome (recovered, recovering, not recovered, fatal). Code: using MedDRA, verify coding accuracy.','2025-11-24 21:08:38','2025-11-24 21:08:38',NULL,NULL,317,NULL,NULL,NULL,2),(320,'step',NULL,'Active','Serious Adverse Event Processing','Processing of serious adverse events including immediate notification, investigation, and regulatory reporting.',NULL,NULL,'Process: serious AEs immediately, notify safety team, investigate, assess causality, prepare reports. Report: SUSARs to authorities (FDA: 7/15 day reports, EMA: 7 day reports).','2025-11-24 21:08:38','2025-11-24 21:08:38',NULL,NULL,317,NULL,NULL,NULL,3),(321,'step',NULL,'Active','Safety Database and Reporting','Maintenance of safety database and generation of safety reports including listings, summaries, and DSUR/IND safety reports.',NULL,NULL,'Maintain: safety database, update with new AEs, generate listings, prepare summaries. Report: DSUR (Development Safety Update Report) annually, IND safety reports per requirements.','2025-11-24 21:08:38','2025-11-24 21:08:38',NULL,NULL,317,NULL,NULL,NULL,4),(322,'process',NULL,'Active','Patient Follow-Up and Post-Treatment Monitoring','Comprehensive patient follow-up system for monitoring after-effects, long-term safety, efficacy outcomes, and quality of life following treatment completion or discontinuation. Includes scheduled follow-up visits, unscheduled visits, long-term monitoring, and post-marketing surveillance.',NULL,NULL,'Critical for: long-term safety assessment, efficacy durability, quality of life evaluation, post-treatment adverse events, survival outcomes, disease progression. Follow-up periods: typically 30 days, 90 days, 6 months, 1 year, and annually thereafter per protocol.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-12-08 18:11:14',NULL,NULL,356,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(323,'step',NULL,'Active','Scheduled Follow-Up Visits','Conducting scheduled follow-up visits per protocol schedule to assess patient status, treatment effects, adverse events, and outcomes.',NULL,NULL,'Schedule: per protocol (typically 30 days, 90 days, 6 months, 1 year post-treatment). Assess: vital signs, physical examination, laboratory tests, adverse events, efficacy endpoints, quality of life. Document: visit date, findings, assessments, next visit date.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,322,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(324,'step',NULL,'Active','Unscheduled Follow-Up and Adverse Event Monitoring','Management of unscheduled patient visits and continuous monitoring for adverse events, treatment-related effects, and safety concerns.',NULL,NULL,'Trigger: patient-initiated visits, adverse events, safety concerns, protocol deviations. Assess: reason for visit, adverse events, treatment effects, safety. Document: visit reason, findings, actions taken, follow-up required.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,322,NULL,NULL,NULL,2),(325,'step',NULL,'Active','Long-Term Safety and Efficacy Monitoring','Long-term monitoring of patient safety, efficacy outcomes, and treatment durability beyond initial follow-up period.',NULL,NULL,'Period: typically 1-5 years post-treatment. Monitor: long-term adverse events, efficacy durability, disease progression, survival outcomes, quality of life. Document: annual assessments, safety updates, efficacy data, survival status.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,322,NULL,NULL,NULL,3),(326,'step',NULL,'Active','Post-Treatment Laboratory and Diagnostic Testing','Laboratory testing and diagnostic procedures during follow-up to assess treatment effects, safety parameters, and disease status.',NULL,NULL,'Tests: hematology, chemistry, liver function, renal function, biomarkers, imaging studies (if applicable). Schedule: per protocol, typically at each follow-up visit. Document: test results, abnormalities, clinical significance, actions taken.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,322,NULL,NULL,NULL,4),(327,'step',NULL,'Active','Quality of Life and Patient-Reported Outcomes','Assessment of patient quality of life, functional status, and patient-reported outcomes during follow-up period.',NULL,NULL,'Assess: quality of life questionnaires (EQ-5D, SF-36, disease-specific), functional status, symptom burden, treatment satisfaction. Schedule: per protocol, typically at key timepoints. Document: questionnaire responses, scores, changes from baseline, clinical significance.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,322,NULL,NULL,NULL,5),(328,'step',NULL,'Active','Post-Marketing Surveillance and Long-Term Registry','Post-marketing surveillance and long-term patient registry for continued safety and efficacy monitoring after product approval.',NULL,NULL,'Period: ongoing post-approval. Monitor: real-world safety, efficacy, patient outcomes, rare adverse events. Methods: registries, post-marketing studies, spontaneous reporting. Document: registry data, safety signals, efficacy outcomes, regulatory reports.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,322,NULL,NULL,NULL,6),(329,'substep',NULL,'Active','Follow-Up Visit Scheduling and Reminders','Scheduling of follow-up visits per protocol and sending reminders to patients to ensure compliance.',NULL,NULL,'Schedule: per protocol timeline (30 days, 90 days, 6 months, 1 year). Send: appointment reminders (phone, email, letter), confirm attendance. Document: scheduled date, reminder sent, patient confirmation.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,323,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(330,'substep',NULL,'Active','Vital Signs and Physical Examination','Assessment of vital signs and comprehensive physical examination during follow-up visit.',NULL,NULL,'Measure: blood pressure, heart rate, respiratory rate, temperature, weight, height. Examine: general appearance, systems review, treatment site (if applicable), adverse event signs. Document: all measurements, examination findings, abnormalities.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,323,NULL,NULL,NULL,2),(331,'substep',NULL,'Active','Adverse Event Assessment and Documentation','Systematic assessment and documentation of adverse events during follow-up visit.',NULL,NULL,'Assess: new adverse events, ongoing adverse events, resolved adverse events, severity, relationship to treatment, outcome. Document: AE forms, narrative, severity, relationship, outcome, actions taken. Update: safety database.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,323,NULL,NULL,NULL,3),(332,'substep',NULL,'Active','Efficacy Endpoint Assessment','Assessment of primary and secondary efficacy endpoints during follow-up visit.',NULL,NULL,'Assess: primary endpoints (per protocol), secondary endpoints, disease status, treatment response, progression. Document: endpoint measurements, changes from baseline, clinical significance, treatment response.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,323,NULL,NULL,NULL,4),(333,'substep',NULL,'Active','Concomitant Medications and Treatments Review','Review of concomitant medications and treatments since last visit.',NULL,NULL,'Review: all medications, treatments, procedures, hospitalizations. Assess: interactions, impact on study treatment, protocol compliance. Document: medication list, changes, compliance, interactions.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,323,NULL,NULL,NULL,5),(334,'substep',NULL,'Active','Follow-Up Visit Documentation and Next Visit Planning','Complete documentation of follow-up visit and planning of next scheduled visit.',NULL,NULL,'Document: visit date, all assessments, findings, adverse events, efficacy data, laboratory results. Plan: next visit date, required tests, follow-up actions. Update: case report forms, safety database, efficacy database.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,323,NULL,NULL,NULL,6),(335,'substep',NULL,'Active','Unscheduled Visit Request and Triage','Receipt and triage of unscheduled visit requests from patients or investigators.',NULL,NULL,'Receive: patient calls, investigator reports, safety concerns. Triage: urgency, severity, need for immediate assessment. Schedule: urgent visits immediately, routine visits within protocol timeframe. Document: request reason, triage decision, scheduled date.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,324,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(336,'substep',NULL,'Active','Adverse Event Investigation and Assessment','Comprehensive investigation and assessment of adverse events reported during unscheduled visit.',NULL,NULL,'Investigate: event details, onset, severity, relationship to treatment, actions taken, outcome. Assess: seriousness, causality, need for regulatory reporting. Document: detailed AE report, investigation findings, causality assessment, regulatory reporting (if required).','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,324,NULL,NULL,NULL,2),(337,'substep',NULL,'Active','Safety Concern Evaluation','Evaluation of safety concerns and determination of appropriate actions.',NULL,NULL,'Evaluate: safety concern nature, severity, impact on patient, impact on study. Determine: actions required (treatment modification, discontinuation, additional monitoring). Document: safety concern, evaluation, actions taken, follow-up required.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,324,NULL,NULL,NULL,3),(338,'substep',NULL,'Active','Treatment Modification or Discontinuation Management','Management of treatment modifications or discontinuations due to adverse events or safety concerns.',NULL,NULL,'Manage: treatment dose reduction, treatment interruption, treatment discontinuation. Document: reason for modification, date, patient status, follow-up required. Update: treatment records, safety database, protocol deviation log.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,324,NULL,NULL,NULL,4),(339,'substep',NULL,'Active','Annual Safety and Efficacy Assessments','Annual comprehensive assessments of patient safety and efficacy outcomes.',NULL,NULL,'Assess: adverse events (new, ongoing, resolved), efficacy outcomes, disease status, survival, quality of life. Schedule: annually post-treatment completion. Document: annual assessment report, safety summary, efficacy summary, survival status.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,325,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(340,'substep',NULL,'Active','Long-Term Adverse Event Tracking','Tracking of long-term adverse events including delayed onset events and late effects.',NULL,NULL,'Track: delayed onset adverse events, late effects, chronic adverse events, rare events. Monitor: patterns, trends, risk factors. Document: long-term AE database, trends analysis, risk assessment, regulatory updates.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,325,NULL,NULL,NULL,2),(341,'substep',NULL,'Active','Survival and Disease Progression Monitoring','Monitoring of patient survival and disease progression outcomes.',NULL,NULL,'Monitor: overall survival, progression-free survival, disease-free survival, time to progression, time to recurrence. Document: survival data, progression events, dates, causes. Analyze: survival curves, progression rates, prognostic factors.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,325,NULL,NULL,NULL,3),(342,'substep',NULL,'Active','Efficacy Durability Assessment','Assessment of treatment efficacy durability and long-term treatment response.',NULL,NULL,'Assess: treatment response duration, maintenance of response, loss of response, need for retreatment. Document: efficacy durability data, response duration, factors affecting durability, retreatment needs.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,325,NULL,NULL,NULL,4),(343,'substep',NULL,'Active','Hematology and Chemistry Testing','Routine hematology and chemistry laboratory testing during follow-up.',NULL,NULL,'Tests: complete blood count (CBC), comprehensive metabolic panel, liver function tests, renal function tests. Schedule: per protocol, typically at each follow-up visit. Document: test results, reference ranges, abnormalities, clinical significance.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,326,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(344,'substep',NULL,'Active','Biomarker and Specialized Testing','Biomarker and specialized laboratory testing for efficacy and safety monitoring.',NULL,NULL,'Tests: disease-specific biomarkers, pharmacodynamic markers, safety biomarkers, genetic testing (if applicable). Schedule: per protocol, at key timepoints. Document: biomarker results, changes from baseline, clinical significance, correlation with outcomes.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,326,NULL,NULL,NULL,2),(345,'substep',NULL,'Active','Imaging Studies and Diagnostic Procedures','Imaging studies and diagnostic procedures for disease assessment and safety monitoring.',NULL,NULL,'Studies: CT, MRI, X-ray, ultrasound, PET scan (as per protocol). Schedule: per protocol, typically at key efficacy timepoints. Document: imaging reports, findings, changes from baseline, clinical significance, radiologist interpretation.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,326,NULL,NULL,NULL,3),(346,'substep',NULL,'Active','Laboratory Result Review and Action','Review of laboratory results and determination of appropriate actions.',NULL,NULL,'Review: all test results, compare to baseline, identify abnormalities, assess clinical significance. Determine: actions required (monitoring, treatment modification, additional testing). Document: result review, clinical interpretation, actions taken, follow-up required.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,326,NULL,NULL,NULL,4),(347,'substep',NULL,'Active','Quality of Life Questionnaire Administration','Administration of quality of life and patient-reported outcome questionnaires.',NULL,NULL,'Questionnaires: generic (EQ-5D, SF-36), disease-specific, symptom-specific. Schedule: per protocol, typically at baseline, key timepoints, and follow-up visits. Administer: in person, by phone, electronically. Document: questionnaire completion, scores, completion date.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,327,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(348,'substep',NULL,'Active','Functional Status and Symptom Assessment','Assessment of patient functional status and symptom burden.',NULL,NULL,'Assess: activities of daily living, functional capacity, symptom severity, symptom frequency, symptom impact. Methods: questionnaires, interviews, physical assessment. Document: functional status, symptom scores, changes from baseline, clinical significance.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,327,NULL,NULL,NULL,2),(349,'substep',NULL,'Active','Treatment Satisfaction and Patient Experience','Assessment of patient satisfaction with treatment and overall treatment experience.',NULL,NULL,'Assess: treatment satisfaction, ease of use, convenience, side effects acceptability, overall experience. Methods: questionnaires, interviews. Document: satisfaction scores, patient feedback, experience narratives, areas for improvement.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,327,NULL,NULL,NULL,3),(350,'substep',NULL,'Active','Quality of Life Data Analysis and Reporting','Analysis and reporting of quality of life and patient-reported outcome data.',NULL,NULL,'Analyze: QOL scores, changes from baseline, treatment group comparisons, factors affecting QOL. Report: QOL summaries, statistical analyses, clinical significance, publication (if applicable). Document: analysis results, reports, publications.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,327,NULL,NULL,NULL,4),(351,'substep',NULL,'Active','Patient Registry Enrollment and Data Collection','Enrollment of patients in post-marketing registry and collection of long-term data.',NULL,NULL,'Enroll: patients post-approval, obtain informed consent, collect baseline data. Collect: demographics, treatment data, outcomes, adverse events, quality of life. Maintain: registry database, data quality, patient follow-up. Document: enrollment, data collection, database updates.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,328,NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(352,'substep',NULL,'Active','Spontaneous Adverse Event Reporting','Collection and processing of spontaneous adverse event reports from healthcare providers and patients.',NULL,NULL,'Collect: spontaneous reports from healthcare providers, patients, regulatory authorities. Process: triage, assessment, causality, seriousness, regulatory reporting. Document: spontaneous reports, assessment, regulatory submissions, follow-up actions.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,328,NULL,NULL,NULL,2),(353,'substep',NULL,'Active','Real-World Evidence Generation','Generation of real-world evidence on product safety and efficacy from post-marketing data.',NULL,NULL,'Generate: real-world safety data, real-world efficacy data, comparative effectiveness, patient outcomes. Methods: registry studies, observational studies, database analyses. Document: study protocols, results, publications, regulatory submissions.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,328,NULL,NULL,NULL,3),(354,'substep',NULL,'Active','Post-Marketing Safety Signal Detection','Detection and evaluation of safety signals from post-marketing data.',NULL,NULL,'Detect: safety signals from spontaneous reports, registries, literature, regulatory databases. Evaluate: signal strength, clinical significance, need for action. Document: signal detection reports, evaluation, risk assessment, regulatory communications.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,328,NULL,NULL,NULL,4),(355,'substep',NULL,'Active','Regulatory Reporting and Communication','Regulatory reporting of post-marketing safety and efficacy data.',NULL,NULL,'Report: PSUR (Periodic Safety Update Report), PADER (Periodic Adverse Drug Experience Report), safety updates, efficacy updates. Schedule: per regulatory requirements (annually, quarterly, as needed). Document: regulatory reports, submissions, communications, responses.','2025-11-24 21:21:40','2025-11-24 21:21:40',NULL,NULL,328,NULL,NULL,NULL,5),(356,'process',NULL,'Active','Amneal Ireland','Top-level organizational structure for all underlying R&D, manufacturing, regulatory, and quality processes.',NULL,NULL,'System-generated root node for the entire process structure hierarchy.','2025-12-08 18:11:14','2025-12-08 18:14:16',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0);
