INSERT INTO `sop_data` VALUES (1,'EHS-004E','Environmental, Health & Safety & Energy Audit & Inspection Procedure','EHS-004 Audit Procedure.pdf','Amanda Power EHS','Amanda Power EHS','Mark Smyth, Engineering','John O\'Dwyer, EHS','2021-10-02','2024-07-04','EHS-004D','This procedure verifies compliance with EHS and Energy Policies, Procedures, and Legislation. It determines the effectiveness of the EHS and Energy management systems.','- Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\n- Systems Audit: Detailed examination of processes, conditions, or systems related to ISO14001, ISO45001, and ISO50001.\n- Operational Audit: Detailed examination of SEUs (Significant Energy Users).\n- EHS: Environmental, Health, and Safety.\n- CAPA: Corrective Action Preventative Action.','To verify compliance with Environment, Health, Safety, and Energy Policies, Procedures, and Legislation. To determine the effectiveness of the EHS and Energy management systems.','Covers the elements of the EHS and Energy Management Systems and the requirements of ISO14001:2015, ISO45001:2018, and ISO50001:2018.','- EHS and Facilities: Implementation and maintenance of the EHS and Energy procedure.\n- Internal Audit Team: Carry out system audits.\n- Management Group: Ensure corrective actions are completed on time.','- EHS-004: First Issued.\n- EHS-004A: Editorial changes to include ISO14001:2015 requirements.\n- EHS-004B: Updated to include Energy policy.\n- EHS-004C: Updated to include ISO45001:2018 and ISO50001:2018.\n- EHS-004D: Definitions added for Operational Audit and SME.\n- EHS-004E: Updated to remove reference to Action Management Software.','- FM-EHS-010: Area Inspection Checklist.\n- FM-EHS-011: Internal EHS Audit Report.\n- FM-EHS-012: SEU Energy Operational Audit Checklist.'),(2,'EHS-001A','Permit to Work','EHS-001 Permit to Work Procedure.pdf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2021-07-07',NULL,NULL,'- Defines the permit-to-work system for safe execution of critical tasks.\n- Covers tasks like confined space entry, hot work, working at height, and electrical work.\n- Requires risk assessments, method statements, and approvals before work begins.','- **Permit Approver**: Individual authorized to approve permits.\n- **Permit User**: Competent person supervising the work.\n- **Hot Work**: Work producing sparks, flames, or ignition sources.\n- **Lock Out/Tag Out**: Procedures to isolate energy sources.\n- **Critical Safe Work**: Tasks like confined space entry, hot work, and working at height.','To ensure safe execution of critical tasks through a permit-to-work system, minimizing risks and ensuring compliance with safety standards.','Applies to all critical tasks requiring permits, including confined space entry, hot work, working at height, and electrical work.','- **Permit User**: Completes risk assessments, ensures safe work execution.\n- **Permit Approver**: Reviews and approves permits.\n- **Area Owner**: Coordinates work activities and ensures safety.\n- **EHS Engineer**: Audits the permit-to-work system.','- **Revision 0**: First Issued.\n- **Revision A (07-Jul-2021)**: Updated template, form references, and permit validity to 7 days.','- EHS-001.F01-00: Confined Space Permit to Work.\n- EHS-001.F02-00: Hot Work Permit.\n- EHS-001.F03-00: Working at Heights Permit.\n- EHS-001.F04-00: General Work Permit.\n- EHS-001.F05-00: Line Breaking & Isolation Permit.\n- EHS-001.F06-00: Energised Electrical Work Permit.\n- EHS-001.F07-00: Excavating and Trenching Permit.\n- EHS-001.F08-00: Crane Operations Permit.'),(3,'EHS-011A','Identification & Review of Environment, Health & Safety Legislative and Other Requirements','EHS-011 EHS Legislative.pdf','Rebecca Toomey, EHS','Rebecca Toomey, EHS',NULL,NULL,'2019-04-17',NULL,'EHS-011','- Identifies and reviews relevant Irish and EU legislation.\n- Maintains a legal register for compliance.\n- Ensures compliance with planning permissions, permits, and licenses.\n- Conducts annual reviews of EHS legislative compliance.',NULL,'To identify and review relevant Irish and EU legislation, planning permissions, permits, and licenses to ensure compliance with EHS requirements.','Applies to all EHS legislative and regulatory requirements relevant to Amneal Ireland, including planning permissions, permits, and licenses.','- **EHS Department**: Responsible for maintaining the EHS Legal Register, reviewing changes, and ensuring compliance.\n- **Antaris**: Assists in the annual review of legislative requirements.','- **EHS-011**: First Issued.\n- **EHS-011A (17-Apr-19)**: Changed \"EHS Manager\" to \"EHS Department.\"','- Pegasus Legal Register (WWW.PegasusLegalRegister.com)'),(4,'EHS-012','Chemical Risk Assessment','EHS-012 Chemical Risk Assessment.pdf','Pearse Moroney EHS','Pearse Moroney EHS','Dover EHS','John O\'Sullivan QC','2017-01-01',NULL,'N/A','- Describes the procedure for risk assessment of hazardous chemicals.\n- Communicates chemical risks to employees.\n- Establishes a program for periodic employee exposure monitoring.','- **EHS Specialist**: A trained person knowledgeable about chemical properties and health effects.\n- **Site Leader**: Person responsible for EHS on site.\n- **Hazardous Chemical**: Any chemical that can cause harm.\n- **Exposure**: Contact with chemicals through skin, inhalation, ingestion, or injection.\n- **OELV (Occupational Exposure Limit Value)**: Air concentration limits for safe exposure.','To assess risks associated with hazardous chemicals, communicate these risks to employees, and establish a program for periodic exposure monitoring.','Applies to the use of hazardous chemicals at the Amneal Ireland facility.','- **Site Leader**: Designates a qualified person to coordinate chemical risk assessments and exposure monitoring.\n- **EHS Specialist**: Ensures risk assessments are carried out for existing and new hazardous chemicals.','- **EHS-012**: First Issued.','- EHS-005 Chemical Substance Management.\n- ES-009 Risk Management.\n- FM-EHS-011-00 Chemical Risk Assessment form.\n- Chemical Agent Code of Practice 2016.'),(5,'EHS-013','Use of Amneal Ireland Company Vehicles','EHS-013 Use of Company Vehicles.pdf','John O\'Dwyer, EHS','John O\'Dwyer, EHS','Kieran O\'Brien, Finance; Zita O\'Rourke, HR','John Reardon, Engineering','2020-01-01',NULL,'N/A','- Establishes procedures for the use of Amneal Ireland\'s owned or leased vehicles.\n- Ensures safe operation on public roadways, private property, and Amneal property.\n- Requires drivers to maintain valid licenses and report incidents promptly.','- **Amneal Ireland**: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\n- **EHS**: Environmental, Health, and Safety.\n- **HR**: Human Resources.\n- **Authorised Persons**: Personnel authorised to operate Amneal Ireland owned or leased vehicles.','To establish procedures for the safe use of Amneal Ireland\'s owned or leased vehicles, ensuring compliance with local regulations and safe driving practices.','Applies to the operation of Amneal Ireland owned or leased vehicles on public roadways, private property, and Amneal property. Excludes specialized off-road equipment like forklifts.','- **Authorised Drivers**: Maintain valid licenses, report incidents, and comply with local regulations.\n- **Department Management**: Qualify and authorise employees for vehicle operation.\n- **EHS Department**: Establish safe operation procedures and investigate incidents.\n- **Maintenance Department**: Ensure vehicles are roadworthy.\n- **Finance Department**: Manage vehicle procurement and insurance.\n- **HR Department**: Maintain medical details and a register of authorised drivers.','- **EHS-013**: First Issued.','- EHS-013.F01-00: Use of Amneal Ireland Company Vehicles Authorisation Form.\n- EHS-013.F01-02: Use of Amneal Ireland Company Vehicles Authorised Users Log.\n- EHS-013.F01-03: Use of Amneal Ireland Company Vehicles Log.\n- ES-008: Reporting and Investigation of Accident, Incident, Near Miss, and Dangerous Occurrence.'),(6,'EHS-014','Movement of Hazardous Liquid Waste to External Site Storage','EHS-014 Movement of Hazardous Liquid to External Site Storage.pdf','Melanie Hayden, QC/ARD','Melanie Hayden, QC/ARD','John O\'Dwyer, EHS','John O\'Sullivan, QC/ARD','2020-01-01',NULL,'N/A','- Describes procedures for moving hazardous liquid waste to external storage.\n- Ensures safe handling and transport of hazardous liquids.\n- Requires proper labeling, PPE, and secondary containment.','- **SOP**: Standard Operating Procedure.\n- **QC/ARD**: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development.\n- **PPE**: Personal Protective Equipment.\n- **IPA**: Isopropanol.\n- **API**: Active Pharmaceutical Ingredient.\n- **EHS**: Environment, Health, and Safety.\n- **EHS Specialist**: A trained person knowledgeable about chemical properties and health effects.\n- **Site Leader**: Person responsible for EHS on site.','To establish procedures for the safe movement of hazardous liquid waste from the QC/ARD Laboratory, Production, and Maintenance Departments to external storage areas at Amneal Ireland.','Applies to the movement of hazardous liquid waste within Amneal Ireland, including proper handling, labeling, and transport to external storage.','- **Departmental Personnel**: Follow the procedures outlined in the SOP.\n- **QC/ARD and Warehouse Teams**: Log the movement of liquid waste and maintain records.\n- **EHS Specialist**: Ensure compliance with safety standards.','- **EHS-014**: First Issued.',NULL),(7,'EHS-017A','Energy Objectives and Targets','EHS-017A Energy Objectives and Targets.pdf','Amanda Power, EHS','Amanda Power, EHS','Mark Smyth, Engineering','John O\'Dwyer, EHS','2021-01-01',NULL,'EHS-017','- Establishes methods for setting and monitoring Energy Objectives and Targets.\n- Ensures continual improvement of the Energy Management System (EnMS).\n- Aligns with ISO 50001:2018 requirements.','- **Amneal Ireland**: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\n- **Energy Objective or Target**: A goal set by the company consistent with the Energy Policy and EnMS.\n- **EnMS**: Energy Management System.\n- **SEUs**: Significant Energy Users.\n- **Energy Audits**: Scheduled audits of the Energy Management System.','To specify the method for setting Energy Objectives and Targets and to monitor their effectiveness, ensuring continual improvement of the Energy Management System (EnMS).','Applies to Amneal Ireland personnel involved in setting, reviewing, and achieving Energy Objectives and Targets in line with ISO 50001:2018 requirements.','- **Facilities Department**: Develops and assesses Energy Objectives and Targets in conjunction with Site Management and the Energy Management Team.\n- **Site Management**: Works with the Facilities Engineer to develop Energy Objectives and Targets.','- **EHS-017**: First Issued.\n- **EHS-017A**: SOP and forms transferred to a new template.','- Energy Manual.\n- Energy Policy.'),(8,'EHS-018A','Energy Record Control Policy','EHS-018A Energy Record Control Policy.pdf','Amanda Power, EHS','Amanda Power, EHS','Mark Smyth, Engineering','John O\'Dwyer, EHS','2021-01-01',NULL,'EHS-018','- Describes the approach for controlling and retaining Energy-related documented information.\n- Ensures compliance with ISO 50001:2018 requirements.\n- Energy records must be retained for the lifetime of the site.','- **Amneal Ireland**: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\n- **EHS**: Environmental, Health, and Safety.\n- **EnMS**: Energy Management System.\n- **Energy Records**: Documents or data (manual or electronic) that provide evidence of energy activities and compliance with regulations.\n- **Documented Information**: Information required to be controlled and retained, including processes, operational documentation, and records.','To describe the approach for controlling and retaining Energy-related documented information at the Amneal Ireland Cashel facility, ensuring compliance with ISO 50001:2018.','Applies to the storage and retention of records and documented information related to the ISO 50001:2018 Management Systems at Amneal Ireland.','- **Facilities Department**: Implements and maintains the procedure, controls equipment maintenance, calibration, and safety assessments.\n- **EHS Department**: Assists the Facilities Department in controlling records and documented information.','- **EHS-018**: First Issued.\n- **EHS-018A**: SOP and forms transferred to a new template.','- ISO 50001:2018.\n- QM-009: Document Storage and Retention.\n- QM-013: Change Control System.'),(9,'EHS-019B','Identification & Review of Energy Legislative and Other Requirements','EHS-019B Identification and Review of Energy Legislative and Other Requirements.pdf','John O\'Dwyer, EHS','John O\'Dwyer, EHS',NULL,'William Moore, Engineering',NULL,NULL,'EHS-019A','- Specifies the method for maintaining, updating, and reviewing the Energy Legal Register.\n- Ensures compliance with Energy legislative and other requirements.\n- Uses Red-on-line for legal register updates.','- **Amneal Ireland**: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\n- **Antaris**: The licensee provider of the Red-on-line Legal Register.','To ensure Amneal Ireland is fully familiar with its Energy legislative and other requirements by maintaining, updating, and reviewing the Energy Legal Register.','Applies to all legislative, regulatory, and other policy requirements related to Energy aspects at Amneal Ireland Cashel.','- **EHS Department**: Communicates codes of practice and monitors compliance with Energy legislative obligations.\n- **Facilities Department**: Ensures awareness of current legislation and addresses actions arising from the legal register.','- **EHS-019**: First Issued.\n- **EHS-019A**: SOP and forms transferred to a new template.\n- **EHS-019B**: Updated references to Red-on-line and removed references to Pegasus.','- Red-on-line Legal Register (Red-on-line | EHS Solutions (hse-compliance.net)).'),(10,'EHS-020B','Energy Efficient Procurement','EHS-020B Energy Efficient Procurement.pdf','Amanda Power, EHS','Amanda Power, EHS','Jolly O\'Dover, EHS','Mark Smyth, Engineering',NULL,NULL,'EHS-020A','- Outlines the procedure for energy-efficient procurement of energy and SEU equipment.\n- Ensures procurement aligns with energy efficiency goals and regulatory requirements.\n- Considers whole-life costs and environmental impacts of SEUs.','- **Amneal Ireland**: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\n- **EHS**: Environmental, Health, and Safety.\n- **Energy Procurement**: Procurement of electricity and gas.\n- **EnMS**: Energy Management System.\n- **EMS**: Energy Monitoring System.\n- **SOP**: Standard Operating Procedure.\n- **HVAC**: Heating, Ventilation, Air Conditioning.\n- **SEU**: Significant Energy User.','To outline the procedure for the energy-efficient procurement of both energy and SEU equipment, ensuring alignment with energy efficiency goals and regulatory requirements.','Applies to the procurement of Significant Energy Users (e.g., boilers, chillers, compressors, HVAC units) and energy at Amneal Ireland Limited.','- **Employees**: Investigate energy-efficient options for SEUs.\n- **Facilities Department**: Handle energy procurement, maintain contact with energy efficiency agencies, and ensure SOP compliance.\n- **EHS Department**: Advise on SEU purchases and consider environmental impacts.\n- **Finance Department**: Assist in the SEU procurement process.','- **EHS-020**: First Issued.\n- **EHS-020A**: Updated to remove reference to EHS-015 and include reference to PROC-001.\n- **EHS-020B**: SOP and forms transferred to a new template.','- PROC-001: Procurement to Payment Procedure.'),(11,'EHS-021A','Operation of the Energy Monitoring System (EMS)','EHS-021 Operation of the Energy Monitoring System (EMS).pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Amanda Power, EHS','Ann Clowyer, EHS','Mark Smyth, Engineering','2021-07-01','2024-12-07','EHS-021','The procedure describes the steps required to operate the EMS system, including user access levels, baselines, alarms, and preventative maintenance.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland; EHS: Environmental, Health and Safety; BMS: Building Management System; EnMS: Energy Management System; EMS: Energy Monitoring System; SOP: Standard Operating Procedure; HVAC: Heating, Ventilation, Air Conditioning; SEU: Significant Energy User; Maximo: On-site Computer Maintenance Management System','The purpose of this SOP is to describe the guidelines for the operation of the Energy Monitoring System (EMS).','This SOP will be used by all personnel who are involved in the operation of the EMS system.','Facilities Department: Responsible for the operation and maintenance of the EMS, performing ongoing checks, and ensuring maintenance is completed. EHS Department: Advise on out-of-specification occurrences and assist in considering environmental effects. IT Department: Complete necessary maintenance through the BMS server maintenance plan.','EHS-021: First Issued; SOP and Forms transferred to new Management Software; Removed reference to Action.','N/A'),(13,'EHS-003A','Environmental Aspects and Impacts','EHS-003 Environmental Aspects and Impacts.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Pearse Moroney, EHS','John O\'Dwyer, EHS','John Reardon, Engineering','2021-04-02','2023-04-03','EHS-003','The procedure provides a system to identify environmental aspects and their impacts, assess their significance, and prioritize actions to mitigate impacts.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland; Change Control: A documented account of a change to be made to equipment or process; Environmental Aspect: An element of the Site activities, products, or services that can interact with the environment; Environmental Impact: Any changes to the environment, whether adverse or beneficial, wholly or partially resulting from the Site\'s activities, products, or services; Aspects/Impacts Register: Register which rates the impacts of each aspect on the environment; EHS: Environmental, Health and Safety.','The purpose of this procedure is to provide a system to identify environmental aspects of the Amneal Ireland Cashel facility\'s activities, products, and services and their impact on the environment, to enable the site to consider actions to mitigate these impacts and comply with ISO 14001:2015.','This SOP applies to all current and past activities, products, and services or new developments, or new or modified activities, to identify those which have a significant impact on the environment.','EHS Manager: Ensures the Aspects/Impacts register is reviewed and updated, and significant environmental aspects are prioritized in the annual objectives discussion during management review.','EHS-003: First Issued; EHS-003A: Editorial changes to include ISO 14001:2015 requirements, clarified frequency of occurrence score, removed activity and score from summary list, removed lead from potential negative impacts, clarified which management of change documents are reviewed, added risks and opportunities section.','ISO 14001:2015; QM-013 Change Control System'),(14,'EHS-005','CHEMICAL SUBSTANCE MANAGEMENT','EHS-005 Chemical Substance Management.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Pearse Moroney EHS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Chemical Inventory Database, Safety Data Sheets (SDS), Labelling, Purchase of Chemicals, Chemical Compatibility, Handling and Storage, Contractors',NULL,'To manage chemical substances safely and ensure compliance with regulations.','Applies to all chemical substances used or stored on site.','EHS, PO requestors, Vendors, Contractors, Project Managers','• Removed tables containing internal and external issues and included as Appendices • Removed tables containing interested parties and included as Appendices • Updated Appendices numbers • Added reference to ISO standard clauses to Chapter titles • Updated Reviewers','ES-006 Spill Response Procedure, Chemical Risk Assessment form'),(15,'EHS-006B','ENVIRONMENTAL HEALTH & SAFETY OBJECTIVES','EHS-006B Environmental Health and Safety Objectives and Targets.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Rebecca Toomey, EHS','Amanda Power, EHS','John O\'Dwyer, EHS',NULL,NULL,'EHS-006A','Objectives and Targets shall be established considering operational and business requirements, EHS Policy, compliance obligations, significant environmental aspects, environmental risks and opportunities, Safety Statement, and risk assessments. Each objective shall have an owner, required resources, and effective date. Objectives are reviewed and updated as needed.','Amneal Ireland - Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. EHS Objective - a goal consistent with the site EHS policy and arising from the site environmental review or Occupational Health and Safety performance.','To specify the method by which Environment Health and Safety objectives are set and how their effectiveness is monitored to ensure continual improvement in the EHS management system.','Applies to Amneal Ireland personnel involved in setting, specifying, reviewing, and achieving EHS objectives in line with legislative and significant aspects and the requirements of ISO14001:2015 and ISO45001:2018.','EHS Manager - Develop site EHS Objectives with the Site Director and ensure regular assessment. Site Director - Develop EHS Objectives with the EHS Manager.','EHS-006 - First Issued. EHS-006A (09-Mar-2018) - Editorial changes to include ISO14001:2015 requirements, EHS Specialist replaced by EHS Manager, Targets removed, definition of EHS objective modified, environmental risks and opportunities added, required resources included. EHS-006B (17-Apr-19) - OHSAS18001:2007 changed to ISO45001:2018.','Aspects and Impacts Register, EHS Policy, Amneal Risk assessment folder'),(16,'EHS-007A','ENVIRONMENT, HEALTH & SAFETY COMMUNICATION AND COMPLAINT PROCEDURE','EHS-007A Environmental Health & Safety Communication & Compliant Procedure.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Pearse Moroney, EHS','John O\'Dwyer, EHS','Gerold McDermott, Site Director',NULL,NULL,'EHS-007','Internal communication encourages employee participation in EHS practices, risk assessments, and incident investigations. External complaints are handled through a formal procedure, with forms retained for three years. EHS information is communicated via intranet, noticeboards, and monthly meetings.','Amneal Ireland - Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. EHS - Environmental, Health and Safety.','To describe the procedure for handling EHS-related communications and external complaints.','Applies to all EHS communications and external complaints received at the Amneal Ireland facility.','EHS Department - Maintain the procedure and handle external complaints. Employees and Security - Direct external complaints to the Site Director via EHS. Site Director - Approve responses to external complaints.','EHS-007 - First Issued. EHS-007A (09-Mar-2018) - Editorial changes to include ISO14001:2015 requirements, noted use of intranet for internal EHS communication, and retention of complaint forms for 3 years.','FM-EHS-009-00 External Communication and Complaint form, Emergency Response Plan'),(17,'EHS-008C','ENVIRONMENT, HEALTH & SAFETY & ENERGY MANAGEMENT REVIEW','EHS-008C EHS Management Review.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Amanda Power, EHS','Mark Smyth, Engineering','John C Dover, EHS',NULL,NULL,'EHS-008B','EHS and Energy Management Review meetings are held annually to assess the suitability, adequacy, and effectiveness of the site EHS and Energy program. The review considers action items, compliance obligations, significant environmental aspects, risks, opportunities, and energy performance. Minutes are retained for 3 years.','Amneal Ireland - Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. EHS - Environmental, Health and Safety. Management Review - A forum for discussion and improvement of EHS and Energy performance. EMS - Environmental Management System.','To describe the procedure for the Environment, Health and Safety, and Energy Management Review program at the Amneal Ireland Cashel facility.','Applies to all EHS and Energy Management Review meetings conducted at the Amneal Ireland Cashel facility.','EHS and Facilities - Ensure annual review meetings, provide necessary documentation, and retain meeting minutes for 3 years. Senior Leadership Team - Attend meetings, participate in discussions, and follow up on action items.','EHS-008 - First Issued. EHS-008A (08-Mar-2018) - Editorial changes to include ISO14001:2015 requirements, replaced Specialist with Manager, and added discussion items. EHS-008B (18-Apr-2019) - Added Energy to EHS references, included Facilities Engineer, and added energy-related discussion items. EHS-008C - SOP and forms transferred to a new template, titles reworded.','EHS Policy, Aspects Impacts Register'),(18,'EHS-009B','PREPARATION AND CONTROL OF ENVIRONMENT, HEALTH & SAFETY STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURES','EHS-009B Preperation and Control of EHS SOP\'s.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Rebecca Toomey, EHS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'EHS documents are developed, implemented, and maintained in compliance with ISO 45001:2018 and ISO 14001:2015. Only soft copies are retained, with master documents stored in the \'EHS Integrated procedures\' folder. Obsolete documents are retained by EHS.',NULL,'To outline the procedure for preparing and controlling Environment, Health, and Safety Standard Operating Procedures.','Applies to the development, implementation, and maintenance of EHS documents in compliance with ISO standards.','EHS function - Develop, implement, and maintain documents. Engineering Director or designee - Approve new and revised documents.','EHS-009 - First Issued. EHS-009A (09-Mar-2018) - Editorial changes to include ISO14001:2015 requirements, added definition of SOP, and replaced Engineering Manager with Engineering Director or designee. EHS-009B (17-Apr-19) - Changed OHSAS18001:2007 to ISO45001:2018.','QM-001 Preparation and Control of Standard Operating Procedures'),(19,'EHS-010B','ENVIRONMENT, HEALTH, SAFETY & ENERGY RECORD CONTROL POLICY','EHS-010B EHS Record Retention Policy.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Rebecca Toomey, EHS','Mark Smyth, Engineering','John O’Dwyer, EHS','2021-07-01','2024-01-06','EHS-010A','Documents required by the company and by ISO45001:2018, ISO14001:2015, and ISO50001:2018 Management Standards shall be stored and retained in the EHS Department and Document Control Centre for the retention period defined in Table 1.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nEHS-Environmental, Health and Safety\nErgo-ergonomic\nHealth and safety Records - Any document in which data is held or stored manually or electronically.\nDocumented information – The Environmental Information required to be controlled and retained by Amneal including processes related to the Environmental Management System, operational documentation (including procedures) and records stating results and providing evidence of activities performed.','The purpose of this document is to describe the approach for controlling and retaining Environmental, Health, Safety & Energy documented information at the Amneal Ireland Cashel facility.','Amneal Ireland have established this policy to control on-site storage and retention of records and documented information that relates to the ISO45001:2018, ISO14001:2015 and ISO50001:2018 Management Systems and the requirements therein.','The EHS Department is responsible for the implementation and maintenance of this procedure and control of certain records and documented information.\nThe Engineering Department is responsible for the control of equipment maintenance, calibration and safety assessments in conjunction with relevant departments and control of certain records and documented information.\nThe Human Resources(HR) Department is responsible for the control of all employee Medical and Occupational Health records. Information on competence and job specific training is shared between the HR department and the EHS team.','EHS-010 - First Issued\nEHS-010A - 08-Mar-2018 - Editorial change to include the standard requirements identified in ISO14001:2015\nEHS-010B - 17-Apr-19 - Updated to include ISO50001:2018 throughout. OHSAS18001:2007 replaced with ISO45001:2018.','International Standard ISO45001:2018\nInternational Standard ISO14001:2015\nInternational Standard ISO50001:2018\nQM-009 Document Storage and Retention'),(20,'ES-001J','MATERIAL DESTRUCTION AND WASTE MANAGEMENT PROCEDURE','ES-001J IMaterial Destruction & Waste Management Procedure.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Olivier Gras','Eoghan Walshe, Katherine Russell','Kuddeep Joshi','2024-07-02','2027-07-20','ES-001I','The procedure outlines the management and disposal of hazardous, non-hazardous, biological, and contaminated waste, including material destruction. It includes steps for waste segregation, labeling, and disposal, as well as responsibilities for different departments.','API: Active Pharmaceutical Ingredient, DGSA: Dangerous Goods Safety Advisor, EWC: European Waste Catalogue, IPA: Isopropyl Alcohol, PPE: Personal Protective Equipment, IBC: Intermediate Bulk Containers, SOP: Standard Operating Procedure, WTF: Waste Transfer Form, TSDF: Treatment, Storage & Disposal Facility, Waste: A material, substance or by-product eliminated or discarded as no longer useful, Contaminated Waste: Impure waste by exposure to or addition of a harmful, poisonous or polluting substance, Hazardous Waste: Any waste which by reason of any of its physical, chemical, reactive, toxic, flammable, explosive or corrosive characteristics causes danger or is likely to cause danger to health or environment, Biological Waste: Any material that contains or has been contaminated by a biohazardous agent, Bio Medical Waste: Discarded medicines including damaged or rejected filled containers, PM: Preventative maintenance, EHS: Environmental, Health and Safety, QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development, Halogenated Waste: Organic solvent waste containing halogenic atoms, Non-Halogenated Waste: All other solvents not mentioned in section 4.18, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland, PD Lab: Product Development Laboratory, Ullage: Loss of liquid, by evaporation or leakage.','To describe the procedure for the effective management and disposal of all hazardous, non-hazardous, biological, and contaminated waste and waste packing materials generated by the Amneal Ireland facility in accordance with local regulations and corporate requirements.','This Procedure applies to the management of waste generated at the Amneal Ireland facility.','Each employee is responsible for the correct segregation and in-house disposal of non-hazardous waste streams. Project Managers ensure contractor compliance. Departments manage waste labeling, segregation, and packaging. Manufacturing transfers waste to the airlock. Contract cleaners handle waste movement and decanting. Warehouse personnel collect and store waste. QC/ARD/PD and Microbiology Laboratory personnel manage specific waste types. EHS oversees overall waste management, appoints licensed contractors, and maintains documentation.','ES-001: 26-Apr-2016 - First Issued, ES-001A: 17-Feb-2017 - Updated text, replaced C1 form with WTF, removed DGSA reference, added new points, updated Table 1, ES-001B: 07-Apr-2017 - Added driver\'s name, updated Table 1, ES-001C: 02-Feb-2018 - Added instructions for labeling and waste log, updated Table 1, ES-001D: 29-Mar-2018 - Updated waste transfer form retention, added torque instruction, updated Table 1, ES-001E: 30-Oct-2018 - Added Microbiology Laboratory responsibilities, updated Table 1, ES-001F: 29-Mar-2019 - Updated template, definitions, and responsibilities, updated Table 1, ES-001G: 15-Mar-2022 - Updated logo and template, ES-001H: 22-Jun-2022 - Added PD Lab, updated Table 1, ES-001I: 05-Oct-2023 - Updated decanting instructions, reviewed Table 1, ES-001J: 31-Jul-24 - Updated FM-ES-006.','FM-ES-006: Hazardous waste consignment check list, FM-ES-001: Internal Waste Log, FM-ES-002: Waste Identification label'),(21,'ES-002C','OPERATION, CLEANING AND STORAGE OF POWERED AIR PURIFYING RESPIRATORS','ES-002C Op, Clean & Storage of Powered Air Purifying Respirators.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Olivier Gras','Liam O’Gorman, Matread Ryan','Kuldeep Joshi',NULL,NULL,'ES-002B','The procedure outlines the operation, cleaning, and storage of Powered Air Purifying Respirators (PAPRs) and personal hoods. It includes hazard identification, risk assessment, selection, and proper use of PAPRs, as well as cleaning and storage protocols.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland, Control or Control measures: A process, policy, device, practice or action designed to eliminate or minimize a risk, PAPR’s: Powered Air Purifying Respirators, EN: EN followed by a series of numbers means relevant European Standard, Elimination: The highest level in the hierarchy of controls which involves the removal of a hazard or exposure, Engineering Control: Methods of eliminating or reducing exposure to chemical, physical, or biological agents by installing or modifying equipment, Harm: Damage to human health or the environment, Hazard Assessment: The process of identifying hazards and prescribing controls to reduce risk, Hierarchy of Control: The practice of selecting and applying controls in the hierarchy of elimination, substitution, engineering, administrative, and PPE, Maintenance: Cleaning, inspection, and repair of PPE to ensure it functions to design specification, OEL: Occupational Exposure Limit – Upper limit on the acceptable concentration of a hazardous substance in workplace air, PPE: Personal Protective Equipment - Items worn to protect an individual from risks, Residual Risk: Risk remaining after implementation of risk control measures, Risk Assessment: The process of hazard identification, risk analysis, and risk control, Risk Control Measure: Workplace EHS safeguards using the hierarchy of control, Substitution: Implementation of a less hazardous operation or material, ES: Environmental Health and Safety, MF: Manufacturing, QA: Quality Assurance, IPA: Isopropyl Alcohol, SOP: Standard Operating Procedure, OJT: On the job training.','To establish a procedure for the operation, cleaning, and storage of Powered Air Purifying Respirators (PAPRs) and personal hoods to fulfil the requirements of the Safety Health and Welfare at Work (General Applications) Regulations 2007-2020, Part 2, Chapter 3: Use of Personal Protective Equipment at Work.','This SOP applies to all personnel and areas where Powered Air Purifying Respirators are required. The requirements of this SOP are in conjunction with ES-005 Usage of Personal Protection Equipment.','EHS Department: Develop and maintain a PPE matrix, assist in hazard identification and risk assessment, provide advice on PAPR use, and replace damaged PAPRs. All Employees: Use appropriate PPE, report damage or concerns, and ensure proper operation, calibration, maintenance, cleaning, and storage of PAPRs. Area Managers: Provide resources, ensure training, and ensure proper use and storage of PAPRs.','ES-002: 10-Nov-2017 - First Issued, ES-002A: 23-Nov-2018 - Updated wording and added new sub-sections, ES-002B: 24-Jan-2020 - Updated to new Amneal Logo, ES-002C: 22-Jan-2020 - Updated Safety Health and Welfare at Work Regulations, added OJT reference, updated calibration instructions, and removed Scott PAPR references.','ES-005: Usage of Personal Protective Equipment, FM-ES-005: PPE Matrix, ES-009: Environmental Health and Safety Risk Assessment Procedure, N/A: Safety Health and Welfare at Work (General Applications) Regulations 2007, Part 2, Chapter 3: Use of Personal Protective Equipment at Work, MF-009: Gowning Procedure for Entering and Exiting the Inhalation Areas.'),(22,'ES-003A','USE OF FACE MASKS/SHIELDS IN THE INHALATION FACILITY, WAREHOUSE, QC CHEMISTRY AND QC MICROBIOLOGY LABORATORIES AT AMNEAL IRELAND','ES-003A Use of Face Masks Shields in the Inhalation Facility.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Amanda Power','Liam O’Gorman, Katharina Russell','Kuldeep Joshi',NULL,NULL,'ES-003','The procedure provides instructions for the proper use and disposal of face masks/shields in the Inhalation Facility, Warehouse, QC Chemistry, and QC Microbiology Laboratories. It includes guidelines for donning and removing masks/shields, sanitization, and disposal in line with Irish Government and CDC recommendations.','SOP: Standard Operating Procedure, QC/ARD: Quality Control Analytical Research and Development, EHS: Environmental Health and Safety, Face mask (Medical Mask): Device covering the mouth, nose, and chin, compliant with EN 14683:2014, Face mask, Non-Medical Mask: Covering over the mouth, nose, and chin, not permitted in the Inhalation facility, Face shield: Device to protect eyes and face from bodily fluids or infectious materials, CDC: Center for Disease Control, PPE: Personal Protective Equipment, IPA: Isopropyl Alcohol, FDA: Food and Drug Administration, MF: Manufacturing, QA: Quality Assurance.','To provide instruction for the proper use and disposal of face masks/shields in the Inhalation Facility, Warehouse, QC Chemistry, and QC Microbiology Laboratories at Amneal Ireland in line with Irish Government and CDC recommendations.','The scope of this SOP is the proper use and disposal of face masks/shields in the Inhalation Facility, Warehouse, QC Chemistry, and QC Microbiology Laboratories by Amneal Personnel, Contractors, and Visitors. General office areas and maintenance areas are out of scope.','All personnel wearing face masks/shields must be trained and adhere to this procedure. Personnel hosting visitors must ensure visitors follow the procedure. EHS is responsible for maintaining an overall stock of face masks/shields.','ES-003: 19-Aug-2020 - Initial, ES-003A: 2.2~<e~ 2e>2c - Updated to include existing control measures, clarified requirements in CNC office area (XP-15), and realigned numbering.','ES-001: Material Destruction and Waste Management Procedure, MF-009: Gowning Procedure for Entering and Exiting the Inhalation Areas, MM-003: Garbing Procedure for Warehouse Entry, QC-029: Gowning Procedure for QC/ARD Laboratory Entry, QC-073: Gowning Procedure for the Microbiology Laboratory, FDA Good Manufacturing Practice Considerations for Responding to COVID-19 Infection in Employees in Drug and Biological Products Manufacturing (June 2020).'),(23,'ES-005A','USAGE OF PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT (PPE)','ES-005A Usage of Personal Protective Equipment (PPE).pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,'Zita O\'Rourke, Paul Delaney','Logram Henry',NULL,NULL,'ES-005','The procedure outlines the management of personal protective equipment (PPE) including eye, hand, foot, and body protection. It includes hazard identification, risk assessment, selection, use, maintenance, and storage of PPE in compliance with the Safety Health and Welfare at Work (General Applications) Regulations 2007.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland, Control or Control measures: A process, policy, device, practice or action designed to eliminate or minimize a risk, dBA: A-weighted decibels – Expression of the relative loudness of sounds in air, EN: EN followed by a series of numbers means relevant European Standard, Elimination: The highest level in the hierarchy of controls involving the removal of a hazard, Engineering Control: Methods of reducing exposure to hazards by modifying equipment, Harm: Damage to human health or the environment, Hazard Assessment: The process of identifying hazards and prescribing controls, Hierarchy of Control: The practice of selecting controls in the order of elimination, substitution, engineering, administrative, and PPE, Maintenance: Cleaning, inspection, and repair of PPE, OEL: Occupational Exposure Limit – Upper limit on the acceptable concentration of a hazardous substance, PPE: Personal Protective Equipment - Items worn to protect against risks, Residual Risk: Risk remaining after control measures, RPE: Respiratory Protective Equipment, Risk Analysis: Systematic process to understand and reduce risk, Risk Assessment: The process of hazard identification, risk analysis, and control, Risk Control Measure: Safeguards using the hierarchy of control, Substitution: Implementation of a less hazardous operation or material, TWA: Time-Weighted Average - Daily exposure to a hazardous substance averaged to an 8-hour workday.','To establish a procedure for managing the use of personal protective equipment (PPE) including eye, hand, foot, and body protection, in compliance with the Safety Health and Welfare at Work (General Applications) Regulations 2007.','This SOP applies to all PPE selected, used, and maintained on site and to all areas where PPE is required.','EHS Department: Develop and maintain a PPE matrix, provide technical guidance, assist in hazard identification, and support training. All Employees: Understand hazards, use appropriate PPE, and report damage. Area Managers: Provide resources, ensure training, and ensure proper use and storage of PPE.','ES-005: 22-Dec-2016 - First Issued, ES-005A: C·S-A·U=a·O - SOP and forms transferred to new template.','FM-ES-012: PPE Matrix, ES-009: Environmental Health and Safety Risk Assessment Procedure, N/A: Safety Health and Welfare at Work (General Applications) Regulations 2007, Part 2, Chapter 3: Use of Personal Protective Equipment at Work.'),(24,'ES-006B','SPILL RESPONSE PROCEDURE','ES-006B Spill Response Procedure.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,'Maurice Ryan, Katherine Russell','Kaldeep Joshi',NULL,NULL,'ES-006A','The procedure outlines the response to spills, including small and large hazardous liquid and solid spills, propellant HFA spills, biological spills, and spills into surface water drains or soil. It includes steps for containment, cleanup, and reporting, as well as responsibilities for the Emergency Response Team (ERT), employees, and external emergency services.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland, Emergency Response: Immediate actions taken to mitigate the impact of an emergency, Emergency Response Team (ERT): A site-level team of specialized individuals for emergency response, Environmental Event: Any spill, release, or non-compliance with environmental regulations, HFA: Hydrofluoroalkane, a propellant used for metered-dose inhalers, Release: An environmental event, Rescue: Activities to locate and remove endangered persons from danger, Response: Activities in preparation for an emergency until emergency apparatus arrives, SDS: Safety Data Sheet, a document detailing the properties and hazards of a chemical, Spill: An environmental event categorized into small, large, and biological spills.','To establish a spill response procedure to ensure a coordinated response in the event of a spill, protecting health, safety, and the environment, and ensuring efficient incident reporting and investigation.','The scope applies to the prevention of and response to spills by the Emergency Response Team (ERT), employees, and contractors. It includes all minor and major spills on site.','Emergency Response Team (ERT): Carry out emergency procedures, respond to major spills, and participate in incident investigations. All Employees: Prevent spills, control and clean small spills, and report large spills. Facilities Team: Shut off valves and assist in spill cleanup. Microbiological Department: Control and clean biological spills. External Emergency Services: Handle major chemical or biological spills.','ES-006: 03-Feb-2017 - First Issued, ES-006A: 23-Jan-2020 - Updated to Amneal new logo, ES-006B: 02-Oct-2023 - Updated ERT responsibilities, added biological spill response, and minor editorial changes.','ES-008: Reporting and investigation of Accident, Incident, Near Miss or any kind of dangerous occurrence, N/A: Amneal Ireland Emergency Response Plan.'),(25,'ES-008B','REPORTING AND INVESTIGATION OF ACCIDENT, INCIDENT, NEAR MISS AND ANY KIND OF DANGEROUS OCCURRENCE','ES-008B Reporting and investigation of accident, incident.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','John O\'Dwyer','Olivier Gras, Paul Delaney',NULL,NULL,NULL,'ES-008A','The procedure outlines the reporting and investigation of accidents, incidents, near misses, and dangerous occurrences. It includes steps for incident reporting, root cause analysis (RCA), corrective and preventive actions (CAPA), and communication of lessons learned.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland, Affected Employees: Employees whose work or work areas could be affected by an incident or near miss, Causal Factor: Any factor contributing to the cause or severity of a hazard or failure, Controlled Substances: Substances requiring a license under the Misuse of Drugs Act, 1977, Co. Co.: County Council, CAPA: Corrective Action and/or Preventative Action, Dangerous Occurrence: An incident reportable to the HSA, EHS: Environmental, Health and Safety, Environmental Event: Any spill, release, or non-compliance with environmental regulations, EPA: Environmental Protection Agency, ERT: Emergency Response Team, First-Aid: One-time medical treatment for minor injuries, HSA: Health and Safety Authority, Illness: Non-traumatic physiological harm or loss of capacity, Incident: A work-related injury, illness, or significant event, Injury: A traumatic wound or condition caused by external forces, Irish Water: Water utility company in Ireland, Lost time Case: A nonfatal injury causing loss of time from work, Lost time Accident: Reportable to HSA if an employee cannot work for more than 3 consecutive days, Medical Treatment: Treatment administered by a physician, Notifiable Incident: An occurrence requiring notification to regulatory authorities, OH: Occupational Health, Potentially Affected Employees: Employees who could benefit from incident reports or corrective actions, Regulatory Authority: EPA, Tipperary County Council, HSA, Recordable Injury/Illness: Any work-related injury/illness requiring medical treatment beyond first aid, Root-Cause: The fundamental reason for a failure, SHWW: Safety, Health & Welfare at Work, Root Cause Analysis (RCA): A method of problem solving to identify root causes, Significant Event: EHS incidents requiring prompt reporting, Supervisor: Direct supervisor, Trend Analysis: The process of spotting patterns or trends, Work-related injury/illness: An injury or illness acquired or aggravated at work, Biological Incident: Unintended release or exposure to potentially infectious materials.','To establish a procedure for reporting and investigating accidents, incidents, near misses, and dangerous occurrences to ensure corrective and preventive actions are implemented, and adequate records are maintained.','This SOP applies to all accidents, incidents, near misses, and EHS non-conformances occurring on company premises or while on company business elsewhere. GMP investigations are performed as per SOP QM-010.','EHS Department: Report and document incidents, ensure RCA completion, track CAPAs, and notify regulatory authorities. All Employees: Report incidents, follow medical advice, and cooperate in investigations. Emergency Response Team/First Aiders/Occupational Health: Provide first aid, refer to Occupational Health, and report injuries. Leadership Team: Ensure emergency response activation, RCA team establishment, and CAPA implementation.','ES-008: 22-Dec-2016 - First Issued, ES-008A: 05-Dec-2019 - Updated to new template, ES-008B: cb - MN-3023 - Included EHS responsibility to report biological incidents, added definition of biological incident, and referenced European Directive 2000/54/EC.','FM-ES-009: Incident Investigation Form, FM-ES-010: 5-Why Worksheet, FM-ES-011: Incident Investigation Process Flow Diagram, N/A: Amneal Ireland Emergency Response Plan, FM-ES-008: Risk Assessment Form, QM-010: Investigation System, N/A: Local Government (Water Pollution) Acts 1977-1990, N/A: Radiological Protection Act of 1991, N/A: European Directive 2000/54/EC Biological Agents at Work.'),(26,'ES-009B','ENVIRONMENTAL HEALTH & SAFETY RISK ASSESSMENT','ES-009B EHS Risk Assessment.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Amanda Power','John O’Dwyer, John O\'Dwyer',NULL,'2020-08-04','2023-07-03','ES-009A','The procedure outlines the risk assessment process for work areas and activities at Amneal Ireland. It includes identifying hazards, assessing risks, and determining controls to prevent harm. Risks are prioritized using a scoring methodology, and control measures follow the hierarchy of controls.','Hazard: A potential source of harm or adverse health effect, Risk: Likelihood of harm or adverse health effects, Controls: Actions to reduce exposure to hazards, CAPA’s: Corrective action and preventative actions, EHS: Environmental Health and Safety, Risk Assessment: Process of identifying hazards, assessing risks, and determining controls, LTA: Lost Time Accident, OEL: Occupational exposure level, Safety Hazard: Hazards creating unsafe working conditions, Chemical Hazard: Chemical agents classified as dangerous substances, Physical Hazard: Environmental factors that can harm without physical contact, Biological Hazard: Viruses, bacteria, fungi, etc., Ergonomic Hazard: Physical factors causing musculoskeletal injuries, Psychosocial Hazard: Hazards affecting mental health or wellbeing, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To describe the procedure for effective risk assessment of work areas and activities at Amneal Ireland, ensuring adequate controls are in place to prevent harm.','This procedure applies to machine and ancillary equipment and work-related activities conducted inside the Amneal Ireland facility.','EHS is responsible for maintaining the EHS Risk Register, documenting risk assessments, and ensuring CAPA’s are recorded. The risk assessment team composition depends on the scope of the assessment.','ES-009: 06-Apr-2016 - First Issued, ES-009A: 16-Apr-2020 - Updated to new Amneal logo, ES-009B: 04-Aug-2020 - Added reference to activities and contractors, updated definitions, and restructured tables.','FM-ES-008: EHS Risk Assessment Form'),(27,'ES-010E','MANAGEMENT OF CONTRACTORS','ES-010E Management of Contractors.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','John Dwyer','Mark Smyth, Paul Delaney','Kuldeep Jóshi','2021-09-13','2024-09-18','ES-010D','The procedure outlines the management of contractors at Amneal Ireland, ensuring compliance with EU/Irish legislation and site EHS procedures. It includes contractor selection, documentation, permits, training, and incident management.','Site Contact: Person responsible for the Contractor’s activity, Approved Contractors List (ACL): List of approved contractors, Contractor: Individual or firm retained on a temporary/contractual basis, Contractor EHS Qualification Form: Form completed by potential contractors, Contractor Personnel: Non-Amneal employees performing work, Visitor: Individual on site not performing physical work, Method Statement: Document detailing job safety, Risk Assessment: Process to identify and control hazards, cGMP: Current good manufacturing practice, CE Mark: Indicates compliance with EU safety requirements, AF2 form: Form for notifying HSA of construction activity, PAT: Portable appliance test, LOTO: Lockout/Tagout procedure, EHS: Environmental, Health and Safety, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland, ISO 14001: Environmental Management System standard, EMAS: Environmental Management and Audit Scheme, ISO 45001: Health and Safety Management System standard, Lost time cases: Non-fatal injury causing loss of work time, Restricted Workday case: Employee prevented from performing routine functions, Medical Attention Cases: Treatment beyond first aid.','To describe the procedure for managing contractors at Amneal Ireland, ensuring compliance with EU/Irish legislation and site EHS procedures.','This procedure applies to all contract companies and personnel performing specific physical activities at the facility, including building maintenance, equipment installation, and construction projects. It does not apply to embedded contractors, temporary staff, or visitors.','Site Contact: Manages and coordinates contractor work, ensures training and compliance. Contract Companies: Ensure contractor employees follow procedures. Security: Manages access control and induction. EHS: Manages the contractor management process and maintains the Approved Contractors List. QA: Assesses GMP impact and maintains documentation.','ES-010: 04-Apr-2016 - First Issued, ES-010A: 20-Apr-2017 - Updated form references, ES-010B: 04-Jul-2017 - Updated definitions, ES-010C: 07-Feb-2018 - Updated form references and added points, ES-010D: 05-Feb-2020 - Updated to new Amneal logo, ES-010E: 13-Sep-2021 - Updated to include Covid-19 requirements, removed outdated references, and aligned with ISO 45001.','N/A: Safety, Health and Welfare at Work Act, 2005, Safety, Health and Welfare at Work (General Application) Regulations, 2007, Safety, Health and Welfare at Work (Construction) Regulations, 2013, FM-ES-004: Method Statement Risk Assessment, FM-ES-007: Approved Contractor List, FM-ES-003: Contractor EHS Qualification Form, N/A: Permit to Work Procedure, QA-006: Procurement and Approval of Miscellaneous Supplies, QM-044: Supplier Management and Control, QM-045: Covid-19 Pandemic GxP Practices, QRM-20: Good Manufacturing Practices related to Covid-19 Pandemic-01.'),(28,'FM-ES-009-02','Incident Investigation Form','FM-ES-009-02 Incident investigation form.docx','Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'The form is used to document and investigate incidents, including environmental or biological releases, injuries, and other potential incidents. It includes sections for incident details, injury details, environmental release information, root cause analysis (RCA), corrective and preventive actions (CAPA), and management review.',NULL,'To provide a structured format for documenting and investigating incidents, ensuring that corrective and preventive actions are identified and implemented.','This form applies to all incidents, including injuries, environmental releases, and other potential incidents that occur on-site or during company business.','EHS Department: Responsible for reviewing and approving the incident investigation form. Site Management: Responsible for verifying that CAPAs are appropriate and sustainable. Incident Investigators: Responsible for completing the form and conducting the root cause analysis.',NULL,NULL),(29,'FM-ES-010','5-Whys','FM-ES-010 5-Whys.docx','Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'The 5-Whys worksheet is a tool used for root cause analysis (RCA) to identify the underlying cause of a problem by repeatedly asking \"Why?\" until the root cause is determined. It helps in identifying corrective actions to prevent recurrence.',NULL,'To provide a structured approach for identifying the root cause of incidents or problems by asking \"Why?\" multiple times, leading to effective corrective actions.','This worksheet applies to all incidents, problems, or non-conformances that require root cause analysis within the organization.','Incident Investigators: Responsible for completing the 5-Whys worksheet as part of the root cause analysis process. EHS Department: Responsible for reviewing and approving the analysis.',NULL,NULL),(30,'FM-ES-010-00','Root Cause Analysis 5-Why Worksheet','FM-ES-010-00 Root Cause Analysis 5-why Worksheet.doc','Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'The 5-Why Worksheet is a tool used for root cause analysis (RCA) to identify the underlying cause of a problem by repeatedly asking \"Why?\" until the root cause is determined. It helps in identifying corrective actions to prevent recurrence.',NULL,'To provide a structured approach for identifying the root cause of incidents or problems by asking \"Why?\" multiple times, leading to effective corrective actions.','This worksheet applies to all incidents, problems, or non-conformances that require root cause analysis within the organization.','Incident Investigators: Responsible for completing the 5-Why Worksheet as part of the root cause analysis process. EHS Department: Responsible for reviewing and approving the analysis.',NULL,NULL),(31,'FM-ES-011-00','Incident Investigation Process Flow Diagram','FM-ES-011-00 Incident Investigation Process Flow Diagram.doc','Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'The Incident Investigation Process Flow Diagram provides a visual representation of the steps involved in investigating incidents, including securing the scene, notifying relevant authorities, conducting the investigation, and implementing corrective actions.',NULL,'To outline the process for investigating incidents, ensuring a structured and consistent approach to identifying root causes and implementing corrective actions.','This flow diagram applies to all incidents, including injuries, environmental releases, and other potential incidents that occur on-site or during company business.','EHS Department: Responsible for overseeing the incident investigation process. Incident Investigators: Responsible for following the flow diagram during investigations. Site Management: Responsible for reviewing and approving corrective actions.',NULL,NULL),(32,'QC-002G','SAMPLING OF RAW MATERIALS AT AMNEAL IRELAND','QC-002G Sampling of Raw Materials at Amneal Ireland.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','David Ryan','Paul O\'Mahony, Danny Ryan','Kuldeep Joshi','2023-04-01','2023-04-01','QC-002F','Defines procedures for sampling raw materials at Amneal Ireland. Includes responsibilities, sampling methods, and documentation requirements.','Raw Material, PPE, COA, ARN, QC/ARD, Amneal Ireland, QA, IPQA, SOP, COC, API, ANSI, MDI, DPI, IPA, Reference/Reserve Sample, Composite Sample','To define the procedures and practices to be used when sampling raw materials at Amneal Ireland.','Applies to all personnel involved in sampling raw materials intended for use in the manufacturing of Exhibit/Submission/IPQ/PV (non-commercial) Clinical (IMP Stage 02) products at Amneal Ireland.','QC/ARD: Outline SOP details, complete sampling request forms, and carry out sampling. Operations: Perform sampling, report deficiencies, ensure training. QA: Complete Area Line Sign-off.','QC-002: First Issued. QC-002A: Updated SOP template, added definitions, updated forms. QC-002B: Updated definitions, added new materials. QC-002C: Added pre-sampling checks. QC-002D: Updated responsibilities, added definitions. QC-002E: Updated sample quantities. QC-002F: Removed sampling log, added contaminant checks. QC-002G: Updated scope, added sampling tools, corrected typos.','FM-QC-034, FM-QC-035, FM-QC-038, FM-QC-258, FM-MF-005, MM-001, MM-011, MF-008, QC-028, QM-027, QC-009, MF-006, FM-MM-001, MM-022, FM-MF-052, FM-QM-099, FM-MF-034, MF-042, MF-014, MF-049, ANSI/ASQ Z1.9, WHO Technical Report Series, EudraLex Volume 4'),(33,'QC-001C','INVESTIGATION OF OUT-OF-SPECIFICATION (OOS) LABORATORY RESULTS','QC-001C Investigation of OOS Laboratory Results.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Agnieszka Lagocka','David Ryan, Paul O\'Mahony','Kuldeep Joshi','2023-06-23','2025-06-23','QC-001B','Defines procedures for managing OOS laboratory results. Includes responsibilities, investigation phases, and documentation requirements.','OOS, Atypical Results, Causative error, Obvious Error, Re-injection, Re-dilution, Re-preparation, Reportable result, Exhibit Batch, IMP, QP, API, CRO, Incident, Approved Document, Assignable / Definitive Cause, Invalid Result, Hypothesis/Investigative Testing, Retest, Resample, Remeasurement / Additional Testing, Quality Unit, Confirmed OOS, Unconfirmed OOS','To define the procedures for managing Laboratory Data, produced at Amneal Ireland, which is out of specification (OOS).','Applies to OOS results observed during routine laboratory testing at Amneal Ireland, including batch release testing, in-process control testing, stability studies, clinical trial batches, and OOS results generated under a failing system suitability.','All Laboratory staff: Report OOS results within one business day. Analyst: Ensure proper testing procedures, retain test preparations, and document errors. Laboratory Supervisor/Manager: Log OOS reports, conduct preliminary investigations, and prepare OOS investigation reports. Qualified Person and Head of Quality: Review and approve OOS investigation reports, determine further investigations, and notify regulatory agencies if necessary.','QC-001: First Issued. QC-001A: Updated for editorial changes, added CRO definition, removed redundant sections. QC-001B: Updated SOP template, added definitions, clarified OOS handling. QC-001C: Added clarification on scope, responsibilities, and investigation phases.','FM-QC-069, FM-QC-070, FM-QC-071, FM-QC-072, FM-QC-073, SOP QM-010, GQS_0007, SOP QM-019, SOP QC-046, SOP QC-086, SOP QC-085, SOP QM-028, FM-QC-224, FDA OOS Guidance, MHRA OOS Guidance, SOP QM-029'),(34,'QC-003F','SETTLE PLATE SAMPLING','QC-003F Settle Plate Sampling.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Anne McGrath','Linda Bannon, Karen Barry','Kuldeep Joshi','2022-09-13','2025-09-13','QC-003E','Describes the Settle Plate Sampling Process for evaluating the microbiological quality of air in cleanrooms. Includes setup, operation, and handling of settle plates.','IPA – Iso Propyl Alcohol, QC/ARD – Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development/Microbiology, SOP – Standard Operating Procedure, QA – Quality Assurance, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To describe the Settle Plate Sampling Process for the evaluation of the microbiological quality of the air in the Amneal Ireland cleanrooms.','Limited to the Set Up, Operation, and Handling of the Settle Plates sampling at Amneal Ireland. Refer to SOP QC-075 for the Settle Plate Environmental Monitoring Sampling plan and Monitoring locations.','All personnel involved in Settle Plate Sampling must adhere to this SOP. QC/ARD Microbiology personnel are responsible for monitoring sample management. Environmental Monitoring Samplers (QA, QC/ARD, Operations) must contact manufacturing and liaise with the planner before performing environmental monitoring sampling.','QC-003: First Issued. QC-003A: Updated incubation conditions. QC-003B: Updated sampling plan, incubation conditions, and handling procedures. QC-003C: Updated responsibilities and exposure time handling. QC-003D: Updated references to QC-075, added responsibilities, and revised handling procedures. QC-003E: Updated template and logo, revised exposure time tolerance. QC-003F: Minor editorial changes, updated handling and labelling procedures.','QC-011: Routine Microbiological Environmental monitoring. QC-075: Environmental Monitoring Sampling and Incubation Procedure. ES-001: Material Destruction and Waste Management Procedure.'),(35,'QC-004G','OPERATION OF MAS-100 AIR SAMPLER','QC-004G Operation of Mas-100 Air Sampler.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Karen Barry','Anne McGrath, Linda Bannon','Kuldeep Joshi','2023-03-10','2025-09-06','QC-004F','Describes the steps needed for the operation of the MAS-100 Microbiological air sampler to perform environmental monitoring at Amneal Ireland. Includes setup, operation, handling, and cleaning of the MAS-100.','LED – Light Emitting Diode, IPA – Iso Propyl Alcohol, MAS – Microbial Air Sampler, HEPA – High-Efficiency Particulate Air, QC – Quality Control, QA – Quality Assurance, SOP – Standard Operating Procedure, STD – Standard Mode, TSA – Tryptic Soy Agar, L – Litre, v/v – Volume per volume, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland, QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development/ Microbiology.','To describe the steps needed for operation of the MAS-100 Microbiological air sampler to perform environmental monitoring at Amneal Ireland.','Limited to the Set-up, Operation, Handling, and Cleaning of the MAS-100. The MAS-100 is used in Amneal Ireland to monitor the microbiological quality of the air in specified manufacturing areas. Refer to SOP-QC-075 for Active Air Environmental Monitoring Sampling plan and Monitoring locations.','All personnel using the MAS-100 must adhere to this SOP. Personnel operating the equipment must report any faults or damage and use a trolley where possible. Environmental Monitoring Samplers (QA, QC/ARD, Operations) must contact manufacturing and liaise with the planner before performing environmental monitoring sampling.','QC-004: First Issued. QC-004A: Updated sampling plan, incubation conditions, and handling procedures. QC-004B: Updated calibration frequency and handling procedures. QC-004C: Updated references to QC-075, added responsibilities, and revised handling procedures. QC-004D: Updated template and logo, revised calibration and handling procedures. QC-004E: Updated volume settings. QC-004F: Updated handling and labelling procedures, added trolley usage. QC-004G: Updated forms, handling procedures, and calibration details.','QC-011: Routine Microbiological Environmental Monitoring, MM-002: Movement of Material between the Warehouse and Manufacturing and between Warehouse and PD Laboratory, MF-006: Movement of Material, Equipment & Waste To & From the Warehouse into Manufacturing, QC-074: Environmental Monitoring Reading and Reporting Procedure, QC-075: Environmental Monitoring Sampling and Incubation Procedure, ES-001: Material Destruction and Waste Management Procedure, QM-010: Unplanned Deviations & Investigations, QC-086: Handling of Laboratory Incidents in the QC/ARD and Microbiology Laboratories, FM-QC-086: Positive Hole Conversion Table, FM-QM-112: Out of Use Status Label, FM-QC-171: MDI Routine Microbiological Environmental Monitoring and Reporting Record, FM-QC-175: DPI Routine Microbiological Environmental Monitoring and Reporting Record, FM-QC-178: General Routine Microbiological Environmental Monitoring and Reporting Record, FM-QC-281: CNC-XP-35 Microbiological Environmental Monitoring and Reporting, QC-017: Operation and Maintenance of VWR USC 300T /1700T /2600T Ultrasonic Cleaning Baths, QM-007: Calibration Policy, QC-022: Control of Laboratory Instruments.'),(36,'QC-006G','REVIEW OF LABORATORY RECORDS','QC-006G Review of Laboratory Records.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD','David Ryan, Paul O’Mahony, David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2021-11-17',NULL,'QC-006F','Controls for the review of laboratory records include written procedures, training, review, audit, and self-inspection controls. Analyst data review, peer review, and final approval are key steps in the process.','Approved document: Data entry documents approved for recording the execution of an analytical method. Original Data: Includes the first or source capture of data or information and all subsequent data required to fully reconstruct the conduct of the laboratory activity.','To describe the procedure for the review, approval, and distribution of data in the Quality Control and Analytical Research & Development (QC/ARD) department to assure the integrity of all laboratory data is maintained.','This SOP applies to the review of laboratory records, both physical and electronic, in the QC/ARD laboratories at Amneal, Ireland.','Laboratory personnel shall comply with the requirements of this procedure. Laboratory personnel must ensure that they are trained to the current version of this procedure. Laboratory Manager or designee shall be responsible to ensure that the steps outlined in this procedure are followed.','QC-006: First issued on 30-Sep-2016. QC-006A: Updated on 09-Jan-2017. QC-006B: Updated on 26-Apr-2017. QC-006C: Updated on 30-Jun-2017. QC-006D: Updated on 20-May-2019. QC-006E: Updated on 19-Jun-2019. QC-006F: Updated on 29-Sep-2021. QC-006G: Updated on 17-Nov-2021.','QC-010: Recording and reporting of Laboratory test data. QM-004: Good Documentation Practices. QC-001: Investigation of Out of Specification Laboratory results. QC-015: The receipt, preparation, storage, labelling and expiration of reagents, solutions and solvents. QC-020: Evaluation of system suitability data for HPLC, GC and UV-Vis applications. QC-021: Operation of Empower Software. QC-022: Control of Laboratory Instruments. QM-036: Data Integrity and Records Management. QM-010: Investigation System. QC-019: Integration of Chromatograms in QC/ARD Lab. QC-043: Release of Results from QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal Ireland.'),(37,'QC-007C','CONTACT PLATE SAMPLING','QC-007C Contact Plate Sampling.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Anne McGrath, QC/ARD','Katherine Russell, QC/ARD','Katherine Russell, QC/ARD','2021-11-09',NULL,'QC-007B','Contact Plate sampling is used to detect microorganisms on surfaces that could lead to product contamination. The procedure includes set-up, operation, and handling of Contact Plates during sampling.','IPA – Iso Propyl Alcohol, QC – Quality Control, TSA – Tryptic Soya Agar, QC/ARD – Quality/ Analytical Research and Development/Microbiology, QA – Quality Assurance, SOP - Standard Operating Procedure, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To describe the steps needed for Contact Plate sampling at Amneal Ireland. This can also be referred to as Surface Plate sampling.','The scope of this SOP is limited to the set-up, operation, and handling of the Contact Plates during sampling. Contact Plate sampling is used in Amneal Ireland to detect microorganisms on surfaces that could lead to product contamination.','It is the responsibility of all personnel completing Contact Plate sampling to adhere to this SOP. It is the responsibility of Environmental Monitoring Samplers (QA, QC/ARD, Operations) to contact manufacturing and to liaise with the planner prior to performing environmental monitoring sampling.','QC-007: First Issued on 25-May-2016. QC-007A: Updated on 14-Apr-2017. QC-007B: Updated on 29-Nov-2018. QC-007C: Updated on 08-Nov-2021.','QC-011: Routine Microbiological Environmental Monitoring, QC-075: Environmental Monitoring Sampling and Incubation Procedure, ES-001: Material Destruction and Waste Management Procedure.'),(38,'QC-008E','OPERATION, CALIBRATION AND MAINTENANCE OF KARL FISCHER TITRATOR (METROHM 851 TITRANDO)','QC-008E Operation Calibration Maintenance of Karl Fischer Titrator.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Patrick Flynn, QC/ARD','David Ryan, QC/ARD, Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2021-07-23','2021-07-22','QC-008D','The procedure includes pre-use checks, cleaning, conditioning, calibration, sample analysis, and maintenance of the Karl Fischer Titrator. Calibration must be performed prior to sample analysis, and maintenance activities are documented in the Karl Fischer Usage and Maintenance Logbook.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. RSD: Relative Standard Deviation. NMT: Not More Than. Tiamo: Tiamo 2.5 multi software.','To define the procedure for the operation, calibration, and maintenance of Karl Fischer Titrator (Metrohm 851 Titrando).','This procedure applies to the Quality Control and Analytical Research & Development (QC/ARD) Laboratory at Amneal, Ireland.','The Laboratory personnel shall follow the instructions in this procedure. The Laboratory Manager is responsible for ensuring that Laboratory personnel comply with this procedure.','QC-008: First Issued on 09-Sep-2016. QC-008A: Updated on 23-Aug-2018. QC-008B: Updated on 10-Dec-2018. QC-008C: Updated on 27-Jul-2020. QC-008D: Updated on 20-Oct-2020. QC-008E: Updated on 23-Jul-2021.','Karl Fischer Calibration Form (FM-QC-003), Karl Fischer Usage and Maintenance Logbook (FM-QC-004), SOP QC-082: Operational use of Tiamo software, SOP QC-022: Control of Laboratory Instruments.'),(39,'QC-009I','RECEIPT AND HANDLING OF INCOMING SAMPLES IN THE QC/ARD AND MICROBIOLOGY LABORATORY','QC-009I Receipt & Handling of incoming samples in QC-Micro Lab.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','David Ryan','David Ryan, Ashok Gulati, Paul O\'Mahony, Kuldeep Joshi','Ashok Gulati, Paul O\'Mahony, Kuldeep Joshi','2023-04-03','2023-10-01','QC-009H','Sample submission, receipt verification, sample identification, sample storage, sample disposal, external laboratory handling, reporting of results, monthly review.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. COA: Certificate of Analysis. Non-cleaning samples: Samples other than Cleaning Validation/Verification Samples. CL: Cleaning. EM: Environmental Monitoring. QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development. ID: Identification. CVR: Cleaning Validation Report. Approved Document: Data entry documents approved for recording the execution of an analytical method e.g. bound logbooks, bound notebooks, Laboratory analytical worksheets (LAWs). LAW: Laboratory Analytical Worksheet.','To provide a procedure for the submission, receipt and handling of all samples submitted to the Quality Control / Analytical Research & Development Laboratory and to the Quality Control / Analytical Research and Development Microbiology Laboratory.','This procedure applies to the submission, receipt and handling of all samples (i.e. raw materials, packaging materials, in process, finished product, stability, cleaning and other samples) received in the QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal, Ireland. This procedure also applies to the submission, receipt and handling of all samples (i.e. EM, media plates, consumables and other samples) received in the QC/ARD Microbiology Laboratory at Amneal Ireland. Retain (Reference /Retention) samples are outside the scope of this SOP and are covered by SOP QM-027.','Personnel involved in the submission and handling of samples shall comply with the requirements of this procedure and ensure that they are trained to the current version of this procedure. QC/ARD personnel or designee involved in the receipt and handling of incoming samples shall comply with the requirements of this procedure and must ensure that they are trained to the current version of this procedure. Laboratory Manager or designee must ensure that all personnel performing the steps outlined in this procedure are appropriately trained.','QC-009: 28-Sep-2016 - First Issued. QC-009A: 20-Dec-2017 - Updated to include handling of all samples, removed duplication, added definitions. QC-009B: 26-Oct-2018 - Updated title, included Microbiology Laboratory, clarified sample identification format. QC-009C: 16-May-2019 - Updated template, added new sections. QC-009D: 20-Jun-2020 - Included submission and receipt, updated sample identification formats. QC-009E: 22-Jun-2020 - Added monthly sample receipt check. QC-009F: 16-Nov-2021 - Updated DPI content uniformity sample submission. QC-009G: 26-Apr-2022 - Updated sample identification for development samples. QC-009H: 22-Nov-2022 - Added documentation for sample removal. QC-009I: 03-Apr-2023 - Added sample inspection instructions.','FM-QC-005: Sample Receipt Logbook. QM-027: Retention Sample Management. FM-MF-034: Sample Test Request Form. MF-042: Procedure for Sample Movement/Management. MF-020: Product Development Sample Analysis Request. MM-011: Courier Shipments. QC-011: Routine Microbiological Environmental Monitoring. QC-074: Environmental Monitoring Reading and Reporting Procedure. QC-075: Environmental Monitoring Sampling and Incubation Procedure. QC-010: Recording and Reporting of Laboratory Test Data. QC-028: Sample Transfer to Global Amneal Sites. ES-001: Material Destruction and Waste Management Procedure. FM-QC-196: QC/ARD Sample Receipt Log. FM-QC-195: QC/ARD Cleaning Sample Receipt Log. FM-MF-032: Sample Label. FM-QC-039: QC/ARD Test Request Form. MF-086: Operation of RF-Smart Labelling. QC-043: Release of Results from QC-ARD. FM-MF-026: Sample for Analysis label. FM-QC-257: Sample Receipt Monthly Review Logbook. FM-QC-283: QC/ARD Development Sample Receipt Log.'),(40,'QC-010H','RECORDING AND REPORTING OF LABORATORY TEST DATA','QC-010H Recording Reporting of Lab Test Data.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Seyanly Anchan','Ashok Gulati, Paul O\'Mahony','Kuldeep Joshi','2022-02-02','2025-02-01','QC-010G','Recording and reporting of laboratory test data, handling of raw data, rounding analytical data, use of Laboratory Analytical Worksheets (LAWs), handling of microbiology results, and monthly review of laboratory records.','Raw Data: Original records and documentation retained in the format in which they were originally generated. Final test result: Result reported on the Certificate of Analysis. Approved Document: Data entry documents approved for recording the execution of an analytical method. Decimal place: Position of a digit to the right of a decimal point. Significant figure: Any digit of a number that is known with certainty. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. TRSF: Test Request Submission Form. Contract Laboratory Requirement (CLR): Document detailing the procedure and specifications for a validated Test Method. C of A: Certificate of Analysis. Data Integrity: Completeness, consistency, and accuracy of data. UD: Unplanned Deviation. NOE: Notification of Event.','To describe the procedure for the recording and reporting of data in the QC/ARD laboratory to assure the integrity of all laboratory data is maintained. To describe the procedure for documenting and reporting Microbiology Results.','This procedure applies to all personnel in the Quality Control and Analytical Research & Development (QC/ARD)/Microbiology department at Amneal, Ireland.','Laboratory personnel shall comply with the requirements of this procedure. Laboratory Manager or designee shall ensure that the steps outlined in this procedure are followed. Laboratory Manager or designee must ensure that all personnel performing the steps outlined in this procedure are appropriately trained. Laboratory personnel is responsible for printing the current version of the LAW from the designated controlled location. Laboratory manager or designee shall be responsible for assigning a unique Laboratory Analytical Worksheets prior to use. QA Document Control are responsible for issuance of approved bound logbooks/notebooks upon request.','QC-010: 30-Sep-2016 - First Issued. QC-010A: 21-Dec-2017 - Updated to include handling of all samples, removed duplication, added definitions. QC-010B: 28-Feb-2019 - Updated procedure to new template, updated Amneal logo, added sections for Microbiology. QC-010C: 15-May-2019 - Updated responsibilities, clarified sample identification formats. QC-010D: 30-Jul-2020 - Clarified sample handling and reporting procedures. QC-010E: 12-Mar-2021 - Updated LAW formats and added new sections. QC-010F: 06-Sep-2021 - Updated diluent handling precautions. QC-010G: 29-Sep-2021 - Updated Approved Document definition and added new sections. QC-010H: 24-Jun-2022 - Added new sections for sample inspection and updated LAW formats.','FM-QC-006: Guideline for reporting test results. FM-QC-108: Microbiological impact assessment of an atypical growth result found during FP testing for organisms of concern. FM-QC-109: Log of Microbiological impact assessment numbers. FM-QC-203: Assignment of LAW numbers logbook. FM-QC-204: Laboratory Analytical Data Pack Cover Page. FM-QC-205: 1298-AS LAW for Blend Uniformity and Blend Assay. FM-QC-206: 1298-AS LAW Blister Content Uniformity and Assay. FM-QC-207: 1298-CL LAW for Cleaning Verification. FM-QC-208: 1298-WC LAW for Water Content. FM-QC-209: 1298-APSD LAW for Aerodynamic Particle Size Distribution. FM-QC-210: 1290-AL LAW for Alcohol Content. FM-QC-211: 1290-CL LAW for Cleaning Verification. FM-QC-212: 1290-AS LAW for Assay. FM-QC-213: 1290-KF LAW for Water Content. FM-QC-214: 1291-AL LAW for Alcohol Content. FM-QC-215: 1291-AS LAW for Assay. FM-QC-216: 1291-KF LAW for Water Content. FM-QC-217: 1291-CL LAW for Cleaning Verification. FM-QC-218: MDI-GM LAW for General Method for Description. FM-QC-219: LQ-CL LAW for Cleaning Verification. FM-QC-260: 1614-CL LAW for Cleaning Verification. FM-QC-261: LAW for General Tests. FM-QC-262: 1614-AS LAW for Assay. FM-QC-263: 1614-WC LAW for Water Content. SOP QM-004: Good Documentation Practices. SOP QA-001: Procedure for Document Issuance. SOP QM-009: Document Storage and Retention. SOP QC-001: Investigation of Out of specification (OOS) laboratory results. SOP QC-006: Review of Laboratory records. SOP QM-010: Unplanned Deviations and Investigation System. SOP QC-034: Management of QC/ARD specifications, analytical methods (procedures) and method transfer protocols. SOP QC-049: Notification of event from contract laboratories to Amneal Ireland. SOP QC-083: Handling of Microbiology Out of Specifications (OOS) Results. SOP QM-013: Change Control System. SOP QM-024: Management of Electronic Forms. SOP QC-028: Sample Transfer to Global Amneal Sites. SOP QM-036: Data Integrity and Records Management. SOP QC-085: Investigation of atypical results reported in QC Lab. FM-QC-253: 01-1623-AS LAW for Assay. FM-QC-254: 01-1623-RC LAW for Related Compounds. FM-QC-255: 01-1623-RS LAW for Residual Solvents. FM-QC-291: LAW for additional pages.'),(41,'QC-011K','ROUTINE MICROBIOLOGICAL ENVIRONMENTAL MONITORING','QC-011K Routine Microbiological EM.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Anne McGrath','Linda Bannon, Katherina Russell','Kuldeep Joshi','2023-06-06','2024-06-06','QC-011J','Procedure for performing Microbiological Environmental Monitoring (EM) of the MDI and DPI Inhalation Facility. Includes safety, methodology, frequency, sampling requirements, incubation conditions, acceptance criteria, failure handling, and trending of results.','At Rest/Static, In Operation/Dynamic, CFU, EM, ISO, MDI, MAS, VAS, QA, QC/ARD, OOS, TSA, DPI, QMS, SOP, HVAC, PPE, NMT, QP, PD, Alert Limit, Action Limit, Specification Limit, Adverse trend, Potential Organism of Concern, Amneal Ireland, CNC','To describe the procedure for performing Microbiological Environmental Monitoring (EM) of the MDI and DPI Inhalation Facility.','This procedure applies to Viable Environmental Monitoring of the Inhalation Facility at Amneal Ireland. Environmental monitoring is performed within the ISO 7 and ISO 8 classified areas and selected CNC area (XP-35) in the Inhalation facility.','Environmental Monitoring Samplers (QA, QC/ARD, Operations) are responsible for sampling. QC/ARD Microbiology personnel handle sample receipt, incubation, reading, and reporting. They also perform colony morphology analysis, streaking, and gram staining. The approved Contract Laboratory is responsible for organism identification and data reporting.','QC-011 (08-Jul-2016): First Issued. QC-011A (24-Jan-2017): Added incubation details. QC-011B (14-Apr-2017): Updated scope and responsibilities. QC-011C (28-Jun-2017): Added DPI references. QC-011D (09-Oct-2017): Added definitions for Adverse Trends and Potential Organism of Concern. QC-011E (21-Dec-2017): Updated responsibilities and sampling details. QC-011F (14-Sep-2018): Updated sampling and monitoring details. QC-011G (26-Oct-2018): Updated responsibilities and definitions. QC-011H (12-Oct-2021): Updated titles and investigation details. QC-011I (30-Mar-2022): Included CNC XP-35 area and updated monitoring details. QC-011J (30-Mar-2022): Updated titles and investigation details.','FM-QC-097, FM-QC-187, FM-QC-188, QC-003, QC-007, QC-004, MF-009, QM-010, QM-013, QC-049, QC-074, QC-075, QC-079, EudraLex, QM-019, MF-007, FM-QC-198, QC-086'),(42,'QC-012B','CHROMATOGRAPHIC COLUMN MANAGEMENT','QC-012B Chromatographic Column Mgt in the Quality Control Laboratory.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'QC-012A','Procedure for managing chromatographic columns in the QC/AR&D Laboratory. Includes column identification, usage logging, storage, cleaning, and disposal.',NULL,'To describe the procedure for managing chromatographic columns in the QC/AR&D Laboratory.','This procedure applies to the management of HPLC, UPLC, and GC columns in the QC/AR&D Laboratory at Amneal Ireland.','QC/AR&D Laboratory personnel are responsible for column identification, usage logging, storage, cleaning, and disposal.','QC-012 (09-Sep-2016): First Issue. QC-012A (20-Aug-2019): Updated SOP and FM-QC-008 to new format. Removed reference to Appendix and specific facility. QC-012B (CC-AMN-23-2555): Updated Form FM-QC-008 to record column receipt activity separately from usage activity. Added new Form FM-QC-298 for column usage logging.','FM-QC-008: Column receipt Logbook. FM-QC-298: Column usage logbook.'),(43,'QC-013B','OPERATION, CALIBRATION AND MAINTENANCE OF THE METTLER TOLEDO SEVENCOMPACT pH METER AND SENSOR','QC-013B Op, Cal & Maintenance of the pH Meter and Sensor.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD','Carla Berglin, Paul O’Mahony','Kudeco Joshii, QA','2020-07-01','2025-04-01','QC-013A','1. Two display modes: full information screen and measurement close-up screen.\n2. Daily calibration required before use.\n3. Three-point calibration using pH buffers 2.00, 4.00, and 7.00.\n4. Maintenance includes keeping the meter clean and ensuring the electrode is properly stored and filled.','1. pH: negative decimal reciprocal log of the hydrogen ion activity of a solution.\n2. LabX: proprietary Mettler software.\n3. ATC: automatic temperature control.\n4. MTC: manual temperature control.\n5. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To define the operation, calibration, and maintenance of the Mettler Toledo SevenCompact pH meter and sensor.','This procedure applies to the use of the Mettler Toledo SevenCompact pH meter and sensor by all QC/ARD personnel at Amneal Ireland.','1. All personnel using the instrument must adhere to this procedure.\n2. The Laboratory Manager (or designee) is responsible for ensuring the procedure is followed.\n3. Any problems encountered must be reported immediately to the Laboratory Manager (or designee).\n4. Personnel must be trained to the current revision of this document.','1. QC-013: First Issued on 03-Oct-2016.\n2. QC-013A: Updated SOP logo and removed reference to Appendix on 12-Sep-2019.\n3. QC-013B: Updated sections 5.2.1, 5.2.4, 5.3, and 5.3.9 on 01-Jul-2020.','1. FM-QC-011: pH instrument calibration logbook form.\n2. FM-QC-010: pH meter maintenance and usage logbook form.\n3. United States Pharmacopeia General Chapter <791>.'),(44,'QC-014A','OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF DESICCATOR','QC-014A Operation & Maintenance of Dessicator (2).pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Brigid Hayes, QC/ARD','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD, Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2020-04-24','2025-04-23','QC-014','1. Reference standards stored in the Desiccator must be logged in the Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-015).\n2. Desiccators contain dry desiccant (e.g., silica gel) to minimize moisture exposure.\n3. Desiccators must be monitored monthly with a Hygrometer.\n4. Desiccant should be replaced when % relative humidity exceeds 40% or if the desiccant colour changes.','1. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To define the operation and maintenance of Desiccators in the Quality Control and Analytical Research & Development (QC/ARD) Laboratory.','This procedure applies to the use of Desiccators by all Laboratory personnel at Amneal, Ireland.','1. All Laboratory personnel must follow the instructions in this procedure.\n2. The Laboratory Manager is responsible for ensuring the procedure is adhered to.','1. QC-014: First Issued on 29-Sep-2016.\n2. QC-014A: Updated SOP format, included reference to FM-QC-015, and updated monitoring frequency to monthly.','1. FM-QC-012: Desiccator Monitoring and Maintenance Logbook.\n2. FM-QC-015: Incoming Reference Standards Logbook.'),(45,'QC-015E','THE RECEIPT, PREPARATION, STORAGE, LABELLING AND EXPIRATION OF STANDARDS, REAGENTS AND SOLVENTS','QC-015E Receipt Prep Storage Label & Exp of Reagent Solutions.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Ashok Gulati, QC/ARD','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD, David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2020-05-05','2023-04-04','QC-015D','1. All lab personnel must read and understand SDS for chemicals and use correct PPE.\n2. Chemicals, standards, reagents, and solvents must be labelled with details such as chemical name, date of receipt, expiry date, and storage conditions.\n3. Solutions must be prepared in a fume hood and stored in designated areas.\n4. Expired solutions and reagents must be disposed of following SOP ES-001.\n5. Solutions must be visually checked for integrity before use.','1. Standardized Solutions: Solutions of known concentration for quantitative determinations.\n2. Test Solutions and Indicators: Solutions of definitive concentrations for specific purposes.\n3. Indicators: Reagents used to determine end points in chemical reactions.\n4. Buffers: Solutions that resist changes in pH.\n5. Sample Solutions: Solutions prepared from test samples for analytical determinations.\n6. Standard Solutions: Solutions prepared from reference standards for quantitative determination.\n7. COA: Certificate of Analysis.\n8. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\n9. QC: Quality Control.\n10. ARD: Analytical Research and Development.\n11. SDS: Safety Data Sheet.\n12. PPE: Personal Protective Equipment.','To outline the steps for receiving, preparing, storing, labelling, and assigning expiry dates to reagents, solutions, and solvents within QC/ARD at Amneal Ireland.','This procedure applies to all solutions prepared in QC/ARD at Amneal Ireland and their subsequent handling.','1. All personnel within QC/ARD must adhere to this procedure.\n2. The Laboratory Manager or designee is responsible for ensuring the procedure is followed.','1. QC-015: First Issued on 30-Sep-2016.\n2. QC-015A: Updated on 27-Jul-2018 to include PPE definition and safety steps.\n3. QC-015B: Updated on 07-Aug-2019 to remove references to appendices and update labelling requirements.\n4. QC-015C: Updated on 14-Jan-2020 to correct typographical errors and include analytical procedure version numbers.\n5. QC-015D: Updated on 27-May-2020 to include best practices for weighing and preparing solutions.\n6. QC-015E: Updated on 05-May-2020 to include monthly standard review checks.','1. FM-QC-009: Laboratory Chemical Register Log.\n2. FM-QC-014: Laboratory Solutions Preparation Log.\n3. FM-QC-126: Seal Wash Preparation Log.\n4. FM-QC-127: Needle Wash Preparation Log.\n5. FM-QC-128: Diluent 1298-AS/1298-CL/1298-APSD Preparation Log.\n6. FM-QC-129: Standard Solution 1298-AS Preparation Log.\n7. FM-QC-130: Standard Solution 1298-CL Preparation Log.\n8. FM-QC-131: Buffer 1298-AS/1298-CL/1298-APSD Preparation Log.\n9. FM-QC-132: Mobile Phase 1298-AS/1298-APSD Preparation Log.\n10. FM-QC-133: Mobile Phase 1298-CL Preparation Log.\n11. FM-QC-134: Standard LQ-CL Preparation Log.\n12. FM-QC-135: Standard Solution 1298-APSD Preparation Log.\n13. FM-QC-231: Laboratory Chemical Register Monthly Review Log.\n14. FM-QC-233: Diluent 1290-AS Preparation Log.\n15. FM-QC-234: Diluent 1290-CL Preparation Log.\n16. FM-QC-236: Mobile Phase 1290-AS Preparation Log.\n17. FM-QC-237: Mobile Phase 1290-CL Preparation Log.\n18. FM-QC-239: Standard Solution 1290-AS Preparation Log.\n19. ES-001: Material, Destruction and Waste Management Procedure.\n20. ES-005: Usage of Personal Protective Equipment (PPE).\n21. QC-029: Gowning Procedure for QC/ARD Laboratory Entry.\n22. P_CQCM-0231: Control of Laboratory Reagents, Solutions and Expiration dating.\n23. QC-016: Usage, Handling and Qualification of Reference Standards.\n24. QC-067: General Laboratory Practices in QC/ARD.\n25. QC-033: Operation Maintenance Cleaning and Calibration of Weigh Balances in the QC/ARD Laboratory.\n26. QC-084: Operation and Calibration of Sartorius MSA6.6s Balance.\n27. FM-QC-246: Standard Solution 1290-AL Preparation Log.\n28. FM-QC-247: Standard Solution 1291-AS Preparation Log.\n29. FM-QC-248: Standard Solution 1291-AL Preparation Log.\n30. FM-QC-249: Standard Solution 1291-CL Preparation Log.\n31. FM-QC-250: Mobile Phase 1291-AS Preparation Log.\n32. FM-QC-251: Mobile Phase 1291-CL Preparation Log.\n33. FM-QC-015: Incoming Reference Standards Logbook.\n34. FM-QC-016: Reference Standards Monthly review Log.\n35. FM-QC-252: Diluent 1291-AS Preparation Log.'),(46,'QC-016C','USAGE, HANDLING AND QUALIFICATION OF REFERENCE STANDARDS','QC-016C Usage, Handling & Qualification of Reference Standards.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Ashok Gulati, QC/ARD','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD, David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2020-05-07','2023-04-08','QC-016B','1. Reference standards must be logged in immediately upon receipt and stored appropriately.\n2. Reference standards must be used before their expiration date.\n3. In-house reference standards are to be used on an \"as is\" basis.\n4. Compendial Reference Standards (CRS) do not require additional qualification testing.\n5. In-house Reference Standards (HRS) must be qualified against a CRS or vendor-supplied certified reference material.','1. QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research & Development.\n2. Internal Standard (IS): A Reference Standard used as an internal standard in chromatographic analysis.\n3. Reference Material (RS): A material used as a reference standard for calibration and/or assay purposes.\n4. Primary Reference Standard (PRS): A reference standard certified to conform to specific criteria.\n5. Compendial Reference Standard (CRS): A reference standard certified by recognized suppliers such as USP, BP, Ph. Eur., etc.\n6. In-house Reference Standards (HRS): Reference standards certified by Amneal Ireland QC/ARD.\n7. Active Pharmaceutical Ingredient (API): The biologically active ingredient of a pharmaceutical drug.\n8. Amneal Ireland Reference Standard (AIRS) number: A unique number assigned to reference standards by Amneal Ireland.','To describe the procedures for acquiring, storing, handling, using, drying, qualifying, labelling, and distributing Reference Standards.','This SOP applies to the receipt, usage, handling, and qualification of reference standard material within the QC/AR&D department at Amneal Ireland.','1. All analysts must ensure that the reference standard (primary or secondary) lot used is within its expiry date.\n2. The QC/ARD Manager (or designee) is responsible for maintaining storage facilities for reference standards.\n3. The QC/ARD Manager (or designee) is responsible for ensuring that all analysts follow this procedure.\n4. The QC/ARD Manager (or designee) is responsible for maintaining an up-to-date log of all reference standards within QC/AR&D.','1. QC-016: First Issued on 30-Sep-2016.\n2. QC-016A: Updated on 24-Sep-2019 to include labelling and second person check upon receipt of standards.\n3. QC-016B: Updated on 26-May-2020 to include a new section on handling reference standards.\n4. QC-016C: Updated on 05-May-2020 to include instructions for monthly standard review and checks by preparer and reviewer.','1. FM-QC-015: Incoming Reference Standards Log.\n2. FM-QC-016: Reference Standard Monthly Review Log.\n3. FM-QC-017: Reference Standard Report form.\n4. QC-015: The Receipt, Preparation, Storage, Labelling and Expiration of Standards, Reagents and Solvents.\n5. Eudralex Chapter 6, Quality Control.\n6. British Pharmacopoeia (BP).\n7. European Pharmacopoeia (Ph. Eur.).\n8. United States Pharmacopeia (USP).\n9. National Institute of Science and Technology (NIST).'),(47,'QC-017A','OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF VWR USC 300T/1700T/2600T ULTRASONIC CLEANING BATHS','QC-017AOperation & Maintenance of the Ultrasonic Cleaning Baths.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Brigid Hayes, QC/ARD','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2020-04-24','2029-04-23','QC-017','1. Unplug the ultrasonic bath before filling or emptying the tank.\n2. Use only water-based cleaning solutions.\n3. Do not operate the ultrasonic bath dry.\n4. Set the timer for sonication.\n5. Degas HPLC solutions by sonication.\n6. Perform monthly maintenance by emptying and refilling the tank.','SOP: Standard Operating Procedure\nHPLC: High Performance Liquid Chromatography\nQC/ARD: Quality Control/ Analytical Research and Development\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To define the procedure for the operation and routine maintenance of the VWR USC 300T, 1700T, and 2600T ultrasonic baths.','This procedure applies to the Quality Control department at Amneal Ireland.','1. All QC/ARD personnel must follow the procedure correctly.\n2. The Laboratory Manager must ensure adherence to the procedure.\n3. Report any equipment problems to the Laboratory Manager.\n4. Ensure all users are trained on the current SOP revision.','QC-017: 30-Sep-2016 - First Issued\nQC-017A: 24-Apr-2020 - Updated SOP to new format, removed reference to Appendix, updated degassing method, and changed monthly water replacement.','FM-QC-018: Ultrasonic Bath Instrument Maintenance Logbook'),(48,'QC-018B','OPERATION, QUALIFICATION AND MAINTENANCE OF THE BINDER DRYING OVENS','QC-018B Operation Qualification & Maintenance of Binder Drying Ovens.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Eva Quinlan, QC/ARD','Elizabeth Moore, Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuddeep Jóshi, QA','2020-10-15','2023-10-14','QC-018A','1. Use thermal gloves or tongs for sample transfer.\n2. Check the safety device operation.\n3. Set the safety device response.\n4. Operate the oven using the control panel.\n5. Perform qualification and maintenance as per schedule.\n6. Record all samples in the usage logbook.','LED: light emitting diode\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To define the procedure for the operation, qualification, and maintenance of the Binder vacuum ovens.','This SOP applies to all personnel operating the Binder drying ovens at Amneal Ireland.','1. All QC/ARD personnel must follow the procedure.\n2. The Laboratory Manager ensures adherence to the procedure.\n3. Report any equipment problems to the Laboratory Manager.\n4. Ensure all users are trained on the current SOP revision.','QC-018: 30-Sep-2016 - First Issued\nQC-018A: 17-Sep-2019 - Updated SOP to new logo and removed reference to Appendix.\nQC-018B: 15-Oct-2020 - Removed reference to VD 23, updated vacuum instructions, and made grammatical amendments.','FM-QC-019: Binder Oven Usage Logbook\nBinder APT.line[TM] VD Vacuum Drying Oven Operating Manual'),(49,'QC-019C','INTEGRATION OF CHROMATOGRAMS IN THE QC/ARD LABORATORY','QC-019C Integration of Chromatograms in the QC-ARD Laboratory.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','David Ryan, QC/ARD','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD, Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2021-11-17','2023-10-02','QC-019B','1. Peak marking based on RT and RRT.\n2. Peak marking based on Blank/Placebo.\n3. Identification of Peak by Spike Solution.\n4. Procedure for Integration of Peaks in a Chromatogram.\n5. General Procedure for integration parameters.\n6. Manual integration requires approval from the Laboratory Manager.','Chromatogram: Graphical representation of detector response vs time.\nPeak: Portion of chromatographic recording when a component is eluted.\nIntegration: Process of calculating peak areas.\nBaseline: Line representing detector signal when only mobile phase is passing.\nBaseline noise: Irregular variations in the baseline.\nValley: Lowest point between two unresolved peaks.\nParent Peak: Larger of a pair of partially resolved peaks.\nRider Peak: Smaller of a pair of partially resolved peaks.\nResolved Peak: Peak with resolution ≥ 2.0.\nPartially resolved peak: Peak with resolution < 2.0.\nPeak separation: Deriving areas of partially resolved peaks.\nPeak Measurement: Integration involving peak start, apex, and end.\nPeak Area: Area under the curve.\nRetention time (RT): Time for elution of a component.\nRelative retention time (RRT): Ratio of RT of component to reference component.\nDrift and Hump: Baseline shift due to mobile phase or instrumental factors.\nKnown peak: Peak with known origin.\nUnknown peak: Peak with unknown origin.\nPlacebo: Pharmaceutical preparation without active ingredient.\nBlank: Diluent/solvent used for injection.\nPlacebo peak: Peak from placebo portion.\nBlank peak: Peak from blank solution.\nHighest unknown peak: Largest unknown peak.\nSystem suitability: Ensures chromatographic system performance.\nSignal-to-noise ratio: Determines sensitivity of the method.\nQC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nLimit of Quantitation (LOQ): Lowest quantifiable concentration.\nLimit of Detection (LOD): Lowest detectable concentration.\nDisregard Limit: Peaks below this limit are disregarded.\nScientifically correct integration: Integration visually correct at minimum zoom level.','To provide a systematic approach to peak identification and integration for chromatograms.','This procedure is applicable for all chromatograms generated during analysis performed by QC/ARD, Amneal Ireland.','1. Laboratory personnel shall comply with the requirements of this procedure.\n2. Laboratory personnel must ensure they are trained to the current version.\n3. Laboratory Manager or designee ensures adherence to the procedure.\n4. Laboratory Manager or designee ensures all personnel are appropriately trained.','QC-019: 03-Oct-2016 - First Issued.\nQC-019A: 02-Oct-2019 - Updated SOP to new format, added definitions, and revised integration procedures.\nQC-019B: 08-Nov-2019 - Corrected spelling errors and included diagrams.\nQC-019C: 17-Nov-2021 - Updated manual integration approval process.','USP\nEDQM- Helpdesk - 04- European Pharmacopoeia & International Harmonisation'),(50,'QC-020H','EVALUATION OF SYSTEM SUITABILITY DATA FOR HPLC, GC AND UV-VIS APPLICATIONS','QC-020H Evaluation of SS Data for HPLC, GC & UV-VIS App.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Aliah Gulati, QC/ARD','David Ryan, QC/ARD, Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD','Lorraine Henry, QA','2022-12-13','2025-03-14','QC-020G','1. General requirements for system suitability.\n2. Data acquisition and integration procedures.\n3. System suitability for HPLC, GC, and UV-Vis.\n4. Handling system suitability failures.\n5. Chromatographic adjustments to achieve system suitability.','HPLC: High Performance Liquid Chromatography.\nGC: Gas Chromatography.\nUV-Vis: Ultra-Violet-Visible.\nIdeal Chromatography: Meets predefined system suitability requirements.\nPoor Chromatography: Identified by symptoms like noisy baseline, shift in retention time, or asymmetric peaks.\nNMT: Not More Than.\nNLT: Not Less Than.\nStandard: Reference standard solution used for system suitability and calibration.\nSystem Suitability: Tests to verify analytical system performance.\nRelative Retention Time (RRT): Retention time of a component relative to a reference peak.\nCapacity Factor (k’): Measure of peak location relative to void volume.\nResolution (R): Measure of separation between two adjacent peaks.\nTailing factor (T): Measure of peak symmetry.\nRelative Standard Deviation (RSD): Measure of reproducibility.\nTheoretical Plates/Column Efficiency: Measure of column performance.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nAPI: Active Pharmaceutical Ingredient.\nIncident: Unexpected event during laboratory operations.\nApproved Document: Data entry documents approved for recording analytical method execution.','To provide general procedures for the conduct of HPLC, GC, and UV-Vis analysis and describe the process for evaluating system suitability data.','This SOP applies to personnel in the QC/ARD laboratory at Amneal Ireland and is supplementary to analytical test methods.','1. QC/ARD personnel must follow this procedure.\n2. QC/ARD personnel must ensure they are trained on the current revision.\n3. QC/ARD Manager (or designee) ensures adherence to the procedure.','QC-020: 30-Sep-2016 - First Issued.\nQC-020A: 27-Jun-2018 - Updated definitions and procedures.\nQC-020B: 07-Aug-2018 - Added new definitions and instructions.\nQC-020C: 20-Jun-2019 - Updated title, definitions, and procedures.\nQC-020D: 13-Aug-2020 - Updated diluent injection instructions.\nQC-020E: 25-Sep-2020 - Updated handling of extraneous peaks.\nQC-020F: 02-Feb-2022 - Updated flowchart and references.\nQC-020G: 15-Jun-2022 - Updated standard injection sequence and system suitability procedures.\nQC-020H: 13-Dec-2022 - Updated standard correlation calculation and bracketing standard criteria.','SOP QC-019: Integration of chromatograms in the QC/ARD Laboratories.\nSOP QC-012: Chromatographic Column Management.\nUnited States Pharmacopeia.\nP_CQCM-1026: Evaluation of Chromatographic and System Suitability Data for HPLC, UPLC, and GC Applications.\nSOP QM-010: Investigation System.\nFM-QC-008: Column receipt and usage logbook.\nSOP QC-086: Handling of Laboratory Incident in the QC/ARD and Microbiology Laboratories.\nSOP QC-001: Investigation of Out of Specification (OOS) Laboratory Results.\nFM-QC-224: Laboratory Incident Report.\nSOP QC-085: Investigation of Atypical Results in the QC Laboratory.\nGQS_0038: Investigation of Unexpected Peaks in Chromatographic Analysis.'),(51,'QC-021B','OPERATION OF EMPOWER SOFTWARE','QC-021B Operation of Empower Software.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Brigid Hayes, QC/ARD','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD, Paul O\'Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2020-01-01','2023-01-01','QC-021A','To provide a systematic approach for the routine operation of Empower Software.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nProject: A user defined collection of data including but not limited to methods, results, view filters, custom fields and raw data.\nMethod: An instruction to Empower to perform a task.\nInstrument Method: Instructions to control a chromatographic instrument and collect data.\nProcessing Method: Instructions including but not limited to the following actions: identify peaks, integrate, calculate results, perform system suitability.\nReport Method: Instructions specifying the content and format of chromatographic reports including but not limited to chromatograms, calibration curves, numerical data.\nMethod Set: Collection of methods that must contain the instrument method. May also contain processing method, report method and export method.\nSample Set Method: A set of instructions that defines what samples will be run and how. Information includes but is not limited to vial position, sample name, injection volume.\nSample Set: A set of data acquired after running a sample set method.\nResult Set: A bound set of results generated from processing selected sample sets.','To provide a systematic approach for the routine operation of Empower Software.','This procedure applies to the Quality Control and Analytical Research & Development (QC/ARD) Laboratory at Amneal, Ireland.','The QC/ARD personnel are responsible for complying with the requirements of this procedure.\nLaboratory manager or designee shall be responsible to ensure that the steps outlined in this procedure are followed.\nLaboratory manager or designee must ensure that all personnel performing the steps outlined in this procedure are appropriately trained.','Revision: QC-021, Date: 30-Sep-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued\nRevision: QC-021A, Date: 17-May-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-19-010, Reason: Header: New Amneal logo added. New Points added: 5.3.5 Creating an Instrument Method (IM) 5.3.5.8 Instrument Methods shall be created by a “Superuser”. The Superuser should print and sign / date the created Instrument Method and pass to the Laboratory Manger or designee for review. 5.3.5.9 Once the Instrument Method is reviewed and signed / dated by the Laboratory Manger or designee the Instrument Method should be locked by the Superuser from “Chemist” user group. The reviewed Instrument should be stored in a designated folder in the QC/ARD Laboratory. 5.3.5.10 Once locked the Instrument Method can be used for routine use. Note: Instrument methods for Headspace Gas Chromatography cannot be locked as the number of vials require updating for each sample set. Instrument methods for Headspace Gas Chromatography will be printed by the analysts and submitted as part of the chromatographic data pack for review. The instrument method will be reviewed by the data reviewer during the review process. 5.3.6: Creating a Method Set 5.3.6.7 Method Sets shall be created by the “Super User”. The Superuser should print and sign/date the created Method Set and pass to the Laboratory Manger or designee for review. 5.3.6.8 Once the Method Set is reviewed and signed / dated by the Laboratory Manger or designee the Method Set should be locked by a Superuser from “Chemist” user group. The reviewed Method Set should be stored in a designated folder in the QC/ARD Laboratory. 5.3.6.9 Once locked the Method Set can be used for routine use. 5.3.7 Creating Report Method 5.3.7.1 Report Methods shall be created for each analytical procedure in the QC/ARD Laboratory. Report Methods may be created by a Superuser or a Chemist. The Superuser or Chemist should print the created Report Method and pass to the Laboratory Manger or designee for review. 5.3.7.2 Report Methods shall include the following • Sample Set • Processing Method • Component Summary Report • Chromatogram of all injections in the relevant Sample Set A separate report Method should be created for System Suitability. Report Methods must contain all critical information as per the relevant analytical procedure 5.3.7.3 Once the Report Method is reviewed by the Laboratory Manger or designee the Report Methods should be locked by a Superuser from the “Chemist” group. 5.3.7.4 Once locked Report Methods can be used for routine use in the QC/ARD laboratory. Correct typographical error in numbering for section 5.1.1\nRevision: QC-021B, Date: 2020-01-01, CCF No.: AI-CC-19-080, Reason: Section 6.0 updated to reflect new SOP Title for SOP QC-020','SOP: QC-019 Integration of Chromatograms in the QC/ARD Laboratory\nSOP: QC-020 Evaluation of System Suitability Data for HPLC, GC and UV-Vis Applications\nSOP: QC-025 Operation and Maintenance of HPLC System\nSOP: QC-030 Operation and Maintenance of GC System'),(52,'QC-022E','CONTROL OF LABORATORY INSTRUMENTS','QC-022E Control of Laboratory Instruments.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','David Ryan, QC/ARD','Katherine Russell, QC/ARD, Paul O\'Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2020-01-01','2023-01-01','QC-022D','To describe the receipt, labelling, qualification, maintenance, re-qualification, re-validation, calibration and repair of instruments/equipment in the Quality Control/Analytical R&D (QC/ARD) and Microbiology Laboratory.','AIQ: Analytical Instrument Qualification.\nIQ: Installation Qualification.\nOQ: Operational Qualification.\nPQ: Performance Qualification.\nRQ: Re-qualification.\nRV: Re-validation.\nPM: Preventive Maintenance.\nCalibration: Set of operations that establish the relationship between values indicated by a measuring instrument and the corresponding values realised by standards.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nSOP: Standard Operating Procedure.\nGMP: Good Manufacturing Practice.\nPPE: Personal Protective Equipment.\nQC/ARD-Micro: Quality Control/ Analytical Research & Development and Micro.\nCOTS: Commercial off the Shelf.\nSDS: Safety Data Sheets.\nQM: Quality Management.\nQA: Quality Assurance.\nIT: Information Technology.\nVMP: Validation Master Plan.\nNIST: National Institute of Standards and Technology.\nNSAI: National Standards Authority of Ireland.\nNPL: National Physics Laboratory.\nCSV: Computer Systems Validation.','To describe the receipt, labelling, qualification, maintenance, re-qualification, re-validation, calibration and repair of instruments/equipment in the Quality Control/Analytical R&D (QC/ARD) and Microbiology Laboratory.','This procedure applies to all instruments/equipment in the QC/ARD Laboratories.','Laboratory personnel shall comply with the requirements of this procedure.\nLaboratory personnel must ensure that they are trained to the current version of this procedure.\nLaboratory Manager or designee shall be responsible for ensuring that the steps outlined in this procedure are followed.\nThe Laboratory Manager or designee must ensure that all personnel performing the steps outlined in this procedure are appropriately trained.\nThe Laboratory Manager or designee is responsible for establishing and implementing the laboratory instrument calibration and preventive maintenance schedule.\nThe Laboratory Manager or designee shall ensure that all activities are documented as per QM-004 (Good Documentation Practices).\nThe Laboratory Manager or designee shall ensure that all contract maintenance providers meet the requirements of SOP QA-002 (Contract Service Provider Management).\nIt is the responsibility of all persons performing calibrations/PM/re-validation/re-qualification work to adhere to all safety signs, notices and guidelines.','Revision: QC-022, Date: 03-Oct-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First issued.\nRevision: QC-022A, Date: 29-Mar-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-014, Reason: Added equipment, re-qualification and re-validation to the Purpose section 1.1. Updated section 2.1 to include equipment. Minor grammatical corrections to section 3. Added responsibilities in section 3 for the Laboratory Manager or designee to ensure all activities are documented as per SOP QM-004, manage spare parts ordering, ensure all contractors meet SOP QA-002 (Contract Service Provider Management). Added responsibilities for persons performing work to adhere to safety signs, wear correct PPE, avoid hot surfaces, have adequate lighting, electrical shocks etc. Added acronyms PM, QC/ARD, SOP, GMP, COTS, SDS, QM, QA, IT, VMP, NIST, NSAI, and NPL to Definitions section 4. Section 4.2 has changed definition to “IQ: Installation Qualification: The documented verification that the facilities, systems, instruments and equipment as installed or modified, comply with the approved design and the manufacturer’s recommendations.” to align with VA-002. Section 4.3 has changed definition to “OQ: Operational Qualification: The documented verification that the facilities, systems, instruments and equipment as installed or modified, perform as intended throughout the anticipated operating ranges.” To align with VA-002. Added definition for Re-validation to Section 4.6. Section 5.1 Added Equipment for clarification. Section 5.1 Added “New instruments shall be assessed and introduced as per QM-013, “Change Control System” if applicable”. Section 5.1 Added “Any instrument that exists on site but has not been previously qualified shall be assessed prior to qualification of this instrument.” Section 5.1.6, responsibility changed to QC/ARD. Added “Record IQ as per VA-002, Appendix IV, “Protocol template for Installation Qualification (IQ).” To Section 5.2.4. Removed reference to presumed instruments in Section 5.2.4. Added “Any re-qualification or re-calibration activities required of the instrument will be managed under the associated Change Control as per this procedure” to Section 5.2.9. Added clarification on the instruments that require qualification following a move to Section 5.2.9. Section 5.5 has been changed from “Instrument Calibration and Preventative Maintenance” to “Instrument Calibration”. Sections 5.5 and 5.5.4 have been amended to reference section 5.4 for categorisation, and SOP QM-007 only for calibration. Section 5.5.2 has been moved to section 5.6.1. Section 5.5.3 is removed as already stated in 3.5. Section 5.5.5 is now covered in section 5.6.10. Section 5.5.6 is re-worded and moved to 5.6.14. Section 5.5.7 is moved to 5.6.11. Section 5.5.8 referencing SOP QM-007 (Calibration Policy) is removed as this SOP does not cover PMs. Section 5.6 amended from ‘Repair of Instruments’ to ‘Instrument PM’ (‘Repair of Instruments’ is now section 5.9). Section 5.6 now covers purpose of PM, forms to be used for annual and monthly PM schedules, reference instruments used, persons qualified to perform PMs, instrument classification, recording and documentation storage, use of labels etc. New section 5.7 added; Maintenance Schedule. New section 5.8 added; Periodic Re-qualification /Re-validation. References expanded to Preventative Maintenance Annual Schedule (FM-QC-123), Preventative Maintenance Monthly Schedule (FM-QC-124), Instrument PM Record – Category A Instruments (FM-QC-125), QM-004, Good Documentation Practices, QA-002, Contract Service Provider Management, QM-010, Investigation System, MF-008, Labelling of Material, Product, Room and Equipment, FM-QM-020, Calibration label, FM-MF-012, Equipment Out of Service/ON HOLD’ label. Update of Appendix II (Instrument Categorisation (FM-QC-027)) to include new instrumentation. Appendix VI and VII added as templates for annual and monthly PM schedules. Appendix VIII added (Instrument PM Record – Category A Instrument). Appendix II updated to include other instrument types. Editorial changes.\nRevision: QC-022B, Date: 18-Sep-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-064, AI-CC-18-097, Reason: Section 5.1.2; replaced ‘Out of Use’ label FM-QC-026 with ‘Out of Use’ label FM-QM-112 (SOP QM-007 Calibration Policy). Section 5.2.13; PM label FM-QC-028 replaced by PM label FM-MF-040, SOP MF-008 Labelling of Material, Product, Room and Equipment. Section 5.6.2 Appendix IV amended to Appendix VI and Appendix V amended to VII to correct typographical errors. Section 5.6.7 Appendix VI amended to Appendix VIII to correct typographical error. Section 5.6.12; replaced ‘Out of Use’ label FM-MF-012 with ‘Out of Use’ label FM-QM-112 (SOP QM-007 Calibration Policy). Section 5.6.13; replaced ‘Equipment Out of Service’/On Hold’ label with ‘Out of Use’ label FM-QM-112, SOP QM-007, Calibration Policy. Changed PM status label from FM-QC-028 to FM-MF-040. Section 5.9.3; replaced ‘Out of Use’ label FM-QC-026 with ‘Out of Use’ label FM-QM-112, SOP QM-007, Calibration Policy. Removed Appendices I and III as no longer required following above changes (see points 1 and 2). Reference to FM-QM-112 Out of Use label, SOP QM-007 added. Addition of FM-MF-040 (Preventative Maintenance Status label) and FM-QM-112 (Out of Use label) to References section, points 6.18 and 6.19 respectively. General editorial changes. Updated Appendix II to include additional new instruments in QC/ARD.\nRevision: QC-022C, Date: 15-Nov-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-125, Reason: Corrected error in the naming of the change controls listed for revision QC-022B. Amended Appendix VII for typographical errors; Page 2 footer in Appendix VII amended from FM-QC-123 to FM-QC-124. Page 2 heading in Appendix VII amended from Appendix VI to Appendix VII.\nRevision: QC-022D, Date: 08-Feb-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-064, Reason: Update procedure to new template. Update Logo in header. Section 1.1 Include “and Microbiology”. Section 2.1 Change Laboratory to Laboratories. Section 4.13 Include “Micro”. Section 4.23 Include Definition for CSV. Section 5.2 Change Laboratory to Laboratories. Section 5.9.2 Include numbering format for Instrument Repair Requests. Section 5.9.9, Addition of “For Microbiology Equipment all repair activities must be documented in the instrument’s usage logbook”. Section 6.17, Include “SOP QM-007”. Update FM-QC-027 to new form template and put titles of form in body of the form as header is removed. Update FM-QC-027 to include new logo in header. Update FM-QC-027 to include a Hotplate. Remove Appendix numbers throughout the document and replace with form number where applicable. Add new point under section 5.5.2 – “In the event that a planned Calibration activity is unable to be completed within it’s defined Calibration schedule window QC/ARD / QA Val and QA can assess impact, if any, and document decision on instrument PM status thereafter. An “Out of Use” label will be applied to the instrument prior to the calibration activity exceeding it’s defined due date pending the outcome of the assessment. The assessment will be documented and stored with the relevant calibration schedule documentation.” Updated section 5.6.2 to remove requirement to initiate an investigation per QM-010 if a planned preventative maintenance task is completed after the allowable due date. Update section 5.6.2 to include “In the event that a planned preventative maintenance activity is unable to be completed within it’s defined PM schedule window QC/ARD / QA Val and QA to assess impact, if any, and document decision on instrument PM status thereafter. An “Out of Use” label will be applied to the instrument prior to the PM activity exceeding it’s defined PM due date (including tolerance where applicable) pending the outcome of the assessment. The assessment will be documented and stored with the relevant maintenance schedule documentation”. Updated form numbers FM-QC-029, FM-QC-030, FM-QC-123, FM-QC-124 and FM-QC-125 to new template and included new logo in header.','FM-QC-027 : Instrument Categorisation.\nFM-QC-029 : Instrument Repair Request.\nFM-QC-030 : Instrument Repair Record Log.\nFM-QC-123 : Preventative Maintenance Annual Schedule.\nFM-QC-124 : Preventative Maintenance Monthly Schedule.\nFM-QC-125 : Instrument PM Record – Category A Instruments.\nQA-005 : Assigning Equipment Identification Number.\nVA-002 : Qualification Procedure.\nQM-007 : Calibration Policy.\nQM-013 : Change Control.\nUSP <1058> Analytical Instrument Qualification.\nEudralex Chapter 6 and Annex 15.\nQM-004 : Good Documentation Practices.\nQA-002 : Contract Service Provider Management.\nQM-010 : Investigation System.\nMF-008 : Labelling of Material, Product, Room and Equipment.\nFM-QM-020 : Calibration label (SOP QM-007).\nFM-QM-112 : OUT OF USE label (SOP QM-007).\nFM-MF-040 : Preventative Maintenance Status label.'),(53,'QC-023A','OPERATION AND CALIBRATION OF VWR 609-0185 STOPWATCHES','QC-023A Operation and Calibration of VWR 609-0185 Stopwatches.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Brigid Hayes, QC/ARD','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2017-12-01','2023-11-01','QC-023','The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and calibration of the VWR 609-0185 stopwatches.','QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and calibration of the VWR 609-0185 stopwatches.','The scope is limited to the use of the timers by the QC/ARD Department in Amneal Ireland.','It is the responsibility of all personnel within QC/ARD to adhere to the requirements outlined in this procedure.\nAll QC/ARD personnel must ensure that they are trained on the current revision of the SOP.\nIt is the responsibility of the Laboratory Manager (or designee) to ensure that the SOP is followed by all QC/ARD personnel.\nIt is the responsibility of the QC Manager (or designee) to ensure that all QC/ARD personnel are trained on the current revision of the SOP.','Revision: QC-023, Date: 30-Sep-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued.\nRevision: QC-023A, Date: 2017-12-01, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Update SOP logo and removed reference to Appendix throughout.','FM-QC-021 : Calibration Log for Stopwatches.'),(54,'QC-024C','OPERATION AND MONITORING OF LIEBHERR FRIDGE IN THE QC/ARD LABORATORY','QC-024C Op & Monitoring of LIEBHERR Fridge in QC-ARD Lab.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','David Ryan, QC/ARD','Paul O\'Mahony, QC/ARD, Ashok Gulati, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2021-07-01','2024-07-01','QC-024B','The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and monitoring of the Liebherr fridge.','QC/ARD: Quality Control/ Analytical Research & Development.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','The purpose of this SOP is to define the procedure for the operation and monitoring of the Liebherr fridge.','The scope is limited to fridges used by the QC/ARD Department in Amneal Ireland.','It is the responsibility of all personnel within QC/ARD to adhere to the requirements outlined in this procedure.\nAll QC/ARD personnel must ensure that they are trained on the current revision of the SOP.\nIt is the responsibility of the Laboratory Manager (or designee) to ensure that the SOP is followed by all QC/ARD personnel.\nIt is the responsibility of the Laboratory Manager (or designee) to ensure that all QC/ARD personnel are trained on the current revision of the SOP.','Revision: QC-024, Date: 17-Jan-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued.\nRevision: QC-024A, Date: 26-Aug-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated SOP to introduce new Amneal Logo. Formatted header to remove preparers name. Section 5.3 - Updated 5.3.5 to remove Fridge Contents logbook, Appendix 1 (FM-QC-024) and to include Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-015). Updated 5.3.7 to remove Fridge Contents logbook, Appendix 1 (FM-QC-024) and to include Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-016). Added 5.3.8 and 5.3.9. Section 5.4 - Update 5.4.1 to include daily alarm check and instruction that data logger to be downloaded in the event of an alarm being encountered. Update 5.4.2 to clarify that the temperature of the fridge will be recorded every 10 minutes. Update 5.4.3 to state that the data logger will be placed in a representative location within the fridge. Section 5.4.4 – include instruction stating that the temperature data from the data logger will be downloaded on a monthly basis and that calibration cert for data logger will be saved also. Remove section 5.4.4. Add section 5.4.5 to state that all deviations from acceptance criteria should be recorded in FM-QC-025. Section 5.5 - Add clarification that maintenance is documented in FM-QC-025 in point 5.5.5. Section 5.6 - Add section in relation to use of data loggers. References Section - Remove appendix references. Remove reference to FM-QC-024 and SOP-035. Insert references to FM-QC-015 and FM-QC-016.\nRevision: QC-024B, Date: 16-Jul-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-051, Reason: Section 5.3.5 updated to All standards stored in the fridge must be recorded in the Incoming Reference Standards Logbook (FM-QC-015). Section 5.3.6 updated to All items stored in the fridge must be securely sealed and clearly labelled. Section 5.3.8 and 5.3.9 was removed. Section 5.5.1 Prior to performing any maintenance remove samples / standards from the fridge. Complete the clean within a maximum period of 30 minutes to minimise the time that standards are outside of the refrigerated conditions. Section 5.5.2 updated to Clean the inside, equipment and outer walls with lukewarm water and a small amount of detergent. Do not use abrasive or acidic cleaners or chemical solvents. Note: Fridge Clean will be performed annually prior the Fridge Calibration.\nRevision: QC-024C, Date: 2021-07-01, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-049, Reason: Section 5.2 – updated instruction as per new Liebherr Fridge, AI-QC-136. Section 5.4 – added new section to describe how to operate the maximum/minimum thermometer. Section 5.5, monitoring the temperature moved from section 5.4. Section 5.5.1 - added instruction for the monitoring of the fridge using the minimum and maximum thermometer “the minimum and maximum temperatures shall be checked as per section 5.4.5 and 5.4.6. The minimum and maximum temperatures shall be recorded along with the date/time of the minimum and maximum temperatures. Section 5.5.2 - Instruction added on how to deal with excursions of temperature outside the 2°C - 8°C range. Removed section 5.6, use of temperate data loggers. Section 6.4, added reference to IT-014. Updated FM-QC-025 to include new process for monitoring refrigerator temperatures with minimum/maximum thermometer.','FM-QC-025 : Fridge Temperature Logbook.\nFM-QC-016 : Reference Standards Monthly Review Log.\nFM-QC-015 : Incoming Reference Standards Logbook.\nIT-014 : Synchronisation of time for standalone equipment/instrument.'),(55,'xxxx','Travel and Expense Policy','Amneal Ireland Travel Expense Policy.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,'Gearoid McDermott','2023-09-27',NULL,NULL,'Employees must book travel through Heffernan Travel. Corporate credit cards are issued to frequent travelers. Reimbursement for business-related expenses is provided. Non-compliance may result in delayed or denied reimbursement or termination. Airline reservations should be made at least 2 weeks in advance. Economy class for UK and Europe, Business class for flights over 10 hours. Rental cars should be intermediate size. Use of personal cars is reimbursable at 39.86 cents/km. Lodging and meals are reimbursable within limits. Travel insurance is provided by the company.',NULL,'To provide guidelines and procedures for employees who travel and incur business-related expenses.','Applies to all Amneal Ireland employees and contractors travelling on Amneal Ireland related business.','Employees must comply with the policy. Managers must approve travel and expenses. Site Director must authorize travel and approve expense reports.',NULL,NULL),(56,'EMP-HANDBOOK-2022','Employee Handbook August 2022','Employee Handbook August 2022.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','HR Department','Management Team','Chirag Patel & Chintu Patel','2022-08-01','2023-08-01','Revision 14','Equal Opportunity, Conflict of Interest, Termination of Employment, Time & Attendance, Compensation & Benefits, Leave Provisions, Key Company Policies, Health & Safety, Code of Conduct','Equal Opportunity: Ensuring no discrimination based on gender, civil status, family status, sexual orientation, age, disability, race, religion, or membership of the Traveller community. Conflict of Interest: Avoiding activities that conflict with the company’s business interests. Termination of Employment: Procedures for termination and payment in lieu of notice. Time & Attendance: Policies on working hours, time off, and flexible working. Compensation & Benefits: Details on base pay, bonuses, and benefits. Leave Provisions: Policies on annual leave, sick leave, maternity leave, etc. Key Company Policies: Anti-discrimination, anti-harassment, and disciplinary policies. Health & Safety: Ensuring a safe workplace. Code of Conduct: Ethical guidelines for employees.','To provide employees with a comprehensive guide on company policies, procedures, and expectations to ensure a productive and compliant work environment.','All employees of Amneal Ireland Limited and Amneal EU Limited.','Employees: To adhere to the policies outlined in the handbook. Management: To enforce and ensure compliance with the policies. HR Department: To provide guidance and support on policy-related matters.','This handbook supersedes and replaces all previous handbooks, personnel policies, practices, and guidelines. Effective August 2022.','Employment Equality Acts 1988-2015, Equal Status Acts 2000-2018, Minimum Notice and Terms of Employment Act 1973-2005, Unfair Dismissals Act 1977-2005, Terms of Employment Information Act 1994-2012, Safety, Health and Welfare at Work Act 2005.'),(57,'HOLIDAY-SELL-SCHEME','Annual Leave Sell Scheme Policy','Holiday Sell Scheme.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','HR Department','Management Team','Chirag Patel & Chintu Patel',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Employees can sell up to 3 days/24 hours of unused Annual Leave. Requests must be submitted by 31 October each year. Payment is based on the employee’s hourly rate and can be paid through payroll or put towards an AVC.','Annual Leave: Paid time off granted to employees. AVC: Additional Voluntary Contribution to pension.','To allow employees to sell a portion of their unused Annual Leave for monetary value while ensuring compliance with the Organisation of Working Time Act.','All Amneal employees who have successfully completed their probationary period.','Employees: Submit requests to sell Annual Leave by the deadline. HR: Process requests and ensure compliance with the policy.','This policy introduces the Annual Leave Sell Scheme, allowing employees to sell up to 3 days of unused Annual Leave.','Organisation of Working Time Act, Working Time Regulations.'),(58,'IT-001B','DOMAIN SECURITY ADMINISTRATION','IT-001B Domain Security Administration.pdf','Michelle O\'Donoghue','Michelle O\'Donoghue','Mary White, QA','Kuldeep Josh, QA','2022-09-14','2024-09-15','IT-001A','1. Enforce unique user password with minimum seven characters.\n2. Password expiry every 90 Days.\n3. System lockout threshold for invalid login attempts is Three (3).\n4. Locked-out users are automatically unlocked after 7 minutes.\n5. Users are given a generic password for password resets and are prompted to change password at first logon.\n6. Desktop and laboratory computers have local administrator password managed by IT.\n7. Anti-Virus software scans for malicious code and content.\n8. Firewall configured to prevent unauthorized intrusion.\n9. VPN access available for remote users.','HOD: Head of Department\nIT: Information Technology\nLAN: Local Area Network\nQA: Quality Assurance\nSOP: Standard Operating Procedure\nVPN: Virtual Private Network','To provide instruction and guidance for the administration of the Amneal Ireland Limited local area network (LAN) and wide area network (WAN) security devices, application and general end-user practices.','The Amneal Ireland Limited LAN/WAN authorize users, security devices, applications, and network operating system active directory settings.','1. The Information Technology (IT) Manager or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\n2. It is the responsibility of Domain User and Instrument Operator to ensure login with his/her user id and logout after task completion.','IT-001 | 12-Jan-2016 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-001A | 05-May-2020 | AI-CC-18-140 | 1. Updated Amneal Logo and removed reference to Appendix\n2. Added FM-IT-053 to reference section.\n3. Removed FM-IT-001-00 from reference section.\n4. Form FM-IT-001-00 to be retired.\nIT-001B | 14-Sep-2022 | AI-CC-21-072 | 1. Add definitions section\n2. Add details for ServiceNow Self-Service Portal.\n3. Add Hiring Manager approval process\n4. Add detail for IT team /ServiceDesk to service the request.\n5. Added additional detail for usernames for employees with same name.','FM-IT-053 : Access & Disable Electronic System Request Form'),(59,'IT-002E','COMPUTER NETWORK ACCESS, HELPDESK AND TERMINATION','IT-002E Computer Network Access Helpdesk & Termination.pdf','Declan Ryan','Declan Ryan','Derek Russell, IT; Mary White, QA','Kuldeep Jones, QA',NULL,NULL,'IT-002D','1. Requesting Secure Folder Access or changing current User Access.\n2. Requests to Helpdesk.\n3. Terminating User Profile.\n4. Transfer of GxP data from original equipment to Secure Folder.\n5. Retention of data on secure folders.','IT: Information Technology.\nHOD: Head of Department.\nAll Amneal Ireland Employees: Full time permanent staff.\nAll Amneal Ireland non-Employees: Directly Supervised Contractor, contract agency person with the same duties as a permanent employee.\nAll Amneal Ireland Contractors: A contractor hired by another company who provide a regular service at Amneal, for example Cleaning Contractor.','This procedure outlines the guideline for providing new computer network access, helpdesk services and network access termination for the computer network.','This procedure applies to all employees requesting computer network access, helpdesk services and network access termination from the computer network at Amneal Ireland.','1. The Information Technology HOD or designee is responsible for the overall security of the Amneal Ireland computer network.\n2. IT team members who have administrator privileges are responsible for administering/managing security of the computer network and network folders.\n3. The respective HOD or designee is responsible for requesting network access for all new employees and requesting to revoke access for existing employees as required.\n4. The Human Resource HOD or designee is responsible for informing the IT department when an employee who has access to the computer network has been terminated or relieved from the services.\n5. The Head of QA or designee is responsible for approving access to the Quality Management folder/subfolders and secure network folders.','IT-002 | 12-Jan-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-002A | 21-Dec-2017 | AI-CC-17-107 | Updated purpose, scope, definitions, and procedures.\nIT-002B | 03-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-036 | Revised section 5.2 and added section 5.5.\nIT-002C | 29-Apr-2021 | AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-21-031 | Amneal Logo change, removed word ‘services’, replaced Department Head with HOD, and other revisions.\nIT-002D | 01-Jun-2021 | AI-CC-21-033 | Added ServiceNow portal details.\nIT-002E | [Date] | AI-CC-21-053, AIM-CC-21-009 | Returned Form FM-IT-027 into service and added MDI Functional Tester.','IT-001 : Domain Security Administration\nFM-IT-027 : Secure Folder Access Request form\nHR-001 : Employee Induction Process\nFM-HR-009 : Exiting Employee/Non-Employee/ Contractor Checklist'),(60,'IT-004E','DATA BACKUP, RESTORE PROCEDURE FOR SERVER SYSTEM','IT-004E Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System.pdf','Declan Ryan','Declan Ryan','Derek Russell, IT','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2023-11-01','2026-10-31','IT-004D','1. Backup Procedure for Acronis Backup for VMWare.\n2. Restore Procedure for Acronis Backup for VMWare.\n3. Backup schedule for Amneal Ireland Servers.\n4. Backup Storage of media.\n5. Retention of external hard drive backups for 3 months.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nData Backup: Making copies of data to restore the original after data loss.\nFull Backup: Complete backup of all software components.\nIncremental Backup: Copies only data changed since the last backup.\nDifferential Backup: Copies all data changed since the last full backup.\nSoftware Backup: Ensures latest and correct versions are available.\nBackup for VMWare: Complete copy of the VM server.\nBackup Interval: Frequency of backups.\nMedia: Means of storing electronic data.\nCD: Compact Disc.\nDVD: Digital Versatile Disk.\nVM: Virtual Machine.\nIT: Information Technology.\nGFS: Grandfather-Father-Son Clean-up Scheme.\nZIP: Archive file format.\nSNMP: Simple Networking Monitoring Protocol.\nFTP: File Transfer Protocol.\nIDF2: Integrated Distribution Frame 2.\nQC: Quality Control.\nRestore Procedure: Returns lost data to its original condition.\nHOD: Head of Department.\nVDMK: Virtual Machine Disk.\nESX: VMware ESXi.\nIP: Internet Protocol.\nURL: Uniform Resource Locator.\nNAS Box: Network Attached Storage Box.\nBMS: Building Management System.\nQEMS: Qualified Environmental Management System.\nLocal USB HD: Local Universal Serial Bus Hard Drive.\nFull Virtual: Restores entire virtual machine.','This procedure outlines the guidance to describe IT approach to backup and restore of the data for the server system.','This procedure applied to software applications, data and documents held in electronic format on the server system as per Table 1 Data Backup Schedule at Amneal Ireland.','1. The designated Systems Administrator or designee is responsible for ensuring the backup and restore procedure is followed.\n2. The HOD, Information Technology or designee is responsible for ensuring compliance to this procedure.','IT-004 | 17-Nov-2016 | -- | First Issued.\nIT-004A | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | Added details for Acronis Backup, NAS storage, and Onsite Fireproof Safe.\nIT-004B | 13-Dec-2018 | AIM-CC-18-031 | Added AMNLIECAESX04 link and details for HP Storage Works Tape Autoloader.\nIT-004C | 25-Feb-2020 | AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-19-146 | Updated definitions, added backup definitions, and updated server links.\nIT-004D | 05-Aug-2021 | AIM-CC-21-019 | Added Serialisation System (VMs) to Table 1.\nIT-004E | 01-Nov-2023 | CC-AMN-23-5881 | Updated NAS Box definition, backup and restore processes, and server assignments.','IT-009 : Preventative maintenance for IT systems\nIT-015 : Empower & Instrument Server Data Backup, Archival & Verification\nFM-IT-052 : IT Fireproof Safe Access Form'),(61,'IT-005A','PROCEDURE TO INSTALL AND CONFIGURE A NETWORK SWITCH','IT-005A Procedure to Install and Configure a Network Switch.pdf','Declan Ryan','Declan Ryan','Derek Russell, IT','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2022-02-01','2025-02-01','IT-005','1. Software Management: Verify correct IOS version for new switches.\n2. Generic commands for all switches: Default configuration, enable services, naming convention, management address, default gateway, console and VTY settings, MOTD banner, UDLD, logging, DNS, HTTP management, SNMP settings, NTP, VTP, VLAN configuration.\n3. Switch specific commands: Access switch, server switch, distribution switch, collapsed core/distribution switch, core switch.\n4. Example configuration: Basic switch configuration example.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nDNS: Domain Naming System.\nHTTP: HyperText Transfer Protocol.\nHSRP: Hot Standby Routing Protocol.\nMOTD: Message Of The Day.\nNTP: Network Time Protocol.\nSNMP: Simple Network Management Protocol.\nUDLD: Unidirectional Link Detection.\nVLAN: Virtual Local Area Network.\nVTP: VLAN Trucking Protocol.\nIOS: Cisco’s Internetwork Operating System.','The purpose of this procedure is to provide the standards and instructions to execute a correct and complete installation and functional verification of switches within the Amneal Ireland network.','This procedure applies to all people involved in the installation of network switches running IOS operating system within the Amneal Ireland network.','1. The Information Technology (IT) Manager or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\n2. It is the responsibility of personnel involved in the configuration of Network Switches at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-005 | 26-Feb-2019 | -- | First Issued.\nIT-005A | 01-Feb-2022 | -- | Updated procedure for new installations and configurations.',NULL),(62,'IT-006B','PROCEDURE TO INSTALL AND CONFIGURE A WINDOWS SERVER','IT-006B Procedure To Install And Configure A windows Server.pdf','Anton Dempsey','Anton Dempsey','Derek Russell, Declan Ryan','Kuddeep Joshi','2022-10-25','2022-10-25','IT-006A','1. VMware Setup\n2. Virtual Machines (VM) Setup\n3. Windows Operating System (O.S) Setup\n4. Add to Domain\n5. Anti-Virus Setup\n6. SQL Installation\n7. Installing and Configuring a Windows Server on VxRail Infrastructure','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nISO: Short for ISO9660, the name of the standard specification for CDs\nUSB: Universal Serial Bus. Port available on computers.\nCD/DVD: Compact Disk/Digital Versatile Disc.\nVM: Virtual Machine','To provide instruction and guidance for the installation and configuration of a Windows Server at Amneal Ireland.','The Windows Servers in operation at Amneal Ireland','The Information Technology (IT) HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the building of Windows Servers at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-006 | 26-Feb-2019 | -- | First Issued\nIT-006A | 21-Feb-2022 | AI-CC-18-140 | SOP updated to new Amneal Logo\nIT-006B | CC-ACM-2000 | CC-AMN-22-4156 | 1. Added “VM: Virtual Machine” to section 4.0 Definitions 2. Updated Section 5.5 Anti-Virus Setup for Crowdstrike on VMs. 3. Added Section 5.7 Installing and Configuring a Windows Server for new VxRail Infrastructure','21CFR Part 11: Electronic Record and Electronic Signature Rule'),(63,'IT-007C','PROCEDURE TO INSTALL BMS APPLICATION SOFTWARE','IT-007C Procedure to Install BMS Application Software.pdf','Oliver Lynch','Oliver Lynch','Declan Ryan, Mark Smyth','Kuldeep Joshi','2024-07-25','2027-07-24','IT-007B','1. Tridium Niagara Supervisor Application Installation','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland\nHOD: Head of Department','To provide instruction and guidance for the installation of BMS Application Software at Amneal Ireland.','The BMS System in operation at Amneal Ireland.','The Information Technology (IT) HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the building of BMS System at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-007 | 26-Feb-2019 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-007A | 21-Feb-2022 | AI-CC-18-140 | SOP updated to new Amneal Logo\nIT-007B | 07-Mar-2022 | CC-AMN-22-1017 | Updated questionnaire onto correct template FM-QM-011.\nIT-007C | √5 ~ √k ~ 2√2 l | CC-AMN-24-3188 | 2.1 Replace ‘Windows Server’ with ‘System’ 3.2 Replace ‘Windows Server’ with ‘System’ 5.1 Replaced ‘Tridium AX’ with ‘Tridium Niagara’. 5.1.1 Added Niagara to Tridium Niagara. General editorial changes.','21CFR Part 11: Electronic Record and Electronic Signature Rule'),(64,'IT-008A','PROCEDURE TO INSTALL QEMS APPLICATION SOFTWARE','IT-008A Procedure To Install QEMS Application Software.pdf','Declan Ryan','Declan Ryan','Declan Ryan, Mark Smyth','Kuldeep Joshi','2022-02-09',NULL,NULL,'1. Trend Application Installation','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To provide instruction and guidance for the installation of QEMS Application Software at Amneal Ireland.','The QEMS Windows Server in operation at Amneal Ireland.','The Information Technology (IT) Manager or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the building of BMS Windows Server at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-008 | 26-Feb-2019 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-008A | ∂1-ℓ̲2 - ∂̲3 | AI-CC-18-140 | SOP updated to new Amneal Logo','21CFR Part 11: Electronic Record and Electronic Signature Rule'),(65,'IT-009D','PREVENTIVE MAINTENANCE FOR IT SYSTEMS','IT-009D Preventative Maintenance for IT Systems.pdf','Anton Dempsey, Aaron Dempsey','Anton Dempsey, Aaron Dempsey','Derek Russell, Declan Ryan','Kuldeep Joshi','2021-07-29',NULL,'IT-009C','1. General IT System Requirements\n2. Quarterly Maintenance Activities\n3. Review of Application Event Logs\n4. Backup Script Checks\n5. Security Log Reviews\n6. Access Control List Reviews\n7. Database Counters Review\n8. Database and OS Defragmentation\n9. Backup and Restore Testing\n10. Server Reboot and Service Restart','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland\nBusiness Owner: An individual who owns the relationship between the system, business process and data, ensures the system is maintained in a compliant state including providing adequate resources, and explains the system and business processes to auditors.\nDomain: Collection of workstations or user accounts in a Windows Server environment.\nDNS: Domain Name System\nDHCP: Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol.\nIT Application Owner: An individual responsible for managing the development / implementation, and/or operation of the system from a technical perspective and supervising the system upgrade. The individual who can answer questions relating to technical or business needs of the system. Provides input for the requirements and the communication planning.\nNAS: Network Attached Storage devices used to backup server data.\nSIEM: Security Information and Event Management.\nMDI: Metered-Dose Inhaler.','This procedure will outline the process for the maintenance activities that are required for IT systems at Amneal Ireland.','In Scope:\n1. Routine maintenance activities that are required to ensure that the IT system applications are running as expected.\n2. Quarterly checks on the IT systems to ensure optimum performance, backup and restore of servers.\n3. Hardware associated with backup and restore (tape drives & NAS boxes).\nOut of Scope:\n1. Maintenance of peripheral hardware such as label printers, scanners, client PCs etc.\n2. Maintenance of stand-alone laboratory and production hardware.','The Information Technology HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the preventive maintenance activities at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-009 | 20-Oct-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-009A | 16-Mar-2017 | AI-CC-17-010 | Sections 2.1.2, 5.2, 5.1.2, 5.1.3, 5.1.4 and 5.1.7 change the word “periodic” to the word “Quarterly”.\nIT009B | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | 1. Additional Row added to table in Section 2.1.3 with description: Maximo – Maintenance Schedule System.\n2. Editorial changes in section 6 – References.\nIT009C | 06-May-2021 | AI-CC-18-140 | AI-CC-21-032 | Annual Logo change\n2.1.3 Added RF-Smart and SCADA\n3.1 Replaced (IT) Manager with HOD\n5.1.2 Replace Appendix I with Form\n5.2.2 Add ‘completed successfully’\n5.2.3 Added details on Event Viewer, SIEM and Falcon Crowdstrike.\n5.2.6 Added details on Defragment and Optimize Drives.\n5.2.7 Added ‘SOP’\n6.1 Replaced Appendix I with FM-IT-004\nIT009D | 06-Aug-2021 | AIM-CC-21-019 | 2.1.3 Table 1: Added MDI Packaging Line\n4.9 Added MDI: Metered-Dose Inhaler.','FM-IT-004: IT Preventive Maintenance Recording Form\nIT-004: Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System\nQM-004: Good Documentation Practice'),(66,'IT-010C','PERFORMANCE MONITORING FOR IT SYSTEMS','IT-010C Performance Monitoring for IT Systems.pdf','Derek Russell','Derek Russell','Declan Ryan, Aaron Dempsey','Kuldeep Joshi','2021-05-04',NULL,'IT-010B','1. General IT System Requirements\n2. Solarwinds Network Performance Monitor Configuration\n3. Network Switch and Server Alerts\n4. Node and Volume Thresholds\n5. Administrator Accounts and Email Recipients Configuration\n6. Incident Logging and Impact Assessment\n7. Performance Monitor Usage in Case of Solarwinds Failure','Business Owner: An individual who owns the relationship between the system, business process and data, ensures the system is maintained in a compliant state including providing adequate resources, and explains the system and business processes to auditors.\nIT Application Owner: An individual responsible for managing the development / implementation, and/or operation of the system from a technical perspective and supervising the system upgrade. The individual who can answer questions relating to technical or business needs of the system. Provides input for the requirements and the communication planning.\nDomain: Collection of workstations or user accounts in a Windows Server environment.\nDNS: Domain Name System.\nCPU: Central Processing Unit.\nGDP: Good Documentation Practices.\nDHCP: Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol.\nSQL: Sequential Query Language.\nPerformance Monitor: Perform application run from Windows Run command field.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','This procedure will outline the process for the performance monitoring activities that are required for IT systems at Amneal Ireland.','In-Scope:\n1. Performance monitoring activities that are required to ensure that the IT system applications continue to perform as expected.\n2. Monitoring of IT systems to ensure optimum performance of servers.\n3. Monitoring of IT systems to ensure optimum performance of backup process.\n4. Monitoring of IT systems to ensure optimum performance of databases.\nOut of Scope:\n1. Performance monitoring of peripheral hardware such as label printers, scanners, client PCs etc.\n2. Performance monitoring of stand-alone laboratory and production hardware.','The Information Technology HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the performance monitoring activities at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-010 | 20-Oct-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-010A | 16-Mar-2017 | AI-CC-17-010 | 1. Sections 2.1.2, 2.1.3, 2.1.4, 5.2.2, 5.2.1, 5.3 and 5.4 from “periodic or “periodically” to “Quarterly”. 2. Section 2.1.5 Amended Table 1 to add the following systems with descriptions; Empower -QC Lab Data Acquisition System Instrument – QC Lab File Storage\nIT-010B | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | 1. Section 2.1.5 Amended Table 1 to add the following with Description; Maximo – Maintenance Schedule System 2. 6.0 References - Editorial changes 3. Section 5.3.1 Replaced instruction to record processor value with “The value that the processor is pegged at should be much less that 100%.” 4. Section 5.3.1 Added “A screen shot of the “Perform” monitor window shall be taken to verify counters are running as expected.” Removed definition for C.S.V. (Computer System Validation).\nIT-010C | 04-May-2021 | AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-21-032 | Annual Logo Change 2.1.1 Replaced ‘Quarter checks’ with ‘Monitoring’ 2.1.5 Added RF-Smart Labelling 3.1 Replace (IT) Manager with HOD','IT-004: Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System\nQM-004: Good Documentation Practices\nIT-011: Computer System Incident Management'),(67,'IT-011D','COMPUTER SYSTEM INCIDENT MANAGEMENT','IT-011D Computer System Incident Management.pdf','Declan Ryan','Declan Ryan','Michelle O\'Donoghue, Paul O\'Mahony','Kuldeep Joshi','2021-05-28',NULL,'IT-011C','1. Incident Reporting and Recording\n2. Incident Resolution\n3. Incident Reporting and Closure\n4. Impact Assessment and QA Approval\n5. Follow-up on Unresolved Incidents','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nCSIM: Computer System Incident Management.\nCCF: Change Control Form.\nIncident: An unplanned interruption to a service, or reduction in the quality of a service.\nIncident Management: The practice of minimising the negative impact of incidents by restoring normal service operation as quickly as possible.\nIssue: System performance that do not adversely impact the business, and so not categorised as an incident.\nIT: Information Technology.\nRAM: Random Access Memory.\nQA: Quality Assurance.\nQC: Quality Control.','The purpose of this SOP is to describe a procedure for managing computer system related incidents experienced by any user(s) of the computer system. Reporting of all such incidents, communication, recording, categorizing, resolution and closure of all incidents.','In Scope:\n1. The scope of this SOP applies to reporting, communicating, recording, categorizing, resolving and closing of Incidents related to GMP computer systems being used at Amneal Ireland.\nOut of Scope:\n1. Issues/service calls that do not adversely impact the business or are non-GMP issues/service calls.','The IT Management is responsible for ensuring that this SOP is successfully implemented, and all incidents related to computer systems shall be formally reported, communicated, recorded, categorized, resolved and closed.\nThe IT department is responsible for documenting the computer system incident management number in FM-IT-015, completing section 1.0 ‘Incident Details’ for each incident identified, escalating all incidents to appropriate software/hardware support team or vendor service support for prompt resolution, and completing section 3.0 ‘Completion of Work’.\nThe Vendor Service Support is responsible for analysing and fixing the incident experienced by users.\nSystem User(s) are responsible for completing section 1.0 ‘Incident Details’ for each incident identified and communicating any computer system related incidents to the IT team.\nThe QA department is responsible for completing section 2.0 ‘Impact Assessment’ and to review and complete section 3.0 ‘QA Approval’ on completion of work.','IT-011 | 20-Oct-2016 | N/A | First Issued\nIT-011A | 11-May-2017 | AI-CC-17-035 | Section 3.1 revised to IT Personnel Section 3.2.1 Ref FM-IT-015 Section 3.2.5 Ref FM-IT-010 Section 4.0 Add to definitions. Issues, CS, RAM, CCF, CAPA Section 5.1.3 Ref FM-IT-016 6.1 Change Annexure to Appendix 6.3 Add ref to new form FM-IT-015 6.4 Add ref to new form FM-IT-016 Appendix I revised to include sections for Incident Details, Impact Assessment and Completion of Work.\nIT-011B | 13-Dec-2019 | AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-19-138 | Amneal logo updated throughout the SOP and Forms. 1.0 Purpose updated to remove references to issues and ‘CS’ and replace communicating to managing computer system related incidents. 2.1.1 Revised order of In-scope list and added categorisations of incidents. Added Categorisation of Incidents. 2.2 revised to combine 2.2.1 and 2.2.2 replaced Exclusions with Out of Scope and added noncritical systems.\nIT-011C | 01-May-2020 | AI-CC-20-034 | Added Issues relating to Server Backup Process to Scope Section 2.1.1\nIT-011D | 28-May-2021 | AI-CC-21-033 | 2.1.1 Added ‘GMP’ for GMP computer systems. 2.2.1 Added ‘or are non-GMP issues/service calls.’ 2.2.1 Replaced ‘ServiceDesk’ with ‘ServiceNow’. 3.4.1 Added ‘Completing section 1.0 ‘Incident Details’ for each incident identified containing all the necessary details as per FM-IT-010’ and removed ‘and to complete section 1.0 ‘Incident Details’ as per FM-IT-010.','FM-IT-010: Computer System Incident Management Form\nFM-IT-015: Log of Computer System Incident Management Forms\nQM-010: Investigation System\nQM-012: Corrective Action Preventive Action\nQM-013: Change Control System'),(68,'IT-012C','DISASTER MANAGEMENT FOR IT SYSTEMS','IT-012C Disaster Management for IT Systems.pdf','Declan Ryan','Declan Ryan','Declan Ryan','Kuldeep Joshi','2021-05-04','2021-05-04','IT-012B','1. Disaster Recovery Plan Documentation\n2. Disaster Recovery Plan Creation\n3. Post Disaster Recovery Reporting\n4. DRP Review','Business Continuity: Business continuity is the activity performed by an organization to ensure that critical business functions will be available to customers, suppliers, regulators, and other entities that must have access to those functions.\nBusiness Owner: An individual who owns the relationship between the system, business process and data, ensures the system is maintained in a compliant state including providing adequate resources, and explains the system and business processes to auditors.\nDisaster: Any catastrophic event that affects the operation of the plant.\nDisaster Recovery: A planned and verified process to be used to recover system functionality in the event of a disaster.\nDRP: Disaster Recovery Plan.\nIT Application Owner: An individual responsible for managing the development/implementation, and/or operation of the system from a technical perspective and supervising the system upgrade. An individual who can answer questions relating to the technical or business needs of the system. Provides input for the requirements and the communication planning.\nSLA: Service Level Agreement.\nSQL: Structured Query Language - a special-purpose programming language designed for managing data held in a relational database management system (RDBMS).\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nHOD: Head of Department.','This procedure will outline the process for the disaster management activities that are required for IT Systems at Amneal Ireland Limited.','In-Scope:\n1. All IT Systems that are physically located at Amneal Ireland Limited that are critical for business continuity.\n2. Disaster Recovery of IT Infrastructure hardware including servers, backup equipment and network switches.\n3. Individual Disaster Recovery procedures will be maintained for each respective critical system.\nOut of Scope:\n1. Disaster Recovery for externally managed Amneal Global systems (e.g. Email).\n2. Disaster Recovery of stand-alone QC/ARD equipment.\n3. Disaster Recovery of production process equipment, including hardware.\n4. Disaster Recovery of standard IT applications such as Excel, SharePoint, MS Word, etc.\n5. Disaster Recovery for Cloud-hosted systems (e.g. Training Manager).','The Information Technology HOD or designee is required to ensure that this procedure is maintained and followed.\nIt is the responsibility of personnel involved in the disaster management at Amneal Ireland to follow this procedure.','IT-012 | 20-Oct-2016 | -- | First Issued.\nIT-012A | 21-Dec-2017 | AI-CC-17-107 | Section 2.1.3 Added references to two SOPs. Section 2.2.3 Added line to Out of Scope. Section 5.1.1 Removed reference to IT-014 Section 5.3.1 Added references to SOP IT-011, QM-010 and QM-013. Section 5.4.1 Added references to relevant disaster recovery testing forms. Section 6.2 Added reference to IT-015 Added reference to IT-017, QM-010, QM-013.\nIT-012B | 08-May-2018 | AI-CC-18-033 | Section 2.2.1 updated. Section 2.1.3 updated to add SOP IT-022 (Disaster Management for Maximo) and SOP IT-004(Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System.) Section 4.0 Removed DHCP, Domain and DNS. Section 5.1.1 Added \"by the It Application Owner\" Section 5.1.2 Added \"such as Fireproof safe\". Section 6.0 updated to add SOP IT-022 (Disaster Management for Maximo) and SOP-QM-004 (Good Documentation Practices).\nIT-012C | 04-May-2021 | AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-21-032 | Amneal Logo change. 2.1.3 Added SOP IT-027 Disaster Recovery for SCADA. 2.2.5 Added Disaster Recovery for Cloud-hosted systems (e.g. Training Manager). 3.1 Replace (IT) Manager with HOD. 4.3 Added catastrophic. 4.10 Added HOD: Head of Department. 5.1.4 Replaced System with architecture. 5.2.3.2 Reworded to list the various sources of contact information. 5.4.1.3 Replaced current with available to IT Team. References: Added SOP IT-027.','SOP IT-017: Disaster Management for BMS & QEMS\nSOP IT-022: Disaster Management for Maximo\nSOP IT-004: Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System\nSOP IT-015: Empower & Instrument Server Data Backup, Archival & Verification\nSOP IT-027: Disaster Recovery for SCADA\n21CFR Part 11: Electronic Record and Electronic Signature Rule.\nSOP QM-010: Investigation System\nSOP QM-013: Change Control System\nSOP QM-004: Good Documentation Practices'),(69,'IT-013I','SECURITY MANAGEMENT OF ELECTRONIC SYSTEMS','IT-013I Security Management of Electronic Systems.pdf','Declan Ryan','Declan Ryan','David McCarthy, Garry O’Meara','Kuldeep Joshi','2014-12-09','2021-12-09','IT-013H','1. General Security Requirements\n2. Physical Security\n3. Network Security\n4. User Access Levels for Electronic Systems\n5. Periodic Review of Electronic Systems\n6. Incident Management and Breach Reporting\n7. Training and Documentation Requirements','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nApplication Owner: An Application Owner is the individual or group with the responsibility to ensure that the program or programs, which make up the application, accomplish the specified objective or set of user requirements established for that application, including appropriate security safeguards.\nElectronic System: An Electronic System is a physical interconnection of components, or parts, that gathers various amounts of information together.\nGxP: Good Manufacturing, Clinical and Laboratory Practices.\nIT: Information Technology.\nSystem Owner: The System Owner is the individual responsible for the overall procurement, development, integration, modification, operation, maintenance, and retirement of an information system.\nHOD: Head of Department.\nSLA: Service Level Agreement.\nSOP: Standard Operating Procedure.','This procedure will outline security and access control requirements for Electronic Systems at Amneal Ireland and ensures the control, confidentiality (as appropriate), integrity and availability of Amneal Ireland’s systems, records and processes.','In-Scope:\n1. Physical Security\n2. Network Security\n3. User Access Levels for Electronic Systems\n4. Levels for Electronic Systems Access\n5. Periodic Review of Electronic Systems\nOut-of-Scope:\n1. Instructions for administration tasks refer to the relevant administration procedure for that Electronic System.','The IT (HOD)/ designee is responsible for ensuring that this procedure is always maintained and adhered.\nAll personnel (Administrators, System Owners) involved in the security and access control requirements at Amneal Ireland are responsible for following this procedure.\nAll personnel (employees, non-employees, contractors) are responsible for following the instructions in this procedure to maintain the physical, logical and user access control measures in place at Amneal Ireland.\nThe IT department/ System Owners/ department heads or designees as appropriate are responsible for carrying out any necessary training.\nThe IT department/ department heads or designees as appropriate are responsible for recording the use of any elevated privileged accounts (e.g. Administrator, Superuser) at Amneal Ireland.','IT-013 | 29-Apr-2016 | -- | First Issued\nIT-013A | 30-Jun-2017 | AI-CC-17-056 | Updated as follows: 1.1 Additional clarity to purpose section. 2.1 Added Maximo to Scope. 2.2 Added reference for Process Equipment and Empower3 which are out of scope of this SOP. 3.3 Added additional responsibility for all personnel to follow the security measures in place for IT systems. 3.4 Added additional responsibility for IT department to carry out any necessary training. 5.1.1 Added reference and clarity for IT systems to be evaluated as per SOP QM-005/QM-006. 5.1.2 Added details for incidences of breaches in security to be logged, impact assessed as per SOP IT-011. 5.1.3 Added details on Contracts/Service Level Agreements to define their responsibility with respect to security procedures. 5.1.4 Added details for changes carried out on an IT system per SOP QM-013 5.1.5 Added detail on maintaining list of GxP systems. 5.2.5 Added detail on environmental conditions monitoring of IT room as per SOP MT-016. 5.3.2.5 Added detail on user account and password combination as per SOP IT-001. 5.3.2.4 Added detail on Auto-log off after 15 minutes. 5.3.3.1 Added detail on periodic review as per SOP IT-009. 5.3.4 Added User Access section. 5.3.4.2 Added detail for OJT as per SOP QM-003 5.3.4.3 Added detail for when user no longer requires access. 6.1 Revised form FM-IT-008 for BMS 6.2 Corrected form number for FM-IT-009 6.4 Added form FM-IT-017 for Maximo 6.5 Added form FM-IT-019 for QEMS 6.6 Added form FM-IT-022 for Computer System Listing 6.7 to 6.20 Added references omitted from previous version.\nIT-013B | 25-Nov-2017 | AI-CC-17-099 | Added 6.21. Form Appendix – VI : Log of User Access for IT Systems (FM-IT-025) Added Reference to SOP QA-011 : On the Job Training Added 5.3.4.4 New point 5.3.4.4 Added 5.3.4.5 Reference to QA-011 in 5.3.4.1 and 5.3.4.2\nIT-013C | 15-Mar-2018 | AI-CC-18-016 | Updated as Follows: Added new point 3.5 -It is the responsibility of the IT department/department heads or designees as appropriate to record the use of any administrator accounts at Amneal Ireland. Added new point 5.3.4.5 To log into the Trend 963 Server administrator account used, the server name logged in, the instance when the account is used (i.e. date/time); who logged in/used the account (name/sign/date) and the purpose for logging in with the account is recorded as per Log of Administrator Account Use for Trend 963 (Form FM-IT-030). Added 6.8 Appendix-VII Log of Administrator Account Use for Trend 963 (FM-IT-030) Editorial Changes\nIT-013D | 10-Aug-2018 | AI-CC-18-084 | 2.2.3 Added Security and Access Control for Metrohm 900 Touch Controller. 2.2.4 Added Security and Access Control for UV-Visible Spectrophotometer Software. 2.2.5 Added Security and Access Control for Paperless Recorder. 5.1.5 Removed Reference to appendix V for template, reference form number instead. 5.3.4.5 Removed reference to Appendix VII use form number instead. 6.2. Removed Appendix-II : Request for Server IT room Access (FM-IT-009) & form that is in use is Form SOP-MT-010. Removed form FM-IT-009 Section 6 renumbered the references to have appendixes first and SOP in ascending order. Added references for QC-051, QC-059, IT-020 and MT-052. Form FM-IT-017 updated to include Operating SOP reference. Editorial Changes.\nIT-013E | 07-May-2020 | AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-20-017 | Title revised to “Security Management of Electronic Systems”. Updated Amneal Logo Throughout document replaced all references to “IT Systems” with “Electronic Systems.” “IT” or “Information Technology Manager” to “IT (HOD). Purpose: Reworded for clarity. In-Scope: Reworded list of In-scope systems and revised Table 1. Out-of-scope: combined 2.2.1, 2.2.2, 2.2.3 into 2.2.1 Responsibilities: Reworded for clarity. 3.4 Added ‘System Owners’ Definitions: Added Electronic System and HOD 5.1.3 Added additional detail for Remote access. 5.1.4 Added words ‘that impact on the validated state’. 5.1.5 Reworded for additional clarity. 5.1.6 Reworded for additional clarity and changed form name ‘Access & Disable Electronic System Form’. 5.1.7 Reworded for additional clarity and changed form name ‘Access & Disable Electronic System Form’. 5.1.8 Reworded for additional clarity and changed form name ‘Access & Disable Electronic System Form’. 5.1.9 Reworded for additional clarity and changed form name ‘Access & Disable Electronic System Form’. 5.1.10 Computer System Number changed to AI-CSL-XXX 5.3 Replaced Logical Security with Network Security and correct grammar in section. 5.3.1 Additional detail on unique usernames if IT-001 can’t be followed. 5.3.2 Reworded for additional clarity 5.3.3 Added detail on Open Systems and correct clarified wording on closed systems. 5.4 Added User Access Levels for Electronic Systems 5.4.1 to 5.4.7 Added instruction steps to guide users in completing form ‘Access & Disable Electronic System’. References: removed BMS, MAXIMO, QEMS and Log of User Access for IT Systems, QC-051. References: Added, IT-020, IT-021, IT-023, IT-024, MT-021, QC-087. Forms: Obsoleted Access Request Forms for BMS, MAXIMO, QEMS, Log of User Access for IT Systems.\nIT-013F | 18-Jun-2021 | AIM-CC-21-009 | 2.1 Added Functional Tester to Table 1. 5.4 Added Functional Tester to Table 2.\nIT-013G | 06-Aug-2021 | AIM-CC-21-019 | 2.1 Added Serialisation System and Print Verification Unit to Table 1. 5.4 Added Serialisation System and Print Verification Unit to Table 2.\nIT-013H | 13-Sep-2021 | AI-CC-21-071 | 2.1 Added HW4 Data Monitoring Software to Table 1. 5.4 Added HW4 Data Monitoring Software to Table 2.\nIT-013I | 20-Nov-2024 | CC-AMN-22-6778 | Added Microbiology Laboratory, Smartdac Temperature Monitoring System to Table 2 6.0 Added IT-029 & QC-107','FM-IT-053: Access & Disable Electronic System Request Form\nFM-IT-054: Log of User Access for Electronic Systems\nFM-IT-022: Computer System Listing\nFM-IT-030: Log of Administrator Account Use for Trend 963\n21 CFR Part 11: Electronic Record and Electronic Signature Rule\nIT-001: Domain Security Administration\nIT-009: Preventative Maintenance for IT Systems\nIT-011: Computer System Incident Management\nIT-020: Administration of Paperless Recorder\nIT-021: Administration of MAXIMO\nIT-023: Administration of RF-Smart Labelling Software\nIT-024: Administration of TIAMO\nIT-025: Administration of Scada\nMF-040: Set-up, operation and cleaning of the MDI Serialisation Equipment\nMF-048: Setup and Operation of the Serialisation System\nMT-010: Access Control\nMT-016: Operation of the BMS\nMT-021: Operation of the QEMS\nMT-052: Security Management for Process Equipment\nMT-064: Handling Setup, Operation and cleaning of Datalogger.\nQA-001: Procedure for Document Issuance\nQA-011: On the Job Training\nQC-044: Empower3 Administration Procedure\nQC-059: Administration of UV-Visible Spectrophotometer Software\nQC-087: Administration of FTIR\nQM-002: Control of Revision Controlled Documents\nQM-003: Training System\nQM-005: Quality Risk Management\nQM-006: Failure Mode and Effect Analysis\nQM-010: Investigation System\nQM-012: Corrective Action Preventative Action (CAPA)\nQM-013: Change Control System\nIT-029: Administration of Yokogawa Smartdac Temperature Monitoring System\nSOP QC-107: Operation of the Microbiology Laboratory Central Temperature Monitoring System'),(70,'IT-014G','SYNCHRONISATION OF TIME FOR STANDALONE EQUIPMENT/INSTRUMENT','IT-014G Synchronisation of time for Standalone Equip Instrument.pdf','Derek Russell','Derek Russell','Declan Ryan, Donnchadh Ryan','Kuldeep Joshi','2022-06-24','2025-06-23','IT-014F','1. Synchronisation of standalone equipment/instruments with Amneal Ireland domain network timings.\n2. Daylight Savings Time adjustments.\n3. Use of forms FM-IT-006 and FM-IT-007 for recording and correcting time.\n4. Procedures for time synchronisation outside of Daylight Savings Time.\n5. Responsibilities for personnel and administrators.','QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research & Development.\nStandalone equipment/instrument: This is equipment/instruments that can perform functions independently and are not linked to a computer server.\nDomain Network Time: This is the AmnealIE domain computer network at Amneal Ireland where all connected computers are synchronised with the domain controller server.\nNTP: Network Time Protocol is a computer service for the synchronisation of time on computers. The Microsoft NTP Server is time.windows.com.\nDaylight savings time: This is the practice of adjusting clocks forward one hour at the start of spring and of adjusting clocks backwards by one hour in the autumn to standard time. Where a piece of equipment/instruments are connected to a server, the server will automatically update the time on the piece of equipment /instrument to reflect Daylight Savings Time.\nSynchronisation: To cause to occur or operate with exact coincidence in time or rate.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To define the procedure for the synchronisation of the time of standalone equipment/instruments with Amneal Ireland domain network timings.','This procedure applies to the synchronisation of the standalone equipment/instruments in any department within Amneal Ireland that requires synchronisation with the Amneal Ireland domain network timings. This includes Daylight Savings Time changes where times are adjusted by one hour.','All relevant Heads of Department are responsible for ensuring that all personnel within their departments adhere to this procedure.\nPersonnel with system administrator/master access rights are responsible for outlining the work required, synchronising the standalone equipment/instruments with the Amneal Ireland domain network timings, and providing supporting documentation.\nAll personnel are responsible for ensuring that equipment displaying time as per Section I of Form FM-IT-006 has the ‘Awaiting Time Synchronisation Label’ attached prior to Daylight Savings Time change and removed after verification.\nAll personnel are responsible for ensuring that equipment displaying time as per Section I of Form FM-IT-006 is not used until verification of correct time has been completed.\nAll personnel are responsible for ensuring that equipment listed in Section III of Form FM-IT-006 and Form FM-IT-007 has the ‘Use Amneal Domain Network Time/Date only’ label attached.','IT-014 | 11-Jan-2017 | -- | First Issued\nIT-014A | 21-Mar-2017 | AI-CC-17-017 | Addition to section 2.1 to include Daylight Savings Time. Addition to section 4.0 Definitions. Addition to section 5.2 to reference Form FM-IT-006 and FM-IT-007. Addition to section 5.2.1 to 5.2.4 to detail steps for Daylight Savings Time and reference SOP MT-005A. Addition to section 5.3 for Form FM-IT-012 for Time / Clock requiring adjusting. Additional references for Section 6 for forms FM-IT-006 and FM-IT-007.\nIT-014B | 15-Mar-2018 | AI-CC-18-016 | Section 5.2 Added detail reflecting updated Form FM-IT-006. Section 5.2.4 Updated daylight saving dates. Added/removed equipment on Forms FM-IT-006 and FM-IT-007. Editorial Changes.\nIT-014C | 30-Jan-2019 | AI-CC-18-140 AID-CC-18-058 | Change Amneal Logo. Add DPI Leak Tester to FM-IT-006 and FM-IT-007.\nIT-014D | 26-Feb-2019 | AI-CC-18-135 AI-CC-19-020 | Additional HPLC to FM-IT-006 and FM-IT-007. Add Sartorius Micro Balance (6 decimal place) to FM-IT-006 and FM-IT-007.\nIT-014E | 27-Mar-2019 | AI-CC-19-038 | Corrected typographical errors. Added responsibilities for personnel regarding time synchronisation labels and verification. Updated procedures for Daylight Savings Time adjustments.\nIT-014F | 09-Jul-2019 | AI-CC-19-083 | Switched 3.3 and 3.4 for correct sequence. Added 3.5 for Section III of forms FM-IT-006 and FM-IT-007. Updated forms FM-IT-006, FM-IT-007, and FM-IT-011.\nIT-014G | 24-Jun-2021 | AI-CC-18-140 CC-AMN-22-3323 | Updated Form FM-IT-012-00 to FM-IT-012-01 to update Amneal Logo. Updated numbering for standalone equipment / instrument forms to AI-DST-YY.','FM-IT-011: Time Synchronisation Work Order /Record Form\nFM-IT-012: Log of Time Synchronisation Work Order Numbers\nFM-IT-006: Instrument Time verification record\nFM-IT-007: List of equipment display time\nFM-IT-048: Awaiting Time Synchronisation Label\nFM-IT-050: Use Amneal Domain Network Time/Date only\nSOP QM-013: Change Control System\nSOP MT-005: Procedure for Maintenance Management at Amneal Ireland\nSOP QA-001: Procedure for Document Issuance\nSOP QM-002: Control of Revision Controlled Documents'),(71,'IT-015C','EMPOWER3 & INSTRUMENT SERVER DATA BACKUP, ARCHIVAL AND VERIFICATION PROCEDURE','IT-015C Empower3 & Ins Server Data Backup, Archival & Ver.pdf','Michelle O\'Donoghue','Michelle O\'Donoghue','Declan Ryan, Paul O\'Mahony','Kuldeep Joshi','2020-04-05','2023-04-04','IT-015B','1. Data Backup Procedures (Hot, Cold, and Complete Backup).\n2. Data Archival and Retrieval Procedures.\n3. Periodic Review and Verification of Back-up and Archived Data.\n4. Retention Policies for Back-up and Archived Data.\n5. Backup and Restore of Empower3 Projects.\n6. Disaster Recovery Testing.','Data Backup: Making copies of data to restore the original in case of data loss.\nCold Backup: Offline backup performed when the database is offline.\nHot Backup: Online backup performed when the database is active.\nComplete Backup: Covers all electronic GMP data, including Empower3 and Instrument servers.\nArchived Data: Data removed from primary storage to secondary devices like NAS or tapes.\nBack-up Data: Data copied from primary storage to secondary devices without removing it from primary storage.\nPeriodic Review: Verification of back-up/archived data to ensure accessibility, accuracy, and availability.\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nHOD: Head of Department.\nNAS: Network Attached Storage.','To provide a systematic approach for the management of electronic data specifically for back-up and restore, archival and retrieval, and periodic verification of back-up and archived data for Empower3 and Instrument Server.','In Scope:\n1. This procedure applies to all Empower3 and Instrument Server electronic data of Amneal Ireland.\nOut of Scope:\n1. Procedure QC-044 Empower3 Administration covers the administration and access to Empower3.','The IT (HOD)/ designee is responsible for ensuring that the backup, archival, and restoration of the data is done according to this procedure.\nThe IT (HOD)/ designee is responsible for performing periodic review/verification of back-up and archived data.\nThe IT department/ System Owners/ department heads or designees are responsible for ensuring that all personnel within IT and QC/ARD Laboratory adhere to this procedure.','IT-015 | 21-Mar-2017 | -- | First Issued.\nIT-015A | 31-May-2017 | AI-CC-17-042 | Added details for Hot and Cold Backups, including Message Centre, Audit Trail, and Empower3 Projects. Added assessment for data archival based on storage space and database management.\nIT-015B | 21-Jun-2018 | AI-CC-18-058 | Changed references from \"Empower\" to \"Empower3\". Updated backup procedures and added instructions for backup and restore of projects.\nIT-015C | 05-Apr-2020 | AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-20-034 | Updated Amneal Logo. Added scope and out-of-scope sections. Updated definitions and backup procedures. Added Table 2 for data verification.','FM-IT-013: Electronic Data Backup and Restore for Lab Instruments\nFM-IT-014: List of Empower3 Projects to be Archived and Retrieved\nFM-IT-021: Log of Empower3 Backup Tapes\nQM-013: Change Control System\nQC-044: Empower3 Administration Procedure\nIT-011: Computer System Incident Management\nIT-012: Disaster Management for IT Systems\nIT-013: Security Management for IT Systems'),(72,'IT-016A','OPERATION OF CCTV SYSTEM','IT-016A Operation of CCTV System.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Gerard Ryan, IT','Declan Ryan, IT, Zita O\'Rourke, HR','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2019-01-10','2023-01-09','IT-016','CCTV system operates 24/7, images owned by Amneal Ireland, access restricted to authorised personnel, footage retained for 30 days unless needed for investigation.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. CCTV: Closed Circuit TV system. Data Controller: A person who determines the purposes for which and the manner in which any personal data are processed. Data Processor: any person who processes the data on behalf of the data controller. SLT: Site Leadership Team at Amneal Ireland. ODPC: Office of the Data Protection Commissioner.','To outline the company approach to using CCTV system to provide a safe environment, protect company property, assist in resolving operational incidents, and comply with the Data Protection Act (1998) and the CCTV Code of Practice.','Applies to all Amneal Ireland employees, contractors, visitors, and members of the public captured on CCTV. Excludes targeted surveillance activity regulated by the Regulation of Investigatory Powers Act (2000).','Heads of Department ensure adherence. All personnel must treat viewed material with confidentiality. Security Services Site Coordinator, Data Controllers, Data Processors handle CCTV data.','IT-016: 10-May-2017, First Issued. IT-016A: 10-Jan-2019, Changed Amneal Logo, Added confidentiality clause, Reworded sentences, Added EHS Manager, Changed Facilities team to Amneal Direct Facilities Staff.','FM-IT-018: CCTV Viewing Record. FM-IT-020: Request for CCTV Access.'),(73,'IT-017B','DISASTER RECOVERY OF BMS AND QEMS','IT-017B Disaster Recovery of BMS and QEMS.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Oliver Lynch, IT','Declan Ryan, IT, Mark Smyth, MT','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-07-22','2027-07-22','IT-017A','Disaster recovery process for BMS and QEMS servers, annual testing required, two methods for restoration depending on server status, NAS and Tape storage solutions used.','Acronis: Backup software. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited. Backup: Copies of data for restoration. BMS: Building Management System. Disaster Recovery Test server: Hardware/VM for testing. ESXi: VMware solution. GxP: Good Manufacturing, Clinical and Laboratory Practices. IP: Internet Protocol. IT: Information Technology. NAS: Network Access Storage. QEMS: Qualified Environmental Monitoring System. Restore: Copying back data. Virtual Machine (VM): Software computer. SOP: Standard Operating Procedure. System Owner: Individual responsible for system management. HOD: Head of Department.','To provide instruction and guidance for the disaster recovery steps for the BMS and QEMS servers.','Applies to the disaster recovery of the BMS and QEMS servers. Excludes infrastructure outside of Application and Database servers.','IT HOD ensures procedure maintenance. All personnel must follow the procedure. IT department conducts training. Annual disaster recovery testing required. Safety guidelines must be adhered to.','IT-017: 26-Nov-2017, First Issued. IT-017A: 09-Nov-2020, Amneal Logo change, Replaced Appendices with Forms, Added SQL queries, Updated Definitions, Additional tests added. IT-017B: 22-Jul-2024, Replaced Manager title with HOD, Updated Definitions, General editorial changes.','FM-IT-023: Disaster Recovery Testing – Application Server. FM-IT-026: Disaster Recovery Testing – Database Server. IT-004: Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System. IT-012: Disaster Management for IT Systems. QM-004: Good Documentation Practices. QM-013: Change Control System. QM-010: Investigation System. IT-011: Computer System Incident Management.'),(74,'IT-018D','PROCEDURE FOR IT MAINTENANCE MANAGEMENT AT AMNEAL IRELAND','IT-018D Procedure for IT Maintenance Management.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Declan Ryan, IT','Patrick McGuire, QA, Paul O’Mahony, QC','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2022-08-30','2025-08-29','IT-018C','Scheduled maintenance programme for electronic systems, daily, weekly, monthly, and annual schedules, incident management for incomplete tasks, annual revision of IT Maintenance Schedule Form.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited. System Owner: Individual responsible for system management. IT: Information Technology. GxP: Good Manufacturing, Clinical and Laboratory Practices. SOP: Standard Operating Procedure. QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research & Development. Audit Trail: System tracing transactions. HOD: Head of Department.','To describe the IT Maintenance Management at Amneal Ireland.','Applies to the scheduled maintenance of electronic systems within Amneal Ireland. Excludes maintenance of manufacturing equipment, utility equipment, building, and facilities.','IT HOD ensures procedure maintenance. All personnel must follow the procedure. IT department conducts training. IT HOD develops and schedules maintenance. Safety guidelines must be adhered to. Documentation must follow GMP practices.','IT-018: 26-Nov-2017, First Issue. IT-018A: 04-Apr-2019, Amneal Logo change, Added maintenance tasks. IT-018B: 01-May-2020, Updated definitions, Added monthly reviews. IT-018C: 28-Oct-2021, Added review of Serialisation. IT-018D: 26-Aug-2022, Corrected typos, Added HOD definition, Added review of Training Manager.','FM-IT-024: IT Maintenance Schedule Form. IT-001: Domain Security Administration. IT-002: Computer Network Access, Helpdesk and Termination. IT-004: Data Backup, Restore Procedure for Server System. IT-009: Preventative Maintenance for IT Systems. IT-011: Computer System Incident Management. IT-012: Disaster Management for IT Systems. IT-013: Security Management for Electronic Systems. IT-014: Synchronisation of time for Standalone Equipment/Instrument. IT-015: Empower & Instrument Server Data Backup, Archival & Verification. IT-016: Operation of CCTV System. IT-017: Disaster Recovery of BMS and QEMS. IT-020: Administration of Paperless Recorder. IT-021: Administration of MAXIMO. IT-022: Disaster Recovery for Maximo. IT-023: Administration of RF-Smart Labelling Software. IT-024: Administration of Tiamo. MT-005: Procedure for Maintenance Management at Amneal Ireland. MT-010: Access Control Procedure. MT-052: Security Management for Process Equipment. QC-044: Empower Administration Procedure. QC-059: Administration of UV-Visible Spectrophotometer Software. QC-066: Electronic Records & Audit Trails Review of Empower3 Software. QC-082: Operational Use of Tiamo Software. QC-087: Administration of FTIR. QM-004: Good Documentation Practices. QM-010: Investigation System. QM-012: Corrective Action Preventative Action (CAPA). QM-013: Change Control System. QM-042: Operation and Administration of Training Manager.'),(75,'IT-019A','SECURITY PATCHING FOR IT SYSTEMS','IT-019A Security Patching for IT Systems.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Declan Ryan, IT','Derek Russell, IT, Elizabeth Moore, QA',NULL,'2022-03-28','2025-03-27','IT-019','Security patch management for servers and PCs, use of PDQ Inventory and PDQ Deploy for patching, WSUS for workstation updates, automatic anti-virus updates, and incident logging for security breaches.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited. IT: Information Technology. Patch: Software update to fix bugs or vulnerabilities. WSUS: Windows Server Update Services. PDQ: Software package for efficient deployment of security patches.','To define the procedure for Security Patch Management at Amneal Ireland.','Applies to the security patch management of servers and PCs within Amneal Ireland.','IT staff ensure vulnerabilities are minimized and infrastructure is patched. Users must allow patches to be deployed and perform reboots as required.','IT-019: 03-Apr-2019, First Issued. IT-019A: 28-Mar-2022, Updated definitions, Added PDQ, Updated patching procedures, Editorial changes.','IT-001: Domain Security Administration. IT-011: Computer System Incident Management.'),(76,'IT-020A','ADMINISTRATION OF PAPERLESS RECORDER','IT-020A Administration of Paperless Recorder.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Declan Ryan, IT','Derek Russell, IT, Elizabeth Moore, QA',NULL,'2022-03-28','2025-03-27','IT-020','User access management, 