(84,'IT-029','ADMINISTRATION OF YOKOGAWA SMARTDAC TEMPERATURE MONITORING SYSTEM','IT-029 Admin of Yokogawa smartdac temp monitoring system.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','David McCarthy, Declan Ryan','David McCarthy, Declan Ryan, Kuldeep Joshi','David McCarthy, Declan Ryan','2024-09-02','2027-09-02','N/A','1. Provides a systematic approach for administering the Yokogawa Smartdac paperless Temperature Monitoring System.\n2. Includes processes for user access, data storage, and audit trail management.\n3. Defines responsibilities for administrators and users.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.\nIT: Information Technology.\nHOD: Head of Department.\nACK: Acknowledgement.\nFTP: File Transfer Protocol.\nSOP: Standard Operating Procedure.\nCAPA: Corrective Action / Preventative Action.\nCSR: Certificate signature request.\nSNTP: Simple Network Time Protocol.\nAO: Analog Output.\nAudit Trail: a sequence of records linking data from its source to completion.','To provide a systematic approach for the administration of the Yokogawa Smartdac paperless Temperature Monitoring System (AI-QC-205) in the Microbiology Laboratory at Amneal Ireland Limited.','This SOP applies to the administration of the Yokogawa Smartdac paperless Temperature Monitoring System (AI-QC-205) in the Microbiology Laboratory at Amneal Ireland Limited. It includes processes for user access, data storage, and audit trail management.','1. MicroLab HOD or designee ensures users are trained.\n2. IT department administrators follow and ensure training on the procedure.\n3. QC Microbiology Department users follow and ensure training on the procedure.\n4. Software administrators manage user access, data backup, and audit trail reviews.','Revision IT-029, Date 2024-09-02, CCF No. CC-AMN-22-6778, Reason: First Issued.','1. 21CFR Part 11 : Electronic Record and Electronic Signature Rule.\n2. SOP QC-107 : Operation of the Microbiology Laboratory Central Temperature Monitoring System.\n3. SOP QM-010 : Investigation System.\n4. SOP QM-013 : Change Control System.\n5. FM-IT-053 : Access & Disable Electronic System Request Form.\n6. FM-IT-054 : Log of User Access for Electronic Systems.'),(85,'QC-002L','Sampling of Raw Materials at Amneal Ireland','QC-002L Sampling of Raw Materials at Amneal Ireland.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Neemt Suresh, QA','Lorraine Henry, QA; David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-01-17','2027-01-16','QC-002K','To provide a standardized procedure for sampling raw materials to ensure compliance with GMP and regulatory requirements. Sampling is done in controlled environments (e.g., dispensing enclosure or isolator). Microbiological and chemical samples are collected separately. Sampling details are recorded in the Raw Material Sampling Report (FM-QC-034).','Raw Material: Active Pharmaceutical Ingredient (API) or excipient. Composite Sample: A homogeneous mix of material from the same batch but from different containers. Reference Sample: A sample stored for future analysis if needed.','To provide a standardized procedure for sampling raw materials to ensure compliance with GMP and regulatory requirements.','Applies to raw materials used in the manufacture of authorized/commercial medicinal products at Amneal Ireland.','Warehouse Personnel: Notify QC/ARD upon receipt of raw materials. QC/ARD: Perform sampling and testing of raw materials. QA: Oversee the sampling process and ensure compliance.','Revision QC-002: First issued on 19-Sep-2016. Revision QC-002A: Updated to include new logo and additional details on 28-Jun-2019. Revision QC-002B: Updated definitions and sampling requirements on 20-Mar-2020. Revision QC-002C: Added pre-sampling labeling checks on 06-Jul-2020. Revision QC-002D: Updated responsibilities and sampling procedures on 17-Nov-2020. Revision QC-002E: Updated sample quantities for specific materials on 18-May-2021. Revision QC-002F: Removed sampling log and added checks for contaminants on 03-Nov-2021. Revision QC-002G: Updated scope and sampling procedures on 11-Apr-2023. Revision QC-002H: Added new raw materials to the sampling list on 02-Nov-2023. Revision QC-002I: Updated sampling requirements for specific materials on 08-Apr-2024. Revision QC-002J: General editorial changes and updated sample quantities on 10-Jun-2024. Revision QC-002K: Added new material (Micronised Albuterol Sulfate) on 27-Jun-2024. Revision QC-002L: Updated sampling request form and added \"checked by\" section on 04-Oct-2024.','FM-QC-034: Raw Material Sampling Report. FM-QC-035: QC/ARD Material Sample Quantity List. FM-QC-038: QC/ARD Sample for Analysis Label. FM-QC-258: Raw Material Sampling Request Form. MM-001: Receipt and Storage of Materials into the Warehouse. MF-008: Labelling of Material, Product, Room and Equipment. QC-009: Receipt and Handling of Incoming Samples in the QC/ARD and Microbiology Laboratory.'),(86,'QC-025C','OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF WATERS HPLC SYSTEM','QC-025C Operation and Maintenance of Waters HPLC System.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Patrick Flynn, QC/ARD','David Ryan, QC/ARD, Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-03-26','2024-03-26','QC-025B','1. Overview of Waters Alliance HPLC System components.\n2. Steps for preparing a new or dry separation module for operation.\n3. Detailed system operation steps including priming, purging, and equilibrating.\n4. Maintenance procedures including preventive maintenance and system washdown.','HPLC: High Performance Liquid Chromatography\nAmneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To define the procedure for the operation and maintenance of Waters Alliance 2695 HPLC system.','This procedure applies to the Quality Control and Analytical Research & Development (QC/ARD) Laboratory at Amneal, Ireland.','The QC/ARD personnel are responsible for complying with the requirements of this procedure.\nThe Laboratory Manager is responsible for ensuring that QC/ARD personnel comply with this procedure.','Revision: QC-025, Date: 30-Sep-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued\nRevision: QC-025A, Date: 11-Sep-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated SOP logo and removed reference to Appendix throughout.\nRevision: QC-025B, Date: 10-Jan-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-19-136, Reason: Updated sections for clarity and added new steps.\nRevision: QC-025C, Date: 26-Mar-2024, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-001, Reason: Updated sections for clarity and added new steps.','FM-QC-022: HPLC Usage Logbook\nFM-QC-023: HPLC Maintenance Logbook\nQC-021: Operation of Empower\nQC-012: Chromatographic Column Management\nFM-QC-008: Column Receipt and Usage Logbook'),(87,'QC-026D','ROUTINE TESTING OF COMPRESSED AIR AT AMNEAL IRELAND','QC-026D Routine Testing of Compressed Air at Amneal Ireland.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','08-Feb-2022','Anne McGrath, QC/ARD, Tracy McCarthy, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Josh, QA','2022-02-15','2035-02-14','QC-026C','Frequency of testing: Viable air sampling every 3 months, Non-viable particulate every 3 months, Dewpoint every 12 months, Oil (hydrocarbon) every 12 months. Sample locations: See FM-QC-053 for Routine Compressed Air Sample Locations. Testing and reporting: Amneal QC/ARD Micro organises third-party contractor for testing. Specifications: Dew Point ≤-40°C, Oil content ≤0.1mg/m³, Solid particulates count as per ISO 8573 Class 2, Microbial (viable air sampling) as per ISO Class 7 and 8.','QC / ARD Micro– Quality Control Analytical Research and Development, CNC – Controlled Non-Classified, DPI – Dry Powder Inhaler, MDI – Metered Dose Inhaler, CFU – Colony Forming Unit, Viable Particle-Viable colony forming units, which can be bacteria, fungi, or yeasts, Non-Viable Particle- A small discrete mass of solid or liquid matter, Dewpoint- Temperature at which water vapour begins to condense, NOE- Notification of Event, Unplanned Deviation (NOI)- Notice of Investigation, ISO-International Organisation of Standardization.','The purpose of this SOP is to describe the routine testing of the Compressed Air for the evaluation of the quality of the Amneal Ireland Compressed Air system.','The scope of this SOP is limited to the routine testing of the Compressed Air system in MDI and DPI for non-viable particulates, dewpoint, oil content and viable air sampling.','It is the responsibility of all personnel actively involved in Compressed Air sampling to adhere to this SOP. QC/ARD Micro to track and monitor sample management of Compressed Air and to compile and review results received from an approved third-party contractor. QC/ARD Micro to ensure adherence to the Compressed Air sampling and testing SOP by the approved third-party contractor. The third-party contractor taking the samples to do so in a safe manner and in compliance with Amneal safety requirements. Engineering as System Owners/ users to ensure the safe and compliant operation of the Compressed Air system.','Revision: QC-026, Date: 27 Oct 2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-026A, Date: 22-Dec-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-068, Reason: General formatting throughout Section 2.1 updated to add reference to MDI and DPI. Revision: QC-026B, Date: 31-Aug-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-021, Reason: Update QC/ARD to QC/ARD Micro throughout the document. Revision: QC-026C, Date: 28-Feb-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140 AIM-CC-19-004, Reason: Update Procedure onto new template. Revision: QC-026D, Date: 15-Feb-2022, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-0601, Reason: Section 4.11 Include Unplanned Deviation, Section 5.2.3, Replaced QA-002 with QM-026, Section 5.4 & 5.4.2 Included a table for events, Section 5.4.3 Updated title of QM-010, Section 6.0 Updated title of QM-010, Replaced QA-002 with QM-026, FM-QC-052-04- Separated out review of form and report, General formatting and editorial updates.','QM-010 : Unplanned Deviations and Investigations. ISO 8573 : Compressed air – Part 1: contaminants and purity classes. QC-049 : Notification of Event from Contract Laboratories to Amneal Ireland. FM-QC-051 : Routine Compressed Air Testing Schedule. FM-QC-052 : Routine Compressed Air Testing Record. FM-QC-053 : Routine Compressed Air Testing Sample Locations. ES-010 : Management of Contractors. QM-026 : Technical Agreements. QM-013 : Change Control System.'),(88,'QC-027X','SAMPLING OF INCOMING PACKAGING MATERIALS','QC-027X Sampling of Incoming Sampling Material.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Donny Ryan, MF','Kayleigh Rosseto, MF','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2022-10-21','2023-10-20','QC-027W','Frequency of testing: Viable air sampling every 3 months, Non-viable particulate every 3 months, Dewpoint every 12 months, Oil (hydrocarbon) every 12 months. Sample locations: See FM-QC-053 for Routine Compressed Air Sample Locations. Testing and reporting: Amneal QC/ARD Micro organises third-party contractor for testing. Specifications: Dew Point ≤-40°C, Oil content ≤0.1mg/m³, Solid particulates count as per ISO 8573 Class 2, Microbial (viable air sampling) as per ISO Class 7 and 8.','PPE: Personal Protective Equipment, HDPE: High Density Polyethylene, ANSI: American National Standards Institute, COA: Certificate of Analysis, AR number: Analytical Receipt number (Amneal lot number), QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research & Development, QA: Quality Assurance, IPQA: In-Process Quality Assurance, SOP: Standard Operating Procedure, COC: Certificate of Conformance, MDI: Metered Dose Inhaler, DPI: Dry Powder Inhaler, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland., Primary Packaging Material: Any material that comes in direct contact with the finished product., Secondary Packaging Material: Any material that does not come in direct contact with the finished product., Routine Sampling: Routine Sampling is the sampling activity carried out on incoming material that provides a representative sample to be used in the release testing of the material., Additional Sampling: Additional Sampling is any sampling activity carried out independent of Routine Sampling., Reference/Reserve Sample: This is a sample of a batch of Packaging Material which is stored for the purpose of being analysed should the need arise during the shelf life of the batch concerned.','To define the procedures and practices to be used when sampling incoming packaging materials at Amneal Ireland.','This procedure applies to all personnel involved in sampling incoming Packaging Materials at Amneal Ireland.','QC/ARD department: Outline the details in this SOP, Complete FM-QC-240, Packaging Material Sampling Request Form prior to sampling and submit to Operations, Carry out the sampling of incoming Packaging Materials if required by strictly adhering to the details outlined in this SOP. MF / Operations department: Carry out the sampling of incoming Packaging Materials if required by strictly adhering to the details outlined in this SOP and complete the packaging material sampling report FM-QC-041, Any deficiencies/defects observed in the sampling equipment, sample container or sampling environment must be reported immediately to the appropriate line supervisor/manager, Personnel performing sampling must ensure that they are trained to the current revision of this document. QA department: IPQA shall complete the relevant Area Line Sign-off as required.','Revision: QC-027, Date: 04-Nov-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-027A, Date: 27-Sep-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-075, Reason: Added definition of routine sampling to section 4.10, Added definition of additional sampling to section 4.11, Added to section 5.2 “sampling area” changed to “area designated for sampling”, Added reference to PPE as per SOP MF-009, Added Section 5.3, “If the container is found in damaged condition, inform the QC/ARD Manager or designee and do not proceed with the sampling. QC/ARD Manager or Designee shall determine further course of actions.”, Section 5.4.6, Removed and added to Section 5.5.7 as “Record the quantity required for each material in Appendix II - Packaging Material Sample Quantity List, (FM-QC-042). The quantity chosen should deliver an overall quantity to meet the testing requirements as per the relevant specification or document/protocol. Also ensure that the quantity chosen delivers an overall quantity to meet retention sample quantity requirements as per QM-027, “Retention Sample Management”, Section 5.4.6, Updated to include cleaning as applicable, “When the sampling is complete, ensure the sampling area is clean as per MF-052, “Operation of Ethanol Sampling-Dispensing Booth. Where possible use disposable sampling tools. Record in Appendix III - Packaging Material Sampling Log, (FM-QC-043)”, Section 5.5.1, Updated to include Primary and Secondary DPI Packaging Materials, Included reference to cleaning of sampling area in 5.4.6.','FM-QC-041 : Packaging Material Sampling Report, FM-QC-042 : Packaging Material Sample Quantity List, FM-QC-044 : QC/ARD Packaging Sample for Analysis Label, FM-QC-142 : Clean and Dirty side of XP-33 with demarcation line, FM-QC-240 : Packaging Material Sampling Request Form, FM-MF-005 : Under Test Label, SOP MM-001 : Receipt and Storage of Materials into the Warehouse, SOP MM-011 : Courier Shipments, SOP MF-008 : Labelling of Material, Equipment and Room, SOP MF-009 : Gowning Procedure for the Inhalation Areas, SOP QC-058 : Packaging Material Sampling Area Clearance and Sign-Off, SOP QC-061 : General Requirements for XP-33 And Operation Of XP-33 Sampling Booth, SOP QC-028 : Transfer of Samples to Global Amneal Sites, SOP QM-027 : Retention Sample Management, ANSI/ASQ Z1.4, WHO Technical Report Series, No. 929, 2005 Annex 4, “WHO guidelines for sampling of pharmaceutical products and related materials”, EudralLex Volume 4, “EU Guidelines to Good Manufacturing Practice Medicinal Products for Human and Veterinary Use – annex 19 Reference and Retention Samples”, SOP QM-018 : Vendor Notification of Quality Issue for RM-PM-Other Material, MM-012 : Warehouse Cleaning Procedure, MM-003 : Garbing Procedure for Warehouse Entry, FM-QC-105 : Packaging Material Sampling Area Clearance Form, FM-QC-106 : Packaging Material Sampling Area Sign-Off Form, QC-052 : Sampling of Finished Product Sample and Stability Samples, FM-QC-342 : Packaging Material Sampling Flow, FM-ES-001 : Internal Waste Log.'),(89,'QC-028E','Sample Transfer to Global Amneal Sites','QC-028E Sample Transfer to Global Amneal Sites.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Mark Quigley','Ashok Gulati, QC/ARD, Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-03-19','2025-03-19','QC-028D','Samples may include all the samples manufactured at Amneal Ireland or any other samples (e.g. Raw material, API, packaging, reference (innovator) product samples etc.) which have not been subjected to stability. Stability samples include Finished Goods that have been identified as being required to be placed on stability for the purposes of a specified protocol/procedure, Raw Materials that have been identified as being required to be placed on stability for the purposes of a specified protocol/procedure, Development samples manufactured at Amneal Ireland or any other samples (e.g. Raw material, API, Reference (innovator) product samples etc.) which have been subjected to various stability conditions.','SOP – Standard Operating Procedure, QC– Quality Control, ARD - Analytical Research and Development, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To provide a systematic approach to be followed for submission of samples to Amneal Quality Control (QC) and/or Amneal Analytical Research and Development (ARD) and /or Amneal Microbiology Departments globally for testing and analysis.','This SOP is applicable for the submission of the samples to an Amneal Global QC/ARD Laboratory/Microbiology Laboratory by Amneal, Ireland for testing or analysis, including but not limited to Raw materials, Packaging development batches, engineering batches, exhibit batches, IMP batches and Commercial batches at Amneal Ireland.','Amneal Ireland QC/ARD Personnel are responsible for submission of samples to an Amneal Global QC/ARD Laboratory/Microbiology Laboratory for testing and analysis. The Laboratory Manager, Amneal Ireland QC/ARD is responsible for compliance to this SOP.','Revision: QC-028, Date: 14-Sep-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-028A, Date: 27-May-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-081 AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Transfer of Procedure onto new template, Logo Change in header, Section 1.1 Added “and /or Amneal Microbiology”, Section 2.1 Added “/Microbiology Laboratory”, Section 3.1 Added “/Microbiology Laboratory”, 5.1.1.2 Added “/Microbiology Laboratory”, 5.2.1.2 Added “/Microbiology Laboratory”, Minor formatting changes, Section 6.0 Include reference to MM-011 Courier Shipments. Revision: QC-028B, Date: 20-May-2022, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140 CC-AMN-22-2713, Reason: Section 2.1 – included IMP batches and commercial batches in scope of SOP, Section 5.1.1.1 revised to read “Collect a representative sample of the product/material and apply relevant labels as per the relevant sampling SOP.”, New section 5.1.1.2 included to state “Samples are submitted to the lab as per MF-042, Procedure for Sample Movement/ Management for all GMP samples and MF-020, Product Development Sample Analysis Request.”, New section 5.1.1.3 included to state “Samples are received into the QC/ARD Lab as per QC-009, Receipt and Handling of incoming samples in the QC/ARD and Microbiology Laboratory”, Section 5.1.1.4 updated to remove reference to Appendix I, Section 5.2.1 updated to include the following for stability samples - Finished Goods that have been identified as being required to be placed on stability for the purposes of a specified protocol/procedure - Raw Materials that have been identified as being required to be placed on stability for the purposes of a specified protocol/procedure, Section 5.2.1.1 revised to state “Collect a representative sample of the product /material and apply the relevant label in accordance with the requirement of MF-020 and/or QC-091 as applicable”, Section 6.1 – removed Appendix I from reference to FM-QC-039, Removed section 6.3 reference to FM-MF-026, Product Development Sample for Analysis Label”, New section 6.4 included for reference to QC-091, Inhalation Drug Product Stability Testing Program, New section 6.5 included for reference to MF-042, Procedure for Sample Movement/ Management, New section 6.6 included for reference to QC-009, Receipt and Handling of Incoming Samples in the QC/ARD and Microbiology Laboratory, FM-QC-039-00 updated to FM-QC-039-01 to change logo in header update to new form format Layout of form changed to make it more user friendly. Revision: QC-028C, Date: 19-Jul-2022, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-3966, Reason: Section 5.1.1.5 added to include the instruction that only pre-siliconized seats and gaskets for AIPM-0001A extractable testing. Revision: QC-028D, Date: 15-Jun-2023, CCF No.: CC-AMN-23-2974, Reason: FM-QC-039-01 updated to FM-QC-039-02 to include footnote 1 - Note: Pre-siliconized seats / gaskets shall be used for extractable testing of component parts of AIPM-0001A valves. Revision: QC-028E, Date: 19-Mar-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-24-1412, Reason: Add section 5.1.1.5 and add section 5.2.1.3 to state “Ensure that relevant AVL has been checked to ensure that the samples are being sent to the correct qualified laboratory for all Drug Product samples.” Renumber subsequent sections accordingly, Revise FM-QC-039-02 to FM-QC-039-03 to include checks for newly added procedure requirements in section 5.1.1.5 and 5.2.1.3, Section 5.1.1.4 updated to read as follow: Note: For Raw Materials and Packaging Materials prior to shipping ensure that vendor batch details are checked to match the details of the sampling reports FM-QC-258 and FM-QC-034, Section 5.2.1 updated to read as follows: Note: For Raw Materials and Packaging Materials prior to shipping ensure that vendor batch details are checked to match the details of the sampling reports FM-QC-258 and FM-QC-034, Reference section updated to include QC-002, QC-027, FM-QC-034 and FM-QC-258.','FM-QC-039 : QC/ARD Test Request Form, MF-020 : Product Development Sample Analysis Request, MM-011 : Courier Shipments, QC-091 : Inhalation Drug Product Stability Testing Program, MF-042 : Procedure for Sample Movement/ Management, QC-009 : Receipt and Handling of Incoming Samples in the QC/ARD and Microbiology Laboratory, QC-002 : Sampling of Raw Materials at Amneal Ireland, FM-QC-034 : Raw Material Sampling Report, QC-027 : Sampling of Incoming Packaging Materials, FM-QC-258 : Raw Material Sampling Request.'),(90,'QC-029B','Gowning Procedure for QC/ARD Laboratory Entry','QC-029B Gowning Procedure for QC-ARD Laboratory Entry.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD','Brigid Hayes, QC/ARD, Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-03-19','2025-03-19','QC-029A','Only trained and authorised personnel are permitted to enter the QC/ARD Laboratory. Contractors and visitors must be escorted by authorised personnel at all times and strictly adhere to the gowning procedures. Safety shoes are not required for accompanied visitors who will not be working in the area, but safety shoes must be worn by Amneal personnel and contractors. Proper gowning is required to maintain the purity and integrity of our products as well as ensuring the safety of our employees and visitors. Gowning procedures must be followed in GMP areas at all times.','SOP: Standard Operating Procedure, cGMP: current Good Manufacturing Practices, PPE: Personal Protective Equipment, MSDS: Material Safety Data Sheet, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To outline the gowning requirements and employee responsibilities when entering or exiting the QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal Ireland.','This Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is applicable to all employees, contractors and visitors entering the QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal Ireland.','It is the responsibility of all Amneal personnel, visitors and contractors, when entering & exiting the QC/ARD Laboratory, to adhere to the practices outlined in this procedure. It is the responsibility of the QC/ARD laboratory manager to ensure that correct gowning PPE (Personal Protective Equipment) is available at all times, and that all employees, contractors and visitors are in compliance with this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP).','Revision: QC-029, Date: 16-Sep-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-029A, Date: 22-Dec-2016, CCF No.: AI-CC-16-015, Reason: Section 5.3: Gowning practice for testing within the QC/ARD Laboratory will now read \"Laboratory coat, glasses, safety shoes and laboratory gloves\". Reference Appendix I, FM-QC-065, “Gowning Pictorial for QC/ARD Laboratory Entry” for pictorial illustrating the correct way to gown\". The pictorial showing the correct way to gown will be included as a form and will be a new Appendix I to the SOP. Reference FM-QC-065, “Gowning Pictorial for QC/ARD Laboratory Entry”. Revision: QC-029B, Date: 19-Mar-2024, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-19-129, Reason: Updated SOP logo and removed reference to Appendix throughout. Section 5.2.4 Updated to: Safety shoes must be worn by All Amneal Staff and Contractors that are working within the QC/ARD Laboratory. Safety shoes are not required for accompanied visitors as per 5.1.2.','FM-QC-065 : Gowning Pictorial for QC/ARD Laboratory Entry.'),(91,'QC-030C','Operation and Maintenance of Agilent GC System (7890B), ALS (7693) and Headspace Sampler (7697A)','QC-030C Operation and Maintenance of GC System.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','David Ryan, QC/ARD','Paul O\'Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2020-10-19','2023-10-15','QC-030B','The Agilent GC System consists of the Agilent 7890B Series Gas Chromatograph (7693A automatic Liquid Sampler) and the Agilent 7697A Headspace sampler. The procedure includes steps for installing a GC column, setting gas flow, igniting the GC FID, setting up the 7697A Headspace sampler, and performing maintenance and calibration.','GC: Gas Chromatograph, Chromatography in which the sample mixture is vaporized and injected into a stream of carrier gas moving through a column containing a stationary phase composed of a liquid or particulate solid and is separated into its component compounds according to their affinity for the stationary phase, FID: Flame Ionization Detector, RT: Retention Time, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To define the procedure for the operation and maintenance of Agilent 7890B Series Gas Chromatograph (7693A automatic Liquid Sampler) and Agilent 7697A Headspace sampler.','This procedure applies to the Quality Control and Analytical Research & Development (QC/ARD) Laboratory at Amneal, Ireland.','The QC/ARD personnel are responsible for complying with the requirements of this procedure. The Laboratory Manager is responsible for ensuring that QC/ARD personnel comply with this procedure.','Revision: QC-030, Date: 30-Sep-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-030A, Date: 25-Sep-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-19-112, Reason: Updated SOP to new format and removed reference to Appendix throughout. Section 1.1 Change 7890N to 7890B and include reference to 7693A automatic Liquid Sampler. Section 5.4.3. Change Senior Chemist to QC / ARD Manager. Section 5.6.1 – Include following setup checks. For Head Space- ensure all sample trays are positioned properly and respective green lights are on. Press the button marked Tray Park/Carousel Advance on Head Space to check free movement and ensure this is kept in unparked position before starting the sample sequence. For liquid Injections, make sure enough vials with sufficient wash and rinse solutions and empty vials for waste collection are kept. Ensure all sample trays are positioned properly and respective green lights are on. Press the button marked P on Auto-sampler to check free movement and ensure it is kept in unparked position before starting sample sequence. Section 5.6.2 - include reference to 7693A automatic Liquid Sampler. Revision: QC-030B, Date: 19-Aug-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-069, Reason: Section 5.6.3 – Removed the requirement for steam cleaning to be carried out as part of the Annual Preventive Maintenance on the 7697A Headspace Sampler. Revision: QC-030C, Date: 19-Oct-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-090, Reason: Corrected Title of SOP by adding Model No. 7693 for Automated Liquid Sampler. Section 5.6.1- Added the requirement for checking the free movement of Plunger in syringe before starting sample sequence using ALS injector. Inserted the picture for clarification of Pre-check. Section 5.6.3 Corrected model No. of Head Space Sampler as 7697A.','FM-QC-046 : GC Usage Logbook, FM-QC-047 : GC Maintenance Logbook, QC-022 : Control of Laboratory Instruments, QC-021 : Operation of Empower, FM-QC-029 : Repair Request Form.'),(92,'QC-031B','Release of Material for Equipment Performance Qualification Studies','QC-031B Release of Material For Equipment Performance Qualification Studies.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Ashok Gulati, QC/ARD','Brigid Hayes, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2023-01-01','2024-01-01','QC-031A','Warehouse personnel must alert QC/ARD that a Material Request has been created for a PQ batch and issue the Form FM-QC-033 “Material Release for PQ study. Warehouse may not release material to Manufacturing until the Material Release for PQ study form is attached. QC/ARD personnel must review the Material Release for PQ Study request and approve or reject each line item requested on the form in line with the following guidance: API may be released for Equipment PQ batches based on verification of a Certificate of Analysis or Certificate of Conformance from the vendor, external test laboratory or Amneal QC/ARD Laboratory. API assay reporting sheet will be shared with manufacturing for the dispensing of API. A hard copy of the Certificate may be attached to the Material Release for Equipment PQ form. Excipients may be released for Equipment PQ batches based on verification of the Certificate of Analysis or Certificate of Conformance from the Vendor, External Test laboratory or Amneal QC/ARD Laboratory. A hard copy of the Certificate may be attached to the Material Release for Equipment PQ form. Primary packaging materials may be released for Equipment PQ batches based on verification of the Certificate of Analysis or Certificate of Conformance from the Vendor, External Test laboratory or Amneal QC/ARD Laboratory. A hard copy of the Certificate may be attached to the Material Release for Equipment PQ form. Secondary packaging materials may be released for Equipment PQ batches based on verification of the Certificate of Analysis or Certificate of Conformance from the Vendor, External Test laboratory or Amneal QC/ARD Laboratory. A hard copy of the Certificate may be attached to the Material Release for Equipment PQ form. QC/ARD personnel return the completed Material Release for Equipment PQ study form to the warehouse indicating which materials are approved and/or rejected. Approved materials will be labelled using FM-QC-045.','COA: Certificate of Analysis, QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research & Development, Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland.','To define the procedure when releasing material for Equipment Performance Qualification (PQ) studies.','This procedure applies to the release of materials for Equipment PQ studies at Amneal Ireland.','It is the responsibility of all personnel releasing materials for Equipment PQ studies to strictly adhere to this procedure. It is the responsibility of the Laboratory manager (or designee) to release material for Equipment PQ batches in accordance with this procedure. It is the responsibility of warehouse personnel to the transfer of materials and ensuring that all associated paperwork and labelling is completed correctly. It is the responsibility of Manufacturing personnel to request material needed for Equipment PQ studies from the Warehouse.','Revision: QC-031, Date: 03-Oct-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-031A, Date: 23-Nov-2016, CCF No.: AI-CC-16-007, Reason: Updated step 5.2.1 to read - API may be released for Equipment PQ batches based on verification of a Certificate of Analysis or Certificate of Conformance from the vendor, external test laboratory or Amneal QC/ARD Laboratory. API assay reporting sheet will be shared with manufacturing for the dispensing of API. Revision: QC-031B, Date: 2023-01-01, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Removed from step 5.2.2, 5.2.3, 5.2.4 – in Piscataway. Editorial correction to section 6.0 References - FM-QC-033 and FM-QC-045. Editorial correction to header page 2 and page 3 – added ‘equipment’. Updated SOP to new format & removed reference to Appendix throughout. Updated forms.','FM-QC-033 : Material Release for Equipment PQ Study, FM-QC-045 : Released Material for Equipment PQ Study Label.'),(93,'QC-032D','Analytical Method Transfer Process','QC-032D Analytical Method Transfer Process.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Katherine Russell — Katharina Russell, QC/ARD, David Ryan — David Ryan, QC/ARD','Andrew Clark — Katharina Russell, QC/ARD, Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-05-02','2027-05-02','QC-032C','The transfer of analytical test methods can be demonstrated through comparative testing, co-validation, revalidation, or transfer waiver. A risk analysis is required to determine the extent of transfer activities. The transfer protocol must detail the testing required, including objectives, scope, responsibilities, materials, instruments, experimental design, and acceptance criteria. The transfer report must document the results, deviations, and conclusions of the transfer process. Microbiology methods are adopted from USP/EU compendia, and only verification by the RL is required.','QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research & Development/Microbiology. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. Originating / Transferring Laboratory (OL / TL): Laboratory from which the Validated Analytical Test Method is being transferred. Receiving Laboratory (RL): Laboratory to which the Validated Analytical Test Method is being transferred. Analytical Test method: A procedure which describes in detail the steps necessary to perform an analytical test. Compendial Method: A method described in the current pharmacopeia of the region where the product will be marketed. Intermediate Precision/Ruggedness: An expression of laboratory variation. Limit Test: A test procedure that verifies that an analyte of interest is present below a pre-set threshold. Linearity: The ability to provide test results directly proportional to the concentration of an analyte. Method Validation: The process of demonstrating that analytical procedures are suitable for their intended use. Method Verification: The process of establishing the ability of a compendial or non-compendial method to meet the requirements of its intended application. Non-Compendia Method: A method not taken from a compendial Monograph. Precision: The closeness of agreement between a series of measurements. Quantitation Limit: The lowest amount of analyte in a sample which can be quantitively determined. Solution Stability: The stability of both the sample and the reference standard solution. Specificity: The ability of a method to unequivocally determine the analyte of interest in the presence of other components. System Suitability: Tests ensure that the complete testing system is in a controlled state. Bracketing: An experimental design to test only the extremes of dosage strength. Inter-laboratory Transfer: A transfer of methods between sites of different companies. Intra-laboratory Transfer: A transfer of methods between sites of the same group of companies or subsidiaries. Starting Materials: Any substance used in the production of a medicinal product. Robustness: The capacity of an analytical procedure to remain unaffected by small but deliberate variations in procedural parameters. Accuracy: The closeness of test results obtained by that procedure to the true value. Range: The interval between the upper and lower levels of analyte that have been demonstrated to be determined with precision, accuracy, and linearity. Detection Limit: The lowest amount of analyte in a sample that can be detected.','To define the procedure for the transfer of Analytical Test Methods to the QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal Ireland.','This procedure applies to the transfer of Analytical Test Methods where the QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal Ireland is deemed the ‘receiving laboratory’ (RL). This SOP describes requirements for inter-laboratory and intra-laboratory transfer of validated analytical procedures. Microbiology methods at Amneal Ireland are adopted from the USP/EU compendia. Verification is required only by the RL therefore Method transfer of Microbiology methods is not applicable.','QC/ARD personnel are responsible for ensuring compliance with the procedure. The Laboratory Manager oversees the transfer process. The transferring laboratory (TL) must provide the validated analytical procedure, reference standards, validation reports, and necessary documentation. The receiving laboratory (RL) must ensure that personnel, facilities, and instrumentation are qualified and compliant with regulations.','Revision: QC-032, Date: 04-Oct-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-032A, Date: 02-Oct-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-19-117, Reason: Updated SOP to new format, clarified responsibilities, aligned definitions with ICH Q2R1, and added detail on transfer approaches. Revision: QC-032B, Date: 11-Mar-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-022, Reason: Updated responsibilities and definitions to align with GQS_0037, restructured sections for clarity, and added pre-transfer and post-transfer checklists. Revision: QC-032C, Date: 03-Dec-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-095, Reason: Updated reference standard requirements and checklist. Revision: QC-032D, Date: 02-May-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-6778, Reason: Added new section 2.2, updated definitions, and made general editorial changes.','FM-QC-048 : Analytical Test Method Transfer Pre-Requisites Form. FM-QC-266 : Pre-Analytical Test Method Transfer Checklist. FM-QC-267 : Post Analytical Test Method Transfer Checklist. EudraLex: Volume 4 EU Guidelines for Good Manufacturing Practice for Medicinal Products for Human and Veterinary Use Part 1 Chapter 6: Quality Control. USP General Chapter, <1224> Transfer of Analytical Procedures. USP General Chapter, <1225> Validation of Compendial Procedures. USP General Chapter, <1226> Verification of Compendial Procedures. QC-105: Suitability of Test Methods Examination. International conference on Harmonisation (ICH) Harmonised Tripartite Guideline, Validation of Analytical Procedures: Text and Methodology – Q2 (R1). GQS_0037 : Global Standard for Analytical Method Transfer.'),(94,'QC-033H','Operation, Maintenance, Cleaning and Calibration of Weigh Balances in the QC/ARD Laboratory','QC-033H Op, Main, Clean & Cal of Weigh Balance in the QC Lab.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Agnieszka Lagocka, QC/ARD, David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-10-08','2027-10-01','QC-033G','Analytical balances should be left powered on during normal operations. Daily verification checks and internal calibration are required before use. Calibration weights must be handled with care and sent for annual external calibration. Ionizer Fan and Pen are used to minimize static charge during weighing. Calibration includes linearity, eccentricity, repeatability, sensitivity, accuracy, and minimum weight tests.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development. Calibration Range: Specified Range over which the balance is calibrated. cGMP: Current Good Manufacturing Practices. IPA: Isopropyl alcohol.','This procedure describes the procedures for the operation, cleaning, internal calibration, and maintenance of analytical balances.','This SOP applies to all balances and/or weighing instruments used in the Quality Control /Analytical Research and Development (QC/ARD) Laboratories at Amneal Ireland. Calibration policy in the QC/ARD Laboratory is defined in SOP QM-007 (Calibration Policy) with instrument categorisation being defined in SOP QC-022 (Control of Laboratory Instruments).','QC/ARD personnel are responsible for following this procedure and ensuring they are trained on the current revision. The Laboratory Manager ensures compliance and training. QA/Validation Department approves all calibration certificates for QC/ARD analytical balances.','Revision: QC-033, Date: 03-Oct-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-033A, Date: 28-Apr-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-015, Reason: Amend linearity specification, divide form FM-QC-049, add internal calibration instruction. Revision: QC-033B, Date: 02-May-18, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-037, Reason: Amend daily verification check, remove internal calibration before use, add balance activity logbook. Revision: QC-033C, Date: 31-Oct-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-120, Reason: Add requirement to report warning lights, amend calibration procedure. Revision: QC-033D, Date: 26-May-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-20-038, Reason: Update SOP template, add Ionizer Fan and Pen instructions. Revision: QC-033E, Date: 15-Feb-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-006, Reason: Update balance leveling and Ionizer instructions. Revision: QC-033F, Date: 23-May-2022, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-2811, Reason: Update calibration date verification. Revision: QC-033G, Date: 22-Aug-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-24-4504, Reason: Update tare weight instructions. Revision: QC-033H, Date: 03-Oct-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-24-5439, Reason: Add weight selection tables, update form FM-QC-136.','FM-QC-074 : Calibration Weight Details. FM-QC-050 : Balance Activity Logbook Form. FM-QC-049 : Before Use Verification Check. FM-QC-136 : Calibration Certificate for QC/ARD Analytical Balance. Sartorius Cubis Series Operating Manual. United States Pharmacopeial (USP). SOP QC-046 : Analyst Qualification in the QC/ARD Laboratory. SOP QM-007 : Calibration Policy. SOP QC-022 : Control of Laboratory Instruments. SOP QM-010 : Investigation System. SOP QC-067 : General Laboratory Practices in QC/ARD. SOP QC-086 : Handling of Laboratory Incidents in the QC/ARD and Microbiology Laboratories.'),(95,'QC-034F','Management of QC/ARD Specifications, Analytical Methods (Procedures) and Method Transfer Protocols','QC-034F Mgt of QC Specs Analytical methods & MTPs.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Katherine Russell, David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-05-23','2027-05-31','QC-034E','This SOP provides a systematic approach for managing QC/ARD specifications, analytical methods, and method transfer protocols. It covers the receipt, logging, distribution, and control of documents from both internal and external laboratories. Microbiology methods are adopted from USP/EU compendia, and only verification by the testing lab is required. The procedure also includes the management of Analytical Method Worksheets (AMWs) and Microbiology Laboratory Worksheets (MLWs).','QC: Quality Control/Microbiology. QA: Quality Assurance. ARD: Analytical Research and Development. RM: Raw Material. PM: Packaging Material. FP: Finished Product. PD: Product Development. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. Contract Laboratory Requirement (CLR): A version-controlled document detailing the procedure for a validated Test Method. TRSF: Test Request Submission Form. QUMAS: An electronic document management system. External Contract Laboratory: A Contract Laboratory not within the Amneal group.','To provide a systematic approach for the management of QC/ARD specifications, analytical methods (procedures), and method transfer protocols, both in hard copy and electronic copy.','This procedure applies to all specifications, analytical methods, and method transfer protocols received by Amneal Ireland from internal and external laboratories. It covers raw materials, packaging materials, in-process products, finished products, stability, and other miscellaneous items. Microbiology methods are adopted from USP/EU compendia, and only verification by the testing lab is required.','The QA documentation person is responsible for providing controlled copies of documents. The Laboratory Manager ensures controlled copies are maintained. QC/ARD Micro personnel receive and forward Micro documents from external contract laboratories. QA documentation provides controlled copies of Micro documents from external contract laboratories.','Revision: QC-034, Date: 06-Jan-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-034A, Date: 25-Nov-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-103, Reason: Updated sections 2.2, 4, and 5.3, added definitions for CSS and ARF. Revision: QC-034B, Date: 02-May-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-19-054, Reason: Updated sections 2.1.1, 2.1.2, 3.1, 3.2, 4.11, 5.1.1, 5.1.6, and references. Revision: QC-034C, Date: 16-May-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-081, Reason: Added new sections 2.1.2, 2.1.4, 3.3, 3.4, 4.9, 4.10, 4.12, 5.1.1, 5.1.2, 5.3, 5.3.1, 5.3.2, 5.3.3, 5.3.4, and updated references. Revision: QC-034D, Date: 11-Mar-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-022, Reason: Updated sections 5.1.1, 5.2.3, added section 5.5, updated references, and created new form FM-QC-268. Revision: QC-034E, Date: 09-Aug-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-062, Reason: Added section 5.6 for reference copies of Analytical Methods. Revision: QC-034F, Date: 23-Oct-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-6778, Reason: Updated sections 2.1.3, 2.1.4, 2.1.5, 2.2, 4.1, 4.10, 5.1.5, 5.1.6, 5.1.7, added section 5.3, renumbered sections 5.3-5.7, updated sections 5.4.2.1, 5.4.2.2, 5.4.2.3, 5.4.2.4, added section 5.8, and updated references.','FM-QC-062 : Log of Laboratory Documents Received into Amneal Ireland from another Amneal Laboratory. FM-QC-063 : QC/ARD Specification/Analytical method (procedure) Distribution Form. FM-QC-194 : Log of Documents received into the QC/ARD Laboratory (Amneal Ireland) from External Contract Laboratories. QA-001 : Procedure for Document Issuance. QM-003 : Training System. QM-004 : Good Documentation Practices. QM-013 : Change Control System. FM-QM-003 : Controlled Document Request. QM-002 : Control of revision-controlled documents. QC-032 : Analytical Method Transfer Process. QM-009 : Document Storage and Retention. FM-QC-268 : Analytical Method Worksheet. QC-104 : Microbial Enumeration and Test for Specified Microorganisms of Non-Sterile Products and Materials. QC-105 : Suitability of Test Methods Examination.'),(96,'QC-037B','Operation, Maintenance and Calibration of Cary 630 FT-IR Spectrophotometer','QC-037B Operation, Maintenance & Calibration of Cary 630 FTIR.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Ashok Gulati, QC/ARD','Mary White, QA','Mary White, QA','2023-11-07','2025-11-06','QC-037A','This SOP defines the procedure for operating, maintaining, and calibrating the Agilent Cary 630 FTIR Spectrometer. It includes instructions for turning on/off the instrument, system suitability checks, sample measurement, and maintenance tasks such as cleaning and desiccant replacement. Preventative maintenance and calibration are performed annually.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. QC/ARD: Quality Control / Analytical Research and Development. FTIR spectroscopy: Fourier Transform Infra-red spectroscopy. LED: Light Emitting Diode. ATR: Attenuated Total Reflectance. KBr: potassium bromide. ZnSe: zinc selenide. PC: personal computer.','To define the procedure for the operation, maintenance, and calibration of the Agilent Cary 630 FTIR Spectrometer.','The procedure applies to the Quality Control and Analytical Research and Development (QC/ARD) Laboratory at Amneal Ireland.','All QC/ARD personnel must adhere to the SOP and ensure they are trained on the current revision. The Laboratory Manager ensures compliance and training.','Revision: QC-037, Date: 20-Dec-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First issued. Revision: QC-037A, Date: 12-Dec-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated SOP logo and removed reference to Appendix. Revision: QC-037B, Date: 07-Nov-2023, CCF No.: CC-AMN-23-6184, Reason: Added section 5.2.3.12 for printing and comparing overlay spectra for sample and standard.','FM-QC-054 : Instrument Usage Logbook. Agilent Cary 630 FTIR Spectrometer User’s Guide (Agilent Technologies).'),(97,'QC-038C','Validation of In-House Analytical Procedures and Verification of Compendial Procedures','QC-038C Val of IN-House Analytical Procedures and Verifications of Compendial Procedures.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Linda Bannon, QC/ARD, Katherine Russell, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2023-10-13','2026-10-17','QC-038B','This SOP describes the policy and procedure for the validation of in-house analytical methods and the verification of compendial methods. It includes guidance for validation/verification of analytical procedures such as HPLC, GC, IR, UV-Visible spectrophotometry, titrimetry, drug release, and qualitative tests. The SOP also covers the verification of existing validated methods or compendial methods when modified.','Analytical procedure/method: The way of performing the analysis. Stability indicating method: A product-specific method used to determine conformance to stability specifications. Placebo: A dosage form matrix without the analyte(s). Accuracy: Closeness of test results to the true value. Precision: Closeness of agreement between a series of measurements. Repeatability: Precision within the same laboratory over a short period. Intermediate Precision / Ruggedness: Within-laboratory variations. Reproducibility: Precision between laboratories. Linearity: Proportionality between concentration and response. Range: Interval between upper and lower analyte levels. Detection Limit (DL): Lowest amount of analyte that can be detected. Quantitation Limit (QL): Lowest amount of analyte that can be quantified. Robustness: Method’s capacity to remain unaffected by variations. Specificity: Ability to assess analyte unequivocally. Validation: Process of establishing method performance characteristics. Method verification: Evidence that a method fulfills specified requirements. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. ARD: Analytical Research and Development.','To describe the policy and procedure for the validation of in-house analytical methods and the verification of compendial methods. It also covers the verification of existing validated methods or compendial methods when modified.','This SOP applies to personnel in the QC/ARD laboratories at Amneal Ireland. It covers validation/verification of analytical procedures including HPLC, GC, IR, UV-Visible spectrophotometry, titrimetry, drug release, and qualitative tests. Verification of microbial compendial methods is completed as per SOP QC-105.','The Laboratory Manager ensures compliance with this procedure and that all QC/ARD personnel are trained. QC/ARD personnel must follow this procedure and ensure they are trained on the current revision.','Revision: QC-038, Date: 10-Feb-2017, CCF No.: N/A, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-038A, Date: 06-Feb-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated to new logo and SOP template, added verification of compendial methods as per USP <1226>, removed section 5.13. Revision: QC-038B, Date: 05-Jul-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-044, Reason: Added section 5.13 (Life Cycle Management), added references to GQS_0013, QC-086, and QM-019, formatting changes. Revision: QC-038C, Date: 16-Oct-2023, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-6778, Reason: Added section 2.3, updated section 5.2 with note on microbiological procedures, added reference to QC-105.','International Conference on Harmonisation (ICH) Harmonised Tripartite Guideline: Validation of Analytical Procedures: Test and Methodology – Q2 (R1). United States Pharmacopeia (USP) section <1225>: Validation of compendial methods. United States Pharmacopeia (USP) section <1226>: Verification of compendial procedures. ORA Laboratory Procedures, Food and Drug Administration Document No.: ORA-LAB 5.4.5 Title: Methods, Method Verification and Method Validation. GQS_0013, Validation and Verification of Analytical Procedures. QC-086: Handling of Laboratory Incidents in the QC/ARD and Microbiology Laboratories. QM-019: Management Review of the Quality System. QC-105: Suitability of Test Methods Examination.'),(98,'QC-039F','Sampling Procedure for Ethanol','QC-039F  Sampling Procedure for Ethanol.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','David Ryan, QC/ARD, Mariscal Ryan, QA','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-09-10','2026-09-10','QC-039E','This SOP defines the procedures and practices for sampling ethanol at Amneal Ireland. It includes requirements for area clearance, line sign-off, and sampling procedures. The SOP ensures that sampling is conducted safely and in compliance with regulatory standards, including the use of appropriate PPE and adherence to cleaning protocols.','PPE: Personal Protective Equipment. HDPE: High Density Polyethylene. ANSI: American National Standards Institute. COA: Certificate of Analysis. AR number: Analytical Receipt number. QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research & Development. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. IPA: Isopropyl Alcohol.','To define the procedures and practices for sampling ethanol at Amneal Ireland.','This procedure applies to all QC/ARD and QA personnel involved in the sampling of ethanol at Amneal Ireland.','All personnel performing sampling must adhere to this procedure, wear appropriate PPE, and report any deficiencies. QA personnel verify area clearance and line sign-off. QC/ARD personnel ensure cleaning and proper sampling procedures are followed.','Revision: QC-039, Date: 04-Nov-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-039A, Date: 25-Oct-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated SOP to new logo and removed reference to Appendix. Revision: QC-039B, Date: 29-Oct-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-082, Reason: Removed section 5.4.12 and retired FM-QC-058. Revision: QC-039C, Date: 08-Nov-2023, CCF No.: CC-AMN-23-6212, Reason: Updated as per US FDA guidance for testing ethanol and isopropyl alcohol for methanol. Revision: QC-039D, Date: 28-Feb-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-23-6551, Reason: Added sections 5.4.8.1 and 5.4.8.2 for sampling ethanol for cleaning and drug product manufacture. Revision: QC-039E, Date: 12-Jun-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-24-2914, Reason: Added QA responsibilities, updated sampling procedures, and added new forms FM-QC-339 and FM-QC-340. Revision: QC-039F, Date: 10-Sep-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-24-4804, Reason: Updated sampling requirements, added section 5.5.8.2, and made editorial changes.','FM-QC-056: Ethanol Sampling Report. FM-QC-057: Ethanol Sample Quantity List. FM-QC-059: QC/ARD Ethanol Sample for Analysis Label. MM-001: Receipt and Storage of Materials into the Warehouse. MM-011: Courier Shipments. QC-008: Labelling of Material, Equipment and Room. QC-028: Transfer of Samples to Global Amneal Sites. QC-061: General Requirements for XP-33 and Operation of XP-33 Sampling Booth. MF-009: Gowning Procedure for Entering and Exiting the Inhalation Areas. MF-007: Area Room Cleaning Requirements in the Inhalation Facility. FM-QC-339: Ethanol Sampling Area Sign-Off Form. FM-QC-340: Ethanol Sampling Area Clearance Form. QM-010: Unplanned Deviations and Investigations. MF-008: Labelling of Material, Product, Room and Equipment. ANSI/ASQ Z1.9. WHO Technical Report Series, No. 929, 2005 Annex 4. EudraLex Volume 4. US FDA guidance for Industry “Policy for Testing of Alcohol (Ethanol) and Isopropyl Alcohol for Methanol”. FM-MM-004: Material Stock Card. FM-MF-005: Under Test Label. MM-002: Movement of Material between the Warehouse and Manufacturing. QM-027: Retention Sample Management.'),(99,'QC-040A','API Assay Reporting Sheet Preparation for Dispensing','QC-040A API Assay Reporting Sheet Preperation SOP.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Brigid Hayes, QC/ARD','Ägnieszka Lagóčka, QC/ARD, Paul O’Mahofty, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2019-01-14','2023-01-13','QC-040','This SOP defines the procedure for the preparation, review, and communication of API assay reporting sheets for dispensing. It ensures that assay results are accurately compiled and communicated to Manufacturing (MF) or Product Development (PD) groups for reconciliation with the Batch Manufacturing Record.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. API: Active Pharmaceutical Ingredient. COA: Certificate of Analysis. QC/ARD: Quality Control Research and Development.','To define the procedure for API assay reporting sheet preparation, review, and communication.','This procedure applies to all API tested by QC/ARD at Amneal Ireland.','QC/ARD Department is responsible for preparing, compiling, and reviewing assay results. QC/ARD personnel must follow this procedure and ensure they are trained on the current revision. The QC/ARD Manager ensures compliance.','Revision: QC-040, Date: 22-Nov-2016, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-040A, Date: 14-Jan-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140 AI-CC-19-125, Reason: Updated SOP to new format, added sections 3.2, 3.3, 3.4, 4.2, 4.3, 4.4, updated section 5.1, added COA to section 5.2, removed section 5.4, and retired FM-QC-037-00.','FM-QC-055: API Assay Reporting Form for dispensing.'),(100,'QC-042H','Procedure for Approval/Rejection of Raw Material/Packaging Material and Quality Impacting Miscellaneous Supplies','QC-042H Procedure for Approval-Rejection of RM PM.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Karen Barry, QC/ARD; Katherina Russell, QC/ARD; David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-05-14','2027-05-14','QC-042G','Testing of raw materials, packaging materials, and Quality Impacting Miscellaneous Supplies (MS) as per Compendial monographs or approved specifications. Secondary and tertiary packaging materials can be approved based on verification with approved artwork or documentation. High-risk drug components require specific testing for Diethylene Glycol (DEG) and Ethylene Glycol (EG). COA (Certificate of Analysis) must be prepared and reviewed for accuracy. Materials are labeled as \"APPROVED\" or \"REJECTED\" based on test results.','GRN: Goods Receipt Note, COA: Certificate of Analysis, COC: Certificate of Conformance, COV: Certificate of Verification, RM/PM: Raw Materials/Packaging Materials, SOP: Standard Operating Procedure, LNB: Laboratory Note Book, LAW: Laboratory Analytical Worksheet, MS: Miscellaneous Supplies, EG: Ethylene Glycol, DEG: Diethylene Glycol, High-Risk Drug Components: Components at higher risk of DEG or EG contamination, MLW: Microbiology Laboratory Worksheet, QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development/Microbiology.','To provide the procedure for approving/rejecting raw materials, packaging materials, and Quality Impacting Miscellaneous Supplies (MS) that require testing, including materials for initial release, re-testing, or materials under stability.','This procedure applies to the approval and rejection of all raw materials, packaging materials, and Quality Impacting Miscellaneous Supplies (MS) that require testing by Quality Control (QC), Analytical Research and Development (ARD), and Microbiology departments of Amneal Ireland.','It is the responsibility of all QC/ARD personnel to follow this procedure. The laboratory manager/designee ensures adherence to the procedure. QC/ARD personnel are responsible for testing, reviewing, and approving/rejecting materials based on specifications. QA must approve any deviations or investigations related to batch/lot testing.','Revision: QC-042, Date: 08-Jan-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-042A, Date: 14-Apr-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-026, Reason: Added text for secondary packaging and tertiary packaging. Revision: QC-042B, Date: 24-Nov-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-102, Reason: Updated Master COA revision process. Revision: QC-042C, Date: 02-Aug-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-078, Reason: Updated title and scope, added definitions for MS. Revision: QC-042D, Date: 26-Nov-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-132, Reason: Updated references and testing procedures. Revision: QC-042E, Date: 02-Jul-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-044, Reason: Updated SOP format and references. Revision: QC-042F, Date: 28-Nov-2023, CCF No.: CC-AMN-23-6401, Reason: Added sections for DEG/EG testing and FDA notification. Revision: QC-042G, Date: 20-Dec-2023, CCF No.: CC-AMN-23-6421, Reason: Added definitions for EG, DEG, and high-risk drug components. Revision: QC-042H, Date: 14-May-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-6778, Reason: Updated scope to include Microbiology department, added references to QC-104, QC-077, and QC-105.','FM-QC-064: Certificate of Analysis for Raw Material/Packaging Material, FM-QC-066: Certificate of Analysis (Master) Approval Page, QM-018: Vendor Notification of Quality Issues, MF-008: Labelling of Material, Product, and Equipment, MM-001: Receipt and Storage of Material, MM-004: Safe Behaviour in Warehouse, QM-013: Change Control System, QA-006: Procurement and Approval of Miscellaneous Supplies, QC-028: Sample Transfer to Global Amneal Sites, QC-038: Validation of Analytical Procedures, QC-049: Notification of Event from Contract Laboratories, QC-062: Expiration and Re-Test Dates, MM-011: Courier Shipments, MF-086: RF-Smart Labelling, FM-MF-034: Sample Test Request Form, QC-043: Release of Results from QC/ARD Laboratory, QC-046: Analyst Qualification, QC-006: Review of Laboratory Records, FM-QC-256: QC/ARD COA Issuance Log, MM-020: Offsite Storage Handling, QM-020: Drug Product Recall, QM-035: Quality Defect Reporting, QC-104: Microbial Enumeration, QC-105: Suitability of Test Methods, QC-083: Handling of Microbiology OOS Results, QC-108: Microbiology Laboratory Investigation, QC-077: Analyst Qualification in Microbiology, FDA Guidance on DEG/EG Testing.'),(101,'QC-043D','Release of Results from QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal Ireland','QC-043D Release of Results from QC-ARD Laboratory.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Katherine Russell, QC/ARD; David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-05-09','2027-05-09','QC-043C','QC/ARD COA shall be developed per material/product type using templates FM-QC-068 (Products/In Process) and FM-QC-064 (Raw Materials/Packaging Materials/MS). Master COA templates are prepared and approved using FM-QC-066. Results are reviewed against approved specifications, and COAs are issued after approval. Microbiology testing data is documented on MLW, and a Certificate of Analysis-Microbial Limits Test (FM-QC-337) is completed. Deviations/investigations must be approved by QA/QP before release or rejection.','COA: Certificate of Analysis, SOP: Standard Operating Procedure, LNB: Laboratory Notebook, LAW: Laboratory Analytical Worksheet, MLW: Microbiology Laboratory Worksheet, QP: Qualified Person, QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research & Development/Microbiology, Bracketing: Testing only the extremes of a range.','To document the procedure for the release of results and preparation of COA, where applicable, from QC/ARD laboratories at Amneal Ireland.','This procedure applies to the release of results and preparation of COA for Raw Materials, Packaging Materials, Quality Impacting Miscellaneous Supplies, In-process, and Finished Product tested by QC/ARD or third-party testing sites.','QC/ARD personnel are responsible for following the procedure. The Laboratory Manager/designee ensures adherence. The reviewer/designee reviews analytical data. The designated Laboratory person generates COAs, and the Laboratory Manager/designee approves them. QA/QP must approve any deviations or investigations.','Revision: QC-043, Date: 11-Jan-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-043A, Date: 31-May-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-044, Reason: Updated for third-party testing, added QP definition, and clarified COA storage. Revision: QC-043B, Date: 28-Feb-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-064, Reason: Updated SOP format, added QC/ARD definition, and references. Revision: QC-043C, Date: 02-Jul-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-044, Reason: Updated Master COA control, added batch COA revision instructions, and general clarifications. Revision: QC-043D, Date: 09-May-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-6778, Reason: Added MLW and Bracketing definitions, updated microbiology testing documentation, and general editorial changes.','FM-QC-068: Certificate of Analysis, FM-QC-066: Certificate of Analysis (Master) Approval Page, QM-013: Change Control System, QM-010: Investigation System, QC-001: Investigation of Out-of-Specification Laboratory Results, QC-049: Notification of Event from Contract Laboratories, QC-083: Handling of Microbiology OOS Results, QM-024: Management of Electronic Forms, QC-085: Investigation of Atypical Results, FM-MF-034: Sample Test Request Form, FM-QC-064: Certificate of Analysis for Raw Material/Packaging Material, FM-QC-256: QC/ARD COA Issuance Log, QC-006: Review of Laboratory Records, QC-104: Microbial Enumeration, QC-108: Microbiology Laboratory Investigation.'),(102,'QC-044F','Empower 3 Administration Procedure','QC-044F Empower3 Administration Procedure.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Derek Russell, IT; Paul O\'Mahony, QC','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2023-05-03','2026-08-03','QC-044E','Administration of Empower3 software includes creating/modifying groups, projects, users, and profiles. User access is managed with unique usernames and passwords. Projects are created, locked, and managed annually. System policies enforce GxP compliance, including audit trails and password complexity. Users are categorized as Chemist, Superuser, or Administrator, each with specific privileges. Data deletion is prohibited, and any inadvertent deletions are escalated during audit trail reviews.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development. IT: Information Technology. HOD: Head of Department. QA: Quality Assurance. SOP: Standard Operating Procedure. GxP: Good X Practice (FDA compliance).','To provide a systematic approach for the Administration of Empower3 Software at Amneal Ireland.','This SOP applies to the Administration of Empower3 software used in the QC/ARD Laboratories at Amneal Ireland. It includes creating/modifying groups, projects, users, and profiles. Disaster recovery, audit trail review, and operation of Empower3 are out of scope.','HOD or designee ensures users are trained. IT Empower3 Administrators manage user accounts, system policies, and escalate issues. QC/ARD Superusers and Chemists have specific roles in managing projects and data. QA/QP approves deviations/investigations.','Revision: QC-044, Date: 10-Jan-2017, CCF No.: N/A, Reason: New Document. Revision: QC-044A, Date: 22-Mar-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-021, Reason: Updated responsibilities and added references. Revision: QC-044B, Date: 21-May-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-045, Reason: Combined responsibilities and added Superuser/Chemist roles. Revision: QC-044C, Date: 30-Aug-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-093, Reason: Updated to Empower3, added GxP policies, and reorganized sections. Revision: QC-044D, Date: 21-Mar-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-19-031, Reason: Added user types and corrected system policies. Revision: QC-044E, Date: 07-May-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-044, Reason: Updated forms and references. Revision: QC-044F, Date: 03-May-2023, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-6778, Reason: Updated password policies, clarified roles, and added Chemist privileges.','FM-QC-121: Empower3 Project Request Form, FM-QC-150: Empower3 Software Activity Logbook, QC-066: Electronic Records and Audit Trails Review, QC-021: Operation of Empower Software, IT-011: Computer System Incident Management, IT-015: Empower3 and Instrument Server Data Backup, FM-IT-053: Access & Disable Electronic System Request Form, FM-IT-054: Log of User Access for Electronic Systems.'),(103,'QC-046G','Analyst Qualification in the QC/ARD Laboratory','QC-046G Analyst Qualification in the QC ARD Laboratory.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Sparkly Anchars, Sryanly Anchan, QC/ARD, David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldcep Joshi, QA','2024-09-16','2024-09-05','QC-046F','1. Induction and Site General Procedures for new analysts. 2. Chemistry Qualification Training programs include Site Induction, Core Laboratory Support Activities, and various Test Method Trainings. 3. Core Laboratory Support Activity Training covers Gowning, Laboratory GLP, Sample Management, Equipment Processes, and more. 4. Analytical Test Method Training includes MDI Assay, DPI Assay, MDI Alcohol testing, Water content testing, and Raw Material/Packaging Material testing. 5. Training Demo, Supervised, and Independent execution of test methods. 6. Acceptance criteria for qualification include system suitability, instrument performance, and method transfer criteria. 7. Re-Qualification and Qualification Waiver processes are outlined.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Ltd, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development. SOP: Standard Operating Procedure. OOS: Out of Specification. Instructor Led Training: Training event led by a qualified colleague. ST – Self Training: Read and understand procedure by trainee with subsequent competence assessment. CL – Classroom training: Trainee is trained to a procedure by a trained analyst with subsequent competence assessment.','To describe the procedure for Qualification of analysts to carry out Analytical Testing in the QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal Ireland.','This procedure is applicable to all QC/ARD personnel at Amneal Ireland and outlines the process for qualifying personnel to carry out analytical testing at Amneal Ireland.','1. The Laboratory Manager/designee is responsible for ensuring that QC/ARD personnel are trained to this SOP. 2. QC/ARD personnel carrying out Analytical Testing in the QC/ARD Laboratory are required to train and adhere to this SOP. 3. It is the responsibility of the trainee to ensure that all training qualification documentation is reviewed and approved prior to commencing live testing.','Revision: QC-046, Date: 31-May-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-046A, Date: 31-Aug-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-080, Reason: Section 5.1 amended for clarification. Added the word “adherence” to 5.4.1.2 for clarification. Added Instructor Led Training on relevant Equipment and Computer Systems SOPs. Revision: QC-046B, Date: 28-Aug-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated SOP and forms to new format. Revision: QC-046C, Date: 11-Mar-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-018, Reason: Added sections 3.3, 4.6, 4.7, and updated sections 5.1, 5.2, 5.3, 5.4, 5.5.1, 5.8.2, 5.8.4. Added new forms FM-QC-264 and FM-QC-265. Revision: QC-046D, Date: 24-Sep-2021, CCF No.: AIM-CC-21-016, AI-CC-21-069, Reason: Updated sections 5.2, 5.4, and FM-QC-264. Revision: QC-046E, Date: 03-Oct-2022, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-5402, Reason: Added statements in sections 5.3, 5.4, and updated FM-QC-078, FM-QC-264. Revision: QC-046F, Date: 26-Jan-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-4138, Reason: Updated FM-QC-264 to include new test methods. Revision: QC-046G, Date: 16-Sep-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-24-2759, Reason: Updated FM-QC-264 to include test methods for Allbutrol Sulfate Inhalation Aerosol.','FM-QC-078: Analyst Qualification/Requalification Form. FM-QC-088: General Laboratory Qualification Form. SOP QM-003: Training System. SOP HR-001: Employee Induction Program. SOP HR-003: Job Description. SOP QC-001: Investigation of Out-of-Specification (OOS) Laboratory Results. SOP QC-006: Review of Laboratory Records. FM-QC-264: Chemistry Analyst Qualification Training Program. FM-QC-265: Glass Pipette Certification.'),(104,'QC-049F','Notification of Event from Contract Laboratories to Amneal Ireland','QC-049F Notification of Event from Contract Lab.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','David Ryan, QC/ARD, Katharina Russell','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2023-10-04','2024-10-03','QC-049E','1. Procedure for handling Notification of Event (NOE) from contract laboratories. 2. Events include Out of Specification (OOS), Out of Trend (OOT), Atypical results, Unplanned Deviations (UD), CAPA, and Critical observations. 3. NOE is logged in FM-QC-082 and may progress to UD if necessary. 4. Contract laboratories must notify Amneal Ireland of any suspect results and conduct investigations. 5. Immediate actions, escalation, and QA assessment are required for NOE closure. 6. NOE details are included in monthly Quality Management Review meetings.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Ltd, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. NOE: Notification of Event. Event: Unexpected/OOS/OOT result or excursion in the Quality system of the Contract lab. UD: Unplanned Deviation. Exhibit Batch: Batch under GMP for process demonstration. IMP: Investigational Medicinal Product. PD: Product Development. PQ: Performance Qualification. PV: Process Validation. QA: Quality Assurance. QP: Qualified Person. Repeat: Verification test after lab error. Re-test: Test performed again using original/primary sample.','To describe the procedure following receipt of a Notification of Event (NOE) from Contract laboratories to Amneal Ireland associated with testing of any product manufactured at Amneal Ireland.','This procedure applies to events observed during contract testing of all batches manufactured at/for Amneal Ireland (i.e., chemical, microbiological, physical testing etc). It also applies to microbial test samples such as Environmental Monitoring, Compressed air, Surface Bioburden, and validation studies.','1. QC/ARD personnel are responsible for entering NOE notifications in FM-QC-082. 2. Laboratory Manager/Designee ensures training, notifies Head of Quality/QP, and assesses immediate actions. 3. Head of Quality/QP identifies actions, assesses impact, and approves NOE closure. 4. Investigation team completes actions, documents results, and establishes CAPA. 5. Contract Laboratory notifies Amneal Ireland of suspect results, conducts investigations, and completes repeat/re-testing as instructed.','Revision: QC-049, Date: 21-Mar-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-049A, Date: 16-Nov-2017, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-093, Reason: Updated sections 1, 2, 4, 5, and added definitions. Revision: QC-049B, Date: 28-Feb-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-064, AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated template, added new sections, and updated forms. Revision: QC-049C, Date: 30-May-19, CCF No.: AI-CC-19-075, AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated responsibilities, added NOE closure timelines, and updated forms. Revision: QC-049D, Date: 19-Sep-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-19-111, Reason: Updated responsibilities, added immediate actions, and updated forms. Revision: QC-049E, Date: 14-Sep-2022, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-5201, Reason: Updated sections, replaced NOI with UD, and updated forms. Revision: QC-049F, Date: 04-Oct-2023, CCF No.: CC-AMN-23-5282, Reason: Added NOE extension process and updated forms.','SOP QM-010: Unplanned Deviations & Investigations. FM-QC-082: Notification of Event from Contract Laboratory Form. FM-QC-083: Notification of Event from Contract Laboratory Log. FM-QC-107: Notification of Event Executive Summary. SOP QM-019: Management Responsibility and Management review of the Quality System. SOP QM-012: Corrective Action Preventative Action (CAPA). SOP QM-024: Management of Electronic Forms. SOP QM-013: Change Control System. SOP QC-083: Handling of Microbiology Out of Specification (OOS) Results. SOP QC-010: Recording and Reporting of Laboratory Data. QM-018: Vendor Notification Procedure. QM-030: Batch certification by a Qualified Person / Batch Release.'),(105,'QC-050C','Cleaning of Glassware at Amneal Ireland QC/ARD Laboratory','QC-050C Cleaning of Glassware at Amneal Ireland QC ARD Lab.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Cara Bergin, QC/ARD, Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2021-10-04','2021-10-03','QC-050B','1. Procedure for cleaning and storage of laboratory glassware and utensils. 2. Pre-cleaning involves rinsing with appropriate solvent before placing in dirty glassware containers. 3. New glassware must be cleaned as per instructions. 4. Large glass bottles (5000mL and greater) require specific cleaning steps with RBS 50 detergent. 5. Miele G 7883 glasswasher is used for cleaning, with pre-cleaning steps and specific loading instructions. 6. Alternative cleaning procedures are provided for temperature-sensitive items, small utensils, and pipettes. 7. Clean glassware must be stored separately from dirty glassware.','Laboratory Glassware: Any glass (e.g., beakers, volumetric flasks, pipettes). Utensils: Mobile phase reservoirs, spatulas, filtration devices, etc. RBS 50: Biodegradable detergent. Temperature Sensitive: Items damaged by temperatures >60°C. Purified Water: As defined in USP. Deionized Water: As defined in USP. Potable Water: Water fit for drinking. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. QC/ARD: Quality Control / Analytical Research and Development. PPE: Personal protective equipment.','To describe the procedures for the cleaning and storage of laboratory glassware and utensils in the Amneal Ireland QC/ARD Laboratory.','This procedure applies in the QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal, Ireland.','1. All QC/ARD personnel must comply with this procedure. 2. The Laboratory Manager ensures adherence to the procedure. 3. Any equipment problems must be reported immediately to the Laboratory Manager. 4. All personnel must be trained to the current revision of the SOP. 5. Appropriate PPE must be worn during washing.','Revision: QC-050, Date: 21-Mar-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-050A, Date: 12-Nov-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-121, Reason: Added definitions, updated cleaning instructions, and corrected grammatical errors. Revision: QC-050B, Date: 27-Jan-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-20-004, Reason: Updated definitions, pre-cleaning steps, and added new sections for cleaning procedures. Revision: QC-050C, Date: 04-Oct-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-083, Reason: Updated pre-cleaning steps, added alternative cleaning procedures for pipettes, and updated storage instructions.','Sigma Aldrich® Care and Safe Handling of Laboratory Glassware (recommended). Instrument Manual Operating Instructions Washer disinfector G7883 CD. FM-QC-243 “Glassware Washer Usage Logbook”.'),(106,'QC-052C','Sampling of Finished Product Sample and Stability Sample','QC-052C Sampling of FP Sample & Stability Sample.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','David Ryan, QC, Paul O\'Mahony, QC','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2022-06-03','2025-06-03','QC-052B','1. Procedure for sampling finished product and stability samples. 2. Sampling in the warehouse sampling area requires setting up partition walls and a folded table. 3. Area/Line Sign off (FM-QC-284) and Area/Line Clearance (FM-QC-285) are required before and after sampling. 4. Sampling during packaging operations requires representative samples from the start, middle, and end of the process. 5. Samples must be labeled and handled according to approved protocols and SOPs. 6. Gloves must be worn during sampling, and all waste must be disposed of properly. 7. Samples are sent to the QC lab or warehouse for shipment as per SOP MF-042.','FP: Finished Product. STAB: Stability. AR number: Analytical Receipt number (Amneal lot number). QC/ARD: Quality Control / Analytical Research Development. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. BMR: Batch manufacturing record. QA: Quality Assurance. SOP: Standard Operating Procedure. BPR: Batch Packaging Record. QP: Qualified Person. IPA: Isopropyl Alcohol.','To define the procedures and practices to be used for sampling of finished product and stability samples.','This procedure applies to all Quality personnel involved in sampling of finished product and stability samples at Amneal Ireland.','1. All Quality personnel performing sampling must adhere to this procedure. 2. Personnel must wear appropriate gowning and gloves during sampling. 3. QA/QC personnel are responsible for verifying area sign-off and clearance before and after sampling. 4. Sampling activities must be documented in the Equipment/Area/Batch Activity Logbook (FM-MF-029). 5. QA/QC personnel must ensure that all sampling equipment and labels are available and correct.','Revision: QC-052, Date: 05-May-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-052A, Date: 30-Apr-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, Reason: Updated Amneal logo. Revision: QC-052B, Date: 26-Nov-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-104, Reason: Added definitions, updated sampling steps, and added new points for sampling during packaging operations. Revision: QC-052C, Date: 03-Jun-2022, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-1975, Reason: Removed reference to SOP QC-061, updated gowning requirements, added area sign-off and clearance steps, and updated sampling procedures.','MF-042: Procedure for Sample movement/management. MM-011: Courier shipment. QC-009: Receipt & handling of incoming samples in the QC-ARD/Microbiology Lab. QM-027: Retention Sample Management. FM-MF-034: Sample Test Request Form. MM-012: Warehouse Cleaning Procedure. FM-QC-284: Finished Product / Stability Sampling Area Sign-Off Form for Warehouse Sampling Area. FM-QC-285: Finished Product / Stability Sampling Area Line Clearance Form for Warehouse Sampling Area. FM-MF-039: Area/Line Sign Off Form. MF-030: Area and Line Sign Off. FM-MF-029: Equipment/Area/Batch/Activity Logbook. MF-007: Area Room Cleaning Requirements in Inhalation Facility. FM-MF-173: Area/Line Clearance DPI Packaging Area. FM-MF-180: Area/Line Clearance MDI Packaging XP-01. MF-004: Post Area Line Clearance. MM-003: Garbing Procedure for Warehouse Entry. MF-009: Gowning Procedure for Entering and Exiting the Inhalation Areas.'),(107,'QC-053C','Operation, Maintenance and Qualification of Cary 60 UV-Visible Spectrophotometer','QC-053C Operation, Maintenance Qualification of Cary 60 UV-Visible.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Styanly Anchan, David Ryan, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2024-10-17','2024-10-16','QC-053B','1. Procedure for operating, maintaining, and qualifying the Agilent Cary 60 UV-Vis spectrometer. 2. Includes steps for turning on the instrument, using Win UV-Vis software for sample measurement, and creating/editing methods. 3. Maintenance includes cleaning and annual qualification. 4. Daily and monthly in-house tests are required for operational qualification. 5. Data is saved automatically, and all activities are logged in the UV Instrument Usage Logbook.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. QC/ARD: Quality Control / Analytical Research and Development. UV-Vis: Ultra-violet-visible. LED: Light Emitting Diode. OQ: Operational Qualification.','To define the procedure for the operation, maintenance, and qualification of the Agilent Cary 60 UV-Vis spectrometer.','The procedure applies to the Quality Control and Analytical Research and Development (QC/ARD) Laboratory at Amneal Ireland.','1. All QC/ARD personnel must adhere to this procedure. 2. Personnel must be trained on the current revision of the SOP. 3. The Laboratory Manager ensures compliance and training. 4. Daily and monthly qualification tests are performed by QC/ARD personnel.','Revision: QC-053, Date: 19-Jul-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-053A, Date: 19-Jun-2019, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-19-073, Reason: Added new section 5.4.4, updated SOP with new Amneal logo, and removed references to appendices. Revision: QC-053B, Date: 12-Aug-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-054, Reason: Updated sections 5.2.1, 5.2.3, 5.2.4, 5.2.5, and 5.4.2.3, and removed references to QC-045. Revision: QC-053C, Date: 17-Oct-2024, CCF No.: CC-AMN-24-0203, Reason: Updated section 5.4.2.2.3 and revised UV Daily Qualification Form (FM-QC-090).','FM-QC-089: UV Instrument Usage Logbook. FM-QC-090: UV Daily Qualification Form. FM-QC-091: UV Monthly Qualification Form. QC-059: Administration of UV-Visible software.'),(108,'QC-054E','Operation, Calibration and Maintenance of Volumetric Karl Fischer Titrator (Metrohm 890 Titrando)','QC-054E Op, Cal & Main of Volumetric KF Titrator (Metrohm 890 Titrando).pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Ashok Gulati, QC/ARD, Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2022-03-02','2025-03-02','QC-054D','1. Procedure for operating, calibrating, and maintaining the Metrohm 890 Titrando Karl Fischer Titrator. 2. Includes steps for dosing, titre determination, sample analysis, and maintenance. 3. Titre determination must be performed daily and after reagent replacement. 4. Maintenance includes checking molecular sieves, seals, and septums, and cleaning the instrument. 5. All activities are logged in the Karl Fischer Usage and Maintenance Logbook (FM-QC-095).','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. RSD: Relative Standard Deviation. NMT: Not More Than. KF: Karl Fisher. IPA: Isopropyl alcohol. DI: Deionized water. Tiamo: Tiamo 2.5 multi software.','To define the procedure for the operation, calibration, and maintenance of the Metrohm 890 Titrando Karl Fischer Titrator.','This procedure applies to the Quality Control and Analytical Research & Development (QC/ARD) Laboratory at Amneal, Ireland.','1. Laboratory personnel must follow the instructions in this procedure. 2. The Laboratory Manager ensures compliance with this procedure. 3. Titre determination and maintenance activities are the responsibility of the analyst.','Revision: QC-054, Date: 21-Sep-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-054A, Date: 24-Aug-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-092, Reason: Updated sections 5.1, 5.2, 5.3, 5.4 for ensuring commands/entries are accepted. Revision: QC-054B, Date: 10-Dec-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-079, Reason: Updated sections for Tiamo software usage, removed touch controller instructions, and added maintenance checks. Revision: QC-054C, Date: 27-Jul-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-20-047, Reason: Updated sections 5.2.1, 5.3.8, 5.3.9, and 5.6.2/5.6.3 for maintenance and calibration failure handling. Revision: QC-054D, Date: 04-Feb-2021, CCF No.: AI-CC-21-011, Reason: Added section 5.1.12 for checking Platinum pins of the electrode. Revision: QC-054E, Date: 10-Mar-2022, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-0808, Reason: Corrected reference to Titrando 851, added note for KF titre determination failure, and renumbered sections.','FM-QC-096: Titre determination Form. FM-QC-095: Karl Fischer Usage and Maintenance Logbook. SOP QC-051: Metrohm 900 touch controller administration procedure. SOP QC-006: Review of laboratory records. SOP QC-082: Operational use of Tiamo Software. SOP QC-022: Control of Laboratory Instruments.'),(109,'QC-058D','Packaging Material Sampling Area Clearance and Sign-Off','QC-058D Packaging Material Sampling Area Clearance & Sign Off.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','Paul O\'Mahony, QC/ARD, Mattead Ryan','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2022-06-01','2025-06-06','QC-058C','1. Procedure for area clearance and sign-off for packaging material sampling. 2. Includes steps for area clearance after sampling and area sign-off before new sampling. 3. Area clearance involves removing all materials, utensils, and waste, and verifying cleaning. 4. Area sign-off involves verifying cleanliness, logbook completion, and equipment readiness. 5. All activities are documented in FM-QC-105 (Clearance Form) and FM-QC-106 (Sign-Off Form).','Area Clearance: A check and verification to ensure the area is free from any packaging materials, paperwork, printouts, or labels from a previous sampling activity. SOP: Standard Operating Procedure. QC/ARD: Quality Control / Analytical Research and Development. QA: Quality Assurance.','This document describes the area clearance/sign-off requirements for Packaging Material Sampling at Amneal Ireland.','This procedure applies to QC/ARD, QA, or Operations personnel involved in the area clearance/line sign-off required for sampling of Packaging Materials at Amneal Ireland.','1. Operations, QA, or QC/ARD personnel are responsible for area clearance after sampling and documenting on FM-QC-105. 2. QC/ARD or QA personnel verify area clearance and sign-off. 3. QC/ARD or QA personnel verify area sign-off before new sampling and document on FM-QC-106. 4. The personnel verifying clearance/sign-off must be different from those performing the tasks.','Revision: QC-058, Date: 06-Oct-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-058A, Date: 29-Jun-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-17-087, Reason: Removed references to MF-052 and added references to QC-061. Revision: QC-058B, Date: 26-Nov-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-20-104, AI-CC-20-094, Reason: Updated Amneal logo, removed references to appendices, and included QA responsibilities. Revision: QC-058C, Date: 29-Jul-2021, CCF No.: AID-CC-21-011, AIM-CC-21-019, Reason: Added Preventative Maintenance checks, removed references to finished product sampling, and updated forms. Revision: QC-058D, Date: 07-Jun-2022, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-1975, Reason: Added references to XP-33 and warehouse sampling area, updated cleaning verification steps, and updated forms.','FM-QC-105: Packaging Material Sampling Area Clearance Form. FM-QC-106: Packaging Material Sampling Area Sign-Off Form. QM-010: Unplanned Deviations and Investigations. MF-007: Area Room Cleaning Requirements in the Inhalation Facility. MF-008: Labelling of Material, Product, Room and Equipment. MF-009: Gowning Procedure for Entering and Exiting the Inhalation Areas. QC-061: General Requirements for XP-33 and Operation of XP-33 Sampling Booth. FM-MM-004: Material Stock Card. MM-003: Garbing Procedure for Warehouse Entry. MM-012: Warehouse Cleaning Procedure. QC-027: Sampling of Incoming Packaging Materials.'),(110,'QC-059B','Administration of UV-Visible Spectrophotometer Software','QC-059B Administration of UV-Visible software.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','David Ryan, QC (April 27, 2020), Paul O’Mahony, QC (April 22, 2020)','Kuldeep Joshi, QA','2020-04-07','2023-04-04','QC-059A','Administration tasks include creating/modifying groups, projects, users, user profiles, admin profiles, stations, and associations. Data backup and restore, archiving and retrieval, and audit trail reviews are also covered.','Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, Ireland. QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development. IT: Information Technology. HOD: Head of Department. SCM: Spectrophotometric Configuration Manager. Audit Trail: a system that traces detailed transactions. SDA: Spectroscopy Database Administrator. Project: A collection of test results related to a product or process. Stations: Identifier for spectroscopy equipment. Basic User: Limited functionality. Service: Supports vendor-related activities. Advanced User: Full functionality including system information. Administrator: Full administrative abilities.','To provide a systematic approach for the Administration of the UV-Visible spectrophotometer software in the QC/ARD laboratory at Amneal Ireland.','This SOP applies to the Administration of UV-Visible spectrophotometer software SCM and SDA used in the QC/ARD laboratories at Amneal Ireland Limited. It includes creating/modifying groups, projects, users, user profiles, admin profiles, stations, and associations, as well as data backup, archiving, and audit trail reviews.','HOD or designee ensures users are trained and have appropriate access levels. UV-Visible spectrophotometer software users and superusers must follow this procedure. IT administrators manage user access, data backup, archiving, and audit trail reviews.','Revision: QC-059, Date: 25-Apr-2018, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-059A, Date: 30-Apr-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-033, Reason: Correct numbering and removed references to Form FM-QC-075 and SOP QC-045. Revision: QC-059B, Date: 07-Apr-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-20-017, Reason: Updated Amneal Logo, removed references to FM-QC-113 and FM-QC-114, and added references to FM-IT-053 and FM-IT-054.','FM-QC-115: Periodic Review of UV-Visible software. FM-QC-116: List of UV-Visible projects for Archival and Retrieval. FM-QC-119: List of UV-Visible projects for Backup and Restore. QM-010: Investigation System. QM-005: Risk Management. QM-006: Failure Mode and Effect Analysis. IT-011: Computer System Incident Management. QC-053: Operation, Maintenance and Qualification of CARY 60 UV-Visible Spectrophotometer. QM-003: Training System. QC-006: Review of Laboratory Records. QA-011: On The Job Training. FM-IT-053: Access & Disable Electronic System Request Form. FM-IT-054: Log of User Access for Electronic Systems.'),(111,'QC-060A','Assignment of Use-By Date for Investigational Medicinal Products','QC-060A Assigning of Use by Date for Inv Medicinal Products.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','','03-Dec-2020 Paul O’Mahony, QC/ARD, 03-Dec-2020 Lorraine Henry, QA','03-Dec-2020 Kuldeep Ondri, QA','2020-12-03','2023-12-04','QC-060','1. The process for assigning a Use-By date to Investigational Medicinal Products (IMPs) is defined. 2. Considerations for assigning the Use-By date include the nature of the product, container characteristics, storage conditions, clinical trial timelines, and available stability data. 3. A minimum of 3 months of IMP batch data is required to extend the Use-By date. 4. Stability data must be continuously monitored, and any failures trigger an assessment under QM-035.','QP: Qualified Person as referred to in Article 49(2) and (3) of Directive 2001/83/EC. Amneal Ireland: Amneal Ireland Limited. IMP(s): Investigational Medicinal Product(s). COA: Certificate of Analysis. QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development. QA: Quality Assurance.','To define the process for assigning a Use-By date to Investigational Medicinal Products (IMPs) and to identify the considerations that shall be taken into account when assigning this Use-By Date.','The scope of this SOP is applicable to IMPs and Placebo products manufactured/Qualified Person (QP) released at Amneal Ireland Limited for clinical study purposes.','1. The Quality Department, in association with Product Development and QC/ARD, is responsible for assigning a justified Use-By date for IMPs. 2. QC/ARD is responsible for issuing the Certificate of Analysis for IMPs and recording the assigned Use-By date.','Revision: QC-060, Date: 07-Dec-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-060A, Date: 03-Dec-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-20-108, Reason: 1. Updated SOP and Forms to new template. 2. Updates to include new Amneal Logo. 3. Section 2.2, Added Placebo product to scope of SOP. 4. Section 5.1.6 added reference to any Use by Date or Extended Use by Date information and changes to such information shall be included in the Product Specification File (PSF) as per SOP QM-025. Changes to the PSF will be implemented as per SOP QM-013. 5. Section 5.2.6 added reference to MF-021 and GQS_0017. 6. Section 6.0, added MF-021, QM-013, GQS_0017.','QM-025 : Manufacture and Control of Investigational Medicinal Products. QM-030 : Batch Certification by a Qualified Person/Batch Release. QA-010 : Criteria for Assigning Manufacturing and Expiration date to finished product. QC-043 : Release of Results from QC/ARD Laboratory at Amneal Ireland. QM-035 : Quality Defect Reporting. Annex 13 : Rules Governing Medicinal Products in the European Community (Volume IV). FM-QC-110 : Assigning and Monitoring Use-By Date for Investigational Medicinal Products. MF-021 : Technology Transfer of Inhalation Drug Products. QM-013 : Change Control System. GQS_0017 : Technology Transfer – R&D to Manufacturing Site.'),(112,'QC-061G','General Requirements for XP-33 and Operation of XP-33 Sampling Booth','QC-061G General Req for XP-33 & Operation of XP-33 Sampling Booth.pdf','Amneal Ireland Limited','Mairead Ryan, QA','David Delaney, Paul Delaney MF, David Ryan, QC/ARD, Kuldeep Joshi QA','David Ryan, QC/ARD','2024-09-05','2027-08-03','QC-061F','1. All personnel must complete training for MM-003 and MF-009 before entering XP-33 and the Sampling Booth. 2. Only trained and authorized personnel are permitted to enter the sampling booth. 3. Visitors can only access the airlock (XP-02) and the dirty side of XP-33 under supervision. 4. PPE requirements include Safety Glasses, Hi-Vis, Safety Shoes, Gloves, Mop Cap, Blue Shoe Covers, Beard Cover (if applicable), Tyvek Suit, and Mask. 5. Sampling activities require two personnel: one to perform the activity and one to verify booth pressure. 6. The booth must be cleaned and documented before use. 7. Ethanol dispensing must follow SOP MF-107.','SOP: Standard Operating Procedure, PPE: Personal Protective Equipment, IPA: Isopropyl Alcohol, Amneal Ireland; Amneal Ireland Limited, Cahir Road, Cashel, Co. Tipperary, QA: Quality Assurance, QC/ARD: Quality Control/Analytical Research and Development','The purpose of this SOP is to provide the general requirements for entry into XP-33 and describe the steps required to operate within XP-33 and the Sampling Booth.','This SOP is applicable to all personnel entering XP-33 and performing tasks within XP-33 and the Sampling Booth.','1. All personnel entering and performing tasks within XP-33 and the sampling booth must operate in accordance with this SOP. 2. Personnel must report any faults or damage in a timely manner. 3. The Laboratory Manager ensures only trained personnel operate the equipment. 4. The Maintenance Supervisor ensures only trained personnel carry out maintenance work. 5. Amneal Pharmaceuticals ensures the room/facility is suitable for activities carried out in XP-33.','Revision: QC-061, Date: 22-Dec-2017, CCF No.: --, Reason: First Issued. Revision: QC-061A, Date: 29-May-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-052, Reason: Updated garbing and gowning requirements. Revision: QC-061B, Date: 31-Jul-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-080, Reason: Moved and updated gowning requirements. Revision: QC-061C, Date: 21-Sep-2018, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-099, Reason: Updated material movement reference. Revision: QC-061D, Date: 26-Nov-2020, CCF No.: AI-CC-18-140, AI-CC-20-104, Reason: Updated Amneal logo, removed appendix references, and updated gowning requirements. Revision: QC-061E, Date: 28-Jul-2021, CCF No.: AIM-CC-21-019, Reason: Added interlock requirement for sampling. Revision: QC-061F, Date: 19-May-2022, CCF No.: CC-AMN-22-1685, Reason: Updated packaging activity restrictions. Revision: QC-061G, Date: 2024-09-05, CCF No.: CC-AMN-24-4886, Reason: Added ethanol dispensing requirements.','MM-003 : Garbing Procedure for Warehouse Entry, MM-002 : Movement of Material between the Warehouse and Manufacturing, MF-009 : Gowning Procedure for Entering and Exiting the Inhalation Areas, MT-010 : Access Control Procedure, QC-027 : Sampling of Incoming Packaging Materials, QC-039 : Sampling Procedure for Ethanol, QC-058 : Packaging material sampling area clearance and sign-off, MF-107 : Procedure for Dispensing of Ethanol in XP-33, FM-QC-142 : Pictorial of Dirty and Clean Side of XP-33 with Demarcation Line, FM-QC-143 : Pictorial of Operating Ranges of the Magnabelic Gauges in XP-33, FM-QC-148 : Pictorial of Gowning Requirements for Entering XP-02 Airlock, FM-QC-149 : Pictorial of Gowning Requirements When Crossing the Demarcation Line and Sampling in the Sampling Booth, FM-QC-245 : Pictorial of Gowning Requirements for Sampling on the Dirty Side of XP-33 and Dispensing of Ethanol, FM-QC-259 : Pictorial of Gowning Requirements prior to Entering XP-33'),(113,'EHS-002A','Portable Appliance Testing (PAT) Procedure',NULL,'Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(114,'EHS-015','Life Cycle Analysis for the Purchase of SEU Equipment',NULL,'Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(115,'EHS-016','Energy Audit and Inspection Procedure',NULL,'Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(116,'EHS-022','Monitoring and Control of EnMs',NULL,'Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(117,'EHS-023','How to Secure Trays and Boxes onto Pallets Using Manual Wrapping Process',NULL,'Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(118,'EHS-024','Pregnancy Risk Assessment Form',NULL,'Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(119,'EHS-025','Life Cycle Analysis',NULL,'Amneal Ireland Limited',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
